eng_translation: I have seen. She is wearing a swimming costume and there is a plate with food on her side.

bem_transcription: Uku kwine kucishiba mumbali balipangamo notubusanshi utunoono apakutushisha umuntu nga afuma mukusamba.
eng_translation: There are even sunloungers at this pool.

bem_transcription: Abana babili akamulumendo nakamukashana nabekala.
eng_translation: These two, a young man and a young woman are sitting.

bem_transcription: Akamulumendo kena nakakwata icakwangasha kuminwe ico kalepuuta elyo akamukashana kaleangala mumenshi kalenyanta mumenshi.
eng_translation: A young boy has something that he is playing with and blowing into and the young girl is playing in the water.

bem_transcription: Elo apa aba abana babili bekele nipamwinshi wakwingila mu n'ganda.
eng_translation: These two are sitting on the house entrance.

bem_transcription: Nintenwa ifyo akamulumendo kafwele, kafwele ifyakufwala ifyafiita elo kabili mwapita nefya katapa katapa.
eng_translation: I love what the boy is wearing. He is wearing black clothes with green in them.

bem_transcription: Ine ntemenweko ulusapato kafwele, nakafwala ulusuma sana, ulwabuuta mwapita notwafiita, ne ntambo ishilipo ishabuuta.
eng_translation: As for me I love the shoes he is wearing. They are very nice, white in color with some black in them and have white laces.

bem_transcription: Akamwana akamukashana kalelye cisabo icakashika.
eng_translation: A girl is eating a red fruit.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati nakacitemwa icisabo kalelya pantu kalemoneka kwati nakomfwa bwino sana.
eng_translation: It looks like she loves the fruit she is eating because it looks like she is enjoying.

bem_transcription: Cishinka monafye ifyo kacitile pamenso, kaleumfwa ubundowe bwacisabo.
eng_translation: Very true. Just look at her face, She is enjoying the sweetness of the fruit.

bem_transcription: Elyo akamwana kena aka nakafwala nakamukame akakashika mumukoshi, kalikwata ne mishishi ishitali, bushe naumona?
eng_translation: This girl is even wearing a poll neck and she has long hair. Have you seen?

bem_transcription: Ee nimbona kalikwata imishishi isha yemba kunuma balishikaka nokushikaka
eng_translation: Yes I have seen she has beautiful hair and it's been tied to her back.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo bali mucibansa cakuteyelamo umupila ubushiku baleteya umupila.
eng_translation: Young men are at the pitch in the night playing football.

bem_transcription: Elo bonse nabafwala ifyabuta ukufuma ku mutwe ukufika fye na ku molu.
eng_translation: They are all wearing white from the head to the feet.

bem_transcription: Awe lolekesha bambi bafwele ifya fita te bonse abafwele ifya buta icilelangila fye ukutila pali amabumba yabili ayapusana.
eng_translation: Look closely, others are wearing black indicating that they are two different teams.

bem_transcription: Ee ca cine niwe walanda kwena muli naba fwele ifya fita elo cilemoneka cungulo.
eng_translation: You are right, others are wearing black and it is in the evening.

bem_transcription: Ni mu cungulo ee pantu nama liti nayabasanika lintu balteya umupila wabo.
eng_translation: Yes it is in the evening because even the lights are flashing on them as they are playing.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo nalala panshi mu mbali ya musebo.
eng_translation: A young man is lying on the ground on the roadside.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Nomba nga wlaolekesha bushe ulemona ukwati uyu muntu ali ba fye umutuntulu?
eng_translation: If you look closely do you think this person is normal?

bem_transcription: Awe talemoneka kwati mutuntulu uyu pantu... lolekesha bwino ifyo akwete.... ku minwe ne fyo abikile mu matumba cilemoneka nalimo te mutuntulu nakalya.
eng_translation: No he doesn't look normal. Just looking at what he has in his hands, what he has put in the pockets you can tell he is not normal.

bem_transcription: Uyu ni mbona te mutuntulu ka normal kena awe nakalya alelele pa fyakufwala pantu nga muntuntulu nga naya ku ng'anda mu kulala.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen that he is not normal because had he been normal, he would have gone to sleep home.

bem_transcription: Abantu ba sano bali ku ncende iya talala sana elyo kabili nafwala ne fya mpepo.
eng_translation: Five people are in a very cold place and they are wearing warm clothes

bem_transcription: Ifi ifya mpepo bafwele fyakuicingila ku mpepo pantu uku kulemoneka kwali talala sana kabili te fya mpepo fyeka naba fwala ne fimpompo.
eng_translation: These warm clothes are to protect them from the cold because this place looks very cold. They are also wearing helmets.

bem_transcription: Kunuma yabo kuli notu ma motoka tulya ba bonfya mu ncende iya talala nge iyi baliko.
eng_translation: There are also small vehicles that they use in cold places behind them.

bem_transcription: Ca cine elo iyi incende yaka ene kalifula ifimuti ifingi. Bushe naufimona?
eng_translation: Yes and there are a lot of trees in this place have you seen?

bem_transcription: Nifimona ifimuti ifya titikana elo na kabili aba bene bantu nafwala ne nsapo ishatikama pakuti impepo ibengila
eng_translation: Yes there are very thick trees and these people are wearing very thick shoes so that they don't catch a cold.

bem_transcription: Umuntu nakwela pe horse.
eng_translation: A person is on a horse.

bem_transcription: Nomba uyu muntu ninshi akwelele pe horse ninshi abankwe bali panshi?
eng_translation: But why is this person on a horse when the friends are just walking?

bem_transcription: Uyu muntu ni kapokola alecingilila icinkupiti ca bantu ukutalukako ku kufulungana.
eng_translation: This person is a police officer that is mantaining peace.

bem_transcription: Batata abali mupepi ne horse balemoneka abasekelela, bushe ninshi basekelele?
eng_translation: The man near the horse looks happy. What could be the reason?

bem_transcription: Nabonfwa bwino ku mulandu wakomona i horse
eng_translation: He is happy to see a horse.

bem_transcription: Abana abengi bali mu cikulwa naba kafundisha babo.
eng_translation: Children are in a room with their teacher.

bem_transcription: Aba abana bali abasnakana mu abalumendo kabili muli na bakashana.
eng_translation: These children are mixed with both girls and girls.

bem_transcription: Elo bakafundisha babo balepitamo ukuposha cila mwana
eng_translation: The teachers are going round greeting each child.

bem_transcription: Umu mu muputule umuli abana mulemoneka kwati mulalila ne cilimba nakalmo balashana nokushana abana
eng_translation: It looks like music is also played in this room where the children are and they dance.

bem_transcription: Pa mwinshi wa muptule wine napeminina na namayo malonda ulelolekesha pa bana
eng_translation: There is a woman guard at they entrance of the building that is looking after the children.

bem_transcription: shitata naimina naikata na ka chola kamawilo mu minwe yakwe
eng_translation: A man is standing holding a bag with wheels in his hands.

bem_transcription: Elo alemoneka uwa nsansa nakalimo naiminina pali abalemukopa icikope
eng_translation: He looks happy like he is posing for a picture.

bem_transcription: Abalemukopa icikope cilepala bamwebele ati sekeniko elo acensa nomba.
eng_translation: The one taking the picture must have told him to smile.

bem_transcription: Iyi incende aliko intu ya yemba nga nshi nomba mumbali ya musebo eminine awe kwena mulemoneka umwafiko.
eng_translation: The place where he is looks nice but the roadside has dirt around.

bem_transcription: Ifi ifiko fiponene ku fimuti ifi ifili mumbali ya musebo abene balonfwa ubuna'ngani ukufipyanga.
eng_translation: The litter is coming from these trees on the sides of the road. They feel lazy to sweep.

bem_transcription: Na mayo ali mu cibansa ca mupila naikata no mupila ku minwe.
eng_translation: A woman is in a pitch and is holding a ball in her hands.

bem_transcription: Uyu umupila akwete nalimo alefwaya ukwamba ukuteya nomba ilaya afwele ,Bushe kuti lya musuminisha ukuteya?
eng_translation: It looks like she wants to start playing. But can she play in that dress she is wearing?

bem_transcription: Ae ae teti ateye muli iyi indeleshi intu afwele cilepala kwati aletungilila fye abaletampa ukuteya umupila.
eng_translation: No she cannot play in that dress. It's like she just came to support the ones playing.

bem_transcription: Nalimo niwe walanda wee ca cine limbi alebatungilila fye elo icibansa caka ena caliba ica yemba.
eng_translation: You are right maybe she is just here to support. The pitch looks amazing.

bem_transcription: Elo apa ali ali fye mu pepi nakulya ukusangwa kekata wa mupila
eng_translation: This woman is near the goal post.

bem_transcription: Shitata ali mu muputle wa kwipikilamo alepekanya ifya kulya.
eng_translation: A man is in the kitchen preparing food.

bem_transcription: Umu mu muputle wakwipikilamo mwaliba ifintu ifingi ifyo batantinka pe tebulo.
eng_translation: There are a lot of things in this room that have been arranged on a table.

bem_transcription: Nomba bushe naumona ifya kulya fintu abikile pa mbale? Filemoneka ni finshi?
eng_translation: But have you seen that food on the plate. What could it be?

bem_transcription: Ifi ifyakulya filemoneka kwati ni cilemba elyo babikapo no mupunga.
eng_translation: This food looks like rice and beans.

bem_transcription: Elyo uyu umulumendo alemoneka ni nkungulume pantu umuputule wakwe uwakwipikilamo ulemoneka fye busanku busanku
eng_translation: This man looks like a bachelor because the kitchen looks messy.

bem_transcription: Umwana umulumendo ali ku paka uko abaice bangalila
eng_translation: A young child is playing at a children's park.

bem_transcription: Uyu uwana nanina napa ntambo epo ekele nakalimo alefwaya ukupeluka nomba ici te cimpelwa nakalaya.
eng_translation: The child is on the ropes and it looks like he wants to swing though this is not a swing.

bem_transcription: Elyo kunuma yakwe kuli na shitata cilepala kwati e wishi ulemulonda.
eng_translation: There is a man behind the child who seems to be the father keeping guard of the child.

bem_transcription: Kunuma yakwe kabili kuli no tumpelwa utwakashika.
eng_translation: There are also red swings behind the child.

bem_transcription: Elo umwana wakaena nacensa pantu natemwa fintu alecita.
eng_translation: This child is smilling because the child is happy with what is happening.

bem_transcription: Ba namayo, bashitata, abana abanakshi na bana abaume bali pa cikulwa cimo.
eng_translation: Men, women, girls and boys are at one building.

bem_transcription: Elyo nabekala mu mabumba bambi nabekala balelya bambi nabemininako fye tabakwete apakwikala
eng_translation: They are seated in groups. Others are seated and are eating while others are just standing, they do not have where to sit.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka abengi bafwele ifyapalana abakashana bane bafwele ifya kufwala fimo fine ifya makumbi makumbi
eng_translation: Many here are wearing similar clothes. Four girls are wearing similar blue clothes.

bem_transcription: Elyo aba bambi abashala bafwelefye ifyapusana pusana, cila muntu nefyo alefwaya.
eng_translation: The others are all wearing different clothes.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka kwati uku teku n'ganda kumyabo, bele fye kuncende imbi mukwangalila capamo.
eng_translation: It looks like this is not their place but they have just gone somewhere to have some fun.

bem_transcription: Abantu bali pabulendo nabanina mwishitima.
eng_translation: People are on a journey aboard a train.

bem_transcription: Bambi nabekalako elo bambi beminine fye.
eng_translation: Others are seated while others are just standing.

bem_transcription: Umbi namayo uwikele nalolesha kubalekopa icikope.
eng_translation: One woman who is seated is looking at the one taking a picture.

bem_transcription: Bushe bashitata aba abeminine teti bapona nokupona nga cakwebati ishitima lyaliiminine mukampampa?
eng_translation: Can't these men who are standing fall if the train made an emergent stop?

bem_transcription: Awe teti bapone no mulandu wakutila mumuulu we shitima kuli intambo no mwakwikata pakutila tabaponene nga cakutila lyaliiminine.
eng_translation: No there cannot fall because there are ropes and where to hold in the train so they cannot fall even if it stopped abruptly.

bem_transcription: Banamayo bali pa ciila baleshana.
eng_translation: Women are dancing at a function.

bem_transcription: Bonse fye umo babelele nabafwala ifitenge elo balemoneka abansansa.
eng_translation: They are all wearing wraps and they look happy.

bem_transcription: Elo cilepala nimfunkutu baleshana pantu bambi baletoota muminwe.
eng_translation: They are dancing a traditional dance of using the waist called 'imfunkutu' because others are clapping.

bem_transcription: Uyu namayo naibila sana, nakalimo eumfwile bwino sana pali bonse.
eng_translation: This woman has gone down low as she is dancing like she is the happiest of them all.

bem_transcription: Aba banamayo nabakwata utupepala pafifuba fyabo icilelengilila ukutila bafumine kwibumba limo line.
eng_translation: These women have papers on their chests indicating that they are from the same group.

bem_transcription: Shitata ali pancito ubushiku.
eng_translation: A man is working in the night.

bem_transcription: Umu ali mulemoneka nimumugodi, pantu nafwala ne cimpompo elo mulemoneka muli amabwe.
eng_translation: This looks like in a mine because he is wearing a helmet and there are rocks around.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka nishimaini pantu nefyakubombelamo fintu afwele filelangilila fye ukutila cilepala nishimaini.
eng_translation: He looks like a miner because even his work suit indicates so.

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati aleputula inshimbi pantu nakwata mashini yakuputwilako inshimbi muminwe.
eng_translation: It looks like he is cutting metals because he even has a grinder in his hands.

bem_transcription: Pantu ali akubula amalaiti ayalemusanikilako palifiita sana tekuti akumanishe nokubomba.
eng_translation: He can't work where he is without the lights because it is very dark.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo aleangalila kuncende iyatalala sana.
eng_translation: A young man is playing in a very cold place.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka nipa lupili apa ali pantu nafwala nefyakumucingililako nga apona.
eng_translation: It looks like he is on a mountain because he is even wearing something to protect himself in case he falls.

bem_transcription: Nakabili nafwala ifyakushelemukilako lintu aleangala ici cine icangalo kumoolu yakwe.
eng_translation: He is also wearing things for sliding on his feet.

bem_transcription: Elo uku kuntu kuncende iyi kulemoneka kwalitalala sana pantu kumwenafye kufyakufwala ifyo afwele.
eng_translation: Just looking at the clothes he is wearing you can tell that this place is very cold.

bem_transcription: Muminwe yakwe uyu umulumendo naikata utumuti tubili uto utulemwafwa ukulapindulula kuntu aleya.
eng_translation: He has two sticks in his hands to help him make turns as he is slidding.

bem_transcription: Abantu nabakwela pama horse.
eng_translation: People are on horses.

bem_transcription: Balemoneka kwati balepepekana bushe ninshi?
eng_translation: They look like they are racing not so?

bem_transcription: Nga balya abali kunse abeminine fye ninshi bena tabalepepekelako?
eng_translation: What about those who are standing outside why are they not racing?

bem_transcription: Emafunde ya bwangalo kwingilamo fye babili mucibansa.
eng_translation: The rules of the game demand only two to be inside at a goal.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo nabakashana bali pa cangalo cakucimfyanya ica lubilo.
eng_translation: Young men and young women are in a race.

bem_transcription: Ulu ulubilo lwakucimfyanya cila muntu ali palweka.
eng_translation: Each one is for himself in this race.

bem_transcription: Emulandu wine bonse pafifuba fyabo nabakwata apalembelwe impendwa pantu bali abengi sana.
eng_translation: That is why each one has a number written on the chest because they are many.

bem_transcription: Pali abalumendo nabakashana elo bonse nabafwala notusote.
eng_translation: There are young men and young women and they all are wearing hats.

bem_transcription: Nakabili bonse aba abalecimfyanya nabafwala ifyakufwala fyakubutukilamo pakutila bengacimfya bwino.
eng_translation: And all these competing are wearing running clothes so that they can run well.

bem_transcription: Shitata ali mucishiba ca menshi alewamyamo.
eng_translation: A man is cleaning in the swimming pool.

bem_transcription: Elo kumbali ya menshi kuli abalumendo batatu, babili nabeminina elo kabili umo aleenda.
eng_translation: There are three young men on the side of the pool who are standing, and one is walking.

bem_transcription: Elo ici cine icishiba bacipanga kwati ni pa cipooma ca menshi pantu kuli namenshi ayaleya mumuulu kwati yalepona kucipooma.
eng_translation: This pool is made like it is a falls because there is water going up and falling like a falls.

bem_transcription: Elyo aba abalumendo babili abeminine bafwele ifyapalana.
eng_translation: These two young men standing are wearing similar clothes.

bem_transcription: Kumbali kulya kuli umusebo, kuli abantu na bambi abengi abalepita.
eng_translation: There is a road behind there with a lot of people passing in it.

bem_transcription: Bashitata babili bali pamumana baleoba mato.
eng_translation: Two men are on the river helming a boat.

bem_transcription: Uku kwine kumbali yamumana kulemoneka kuli ne mpili ishitali.
eng_translation: There are even high mountains on the sides of the river.

bem_transcription: Nomba utumato banininemo mwati naumona ukutila tunoono sana?
eng_translation: Have you seen that the boats they are in are very small?

bem_transcription: Ca cine tunoono elo kuti twabaponya banwina nokumwina nga tabaishiba ukusamba.
eng_translation: Yes they are very small and they can drown them if they don't know how to swim.

bem_transcription: Nga cakutila utumato tu twalibudile nabakwata ifyakufwala ifyakubacingilila pakutila tabanwinine.
eng_translation: If these boats capsized they have clothes to protect them so that they don't drown.

bem_transcription: Banamayo nabaya mukusamba kumumana ukalamba.
eng_translation: Women have gone to swim at a very large river.

bem_transcription: Kumbali yamumana kwaliba umucanga uwingi sana.
eng_translation: There is a lot of sand in the sides of the river.

bem_transcription: Elo nakabili no mumana wakaena walipabuka sana.
eng_translation: And the river is very wide.

bem_transcription: Kumbali yamumana wakaena balibikako ne cipampa icilelangilila ukwebati bafwile baisunga bwino.
eng_translation: There is a sign on the sides of the river that tells them to be careful.

bem_transcription: Nga nalolesha mumuulu cilepala kwati ikumbi lya mfula naliteka pantu umuulu ulemoneka mfula mfula.
eng_translation: If I look at the sky, I can see that it's cloudy and rainy.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo bali cibansa cafyangalo baleteya icangalo.
eng_translation: Young men are at a play ground playing games.

bem_transcription: Ici icangalo baleangala calibe cashupa eico icilengele ukwebati bafwale ifyakuicingilisha.
eng_translation: This game is hard that is why they are wearing protective clothing.

bem_transcription: Cishinka nabafwala ifyakucingilisha umutwe wabo pakutila ameno tayasokweke nga cakutila balipunkene.
eng_translation: Yes they are wearing things to protect their faces so that they don't break their teeth when they collide.

bem_transcription: Ne nsapato bafwele nishilya ishkwebati kuti waba uwacingilishiwa nga cakwebati umo akunyanta.
eng_translation: The shoes too that are wearing are able to protect them even when they are stepped on.

bem_transcription: Elo pakuteye ci icangalo bafwala ifyakucingilila ififuba fyabo pantu ici icangalo calishupa sana.
eng_translation: When playing this game they also wear things to protect their chests because this game is difficult.

bem_transcription: Abantu abalumendo nabakshana bali mu muputule umo balelanshanyapo fimo.
eng_translation: Young men and young women are in a room discussing something.

bem_transcription: Elyo balelanshanya nabasha ne citunshi tunshi icilelanga ifyo balelanshanyapo.
eng_translation: There is even a screen projecting what they are discussing on.

bem_transcription: Elyo nakabili cilepa kwati niku kampani uku balefwaya amakwebo yaleya pantanshi emulandu wine balelanshanyishisha.
eng_translation: This looks like a company and they want to improve their business that is why they are having this meeting.

bem_transcription: Eico nangu balelanshya cilemoneka nabanaka.
eng_translation: They look tired even though they are discussing.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilapala kwati bonse balekutika kuli umo ulelanda uyu wine muntu cilepala kwati eulebatungulula
eng_translation: It looks like they are all listening to one person and it's like he is the one taking the lead.

bem_transcription: Abantu bali mucibansa ca fyangalo umo bacinfyanishisha ama motoka.
eng_translation: People are in a stadium where there are car races.

bem_transcription: Ici icangalo cilemoneka balicitemwa sana pantu abantu baliko nabafulisha.
eng_translation: People seem to enjoy this game a lot because there are just too many people here.

bem_transcription: Na kabili iyi motoka iyili pantanshi apa cilepala kwati eya wina naisha imyotoka shinankwe
eng_translation: It looks like this vehicle that is in front is the one that has won because it has left all the vehicles behind.

bem_transcription: Nomba icikope caka ena tacilemoneka bwino sana pantu abantu teti ubamone napa menso nakalimo uwakope takopele bwino.
eng_translation: But the picture is not very clear because you cannot even see peoples faces. Maybe it wasn't well taken.

bem_transcription: Nimbona naine pantu abantu balemoneka kwati bali mul ubilo elo ndemonapo na malonda uyo ufwele ifya katapa katapa.
eng_translation: I have seen, people seem to be running and I can see a guard there in green.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo batatu baleimba ulwimbo.
eng_translation: Three young men are singing a song.

bem_transcription: Umo nikasamuna elo babili balemwafwako.
eng_translation: One is the lead singer and two are backing him.

bem_transcription: Aba babili balelisha ifilimba fya nsale elyo lubali lumbi balemwafwako no kwimba.
eng_translation: These two are playing stringed instruments and helping him sing at the same time.

bem_transcription: Uyu umulumendo eminine pa ntanshi cilemoneka aletungulula abantu ukwimba pantu alelolesha ku ntanshi.
eng_translation: This young man in front seems to be leading the people in singing because he is looking in front.

bem_transcription: Elo natemwa ulwimbo luntu aleimba alelunfwa bwino sana mona fye ifyo asamwine mukanwa
eng_translation: He is enjoying the song that he is singing and he is happy. You can just see from the way he is opening his mouth.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo naimya isaka kumbali ya mumana.
eng_translation: A young man has raised a sack on the side of the river.

bem_transcription: Isaka emishe lilekoneka nalifina nakalimo muli ifintu ifya fina nganshi.
eng_translation: The sack looks heavy. It's like there are heavy things in it.

bem_transcription: Mwati naumona ukutila ku lumba lwa mumana kulemoneka ukwa fiko?
eng_translation: Have you noticed that the seashore looks dirty?

bem_transcription: Ee  nimbona cishinka pantu kulemoneka nakalimo abantu baposaika fye ifiko icipose pose.
eng_translation: Yes it's like people through litter and garbage there.

bem_transcription: Cipalle kwati fimbi ifi ifko fisa no mwela lintu umwela ukalamba ulepupa pa mu mana.
eng_translation: It's like this litter comes as the air blows onto the sea and is carried by the water tomthe seashore.

bem_transcription: Abantu nabaya mukusefya mukati ka musumba.
eng_translation: People have gone to celebrate inside the city.

bem_transcription: Kuli abantu abali pakati ka musebo abafwele ifya palana ebo abantu beshile mukutamba.
eng_translation: There are people in the middle of the road wearing similar clothes that people have come to watch.

bem_transcription: Elo bonse aba bantu abeshile mukutamba balemoneka fye abalubana lubana bambi napeta ku menso bambi nafwala imishishi isha pusana pusana.
eng_translation: All these people that have come to watch just look strange with painted faces and different hair wigs.

bem_transcription: Elto pali aba bene ableangala ifyangalo nga nalolekesha bwino nabapapa notufyola munuma napo nga balongelemo inshi kwatishi  nga baleya kwisa?
eng_translation: These people that are playing this game even have bags in their backs. I don't know what could be in them and where they could be going.

bem_transcription: Icimpapwishe cakutila pali aba abli mu fyangalo pali umwana umukashana uwacepesha sana nakwe nafwala fimo fine nabakalamba.
eng_translation: What is surprising of these playing the game is that there is a small girl who is wearing the same clothes as the older ones

bem_transcription: Na mayo naikala alebila.
eng_translation: A woman is seated and is sewing.

bem_transcription: Namayo wine alebilila panse?
eng_translation: Is she sewing from outside?

bem_transcription: Ee alebilila panse natantinka ni pantemba yakwe
eng_translation: Yes she is sewing from outside in her booth.

bem_transcription: Bushe ni finshi alebila?
eng_translation: What is she sewing?

bem_transcription: Alebila ifyakufwala, fyakufwala mu mpepo.
eng_translation: She is sewing clothes to wear in the cold.

bem_transcription: Utubana tubili utu balumendo natwiminina ukwabula ama sheti.
eng_translation: Two young boys are standing shirtless.

bem_transcription: Natufwala ne nsapato ishapalana kabili twiminie pa muulu we libwe
eng_translation: They are standing on a rock and are wearing similar clothes.

bem_transcription: Elo nakabili bonse babili bafwele amakaputula yamo yene.
eng_translation: And they both are wearing similar shorts.

bem_transcription: Elo kuncende bali aba abana kulemoneka ni ku mpanga pantu nkaufula ifimuti.
eng_translation: It seems these children are at the a bush because there are a lot of trees.

bem_transcription: No mu mwine bemine ni mumbali ya cimuti pantu ni mucintelelwe bali icimuti ecilebapela icintelelwe.
eng_translation: Even where they are standing us under a tree that is giving them the shade.

bem_transcription: Imbwa nailala pa mwinshi wa ng'anda.
eng_translation: A dog is sleeping at the entrance of the house.

bem_transcription: Apapene pantu ilele imbwa uku lubali kuli icitabo elo uku kumbi kuli akabotolo ka menshi.
eng_translation: Where this dog is sleeping there is a book on its side and a bottle of water on the other side.

bem_transcription: Apo ilele ni pakasalu cilepala kwati abene ba ng'anda ebaibikilepo akasu aka.
eng_translation: It is sleeping on a cloth and it seems like the owners of the house out that cloth there.

bem_transcription: Pa mwinshi epo imbwa ilele uyu umwinshi wakaena baliukula bwino sana balilembapo no tumashiwi.
eng_translation: The entrance where the dog is sleeping is well built and there are words written there.

bem_transcription: Elo imbwa uko iloleshe umutwe kuli ne mbale apo baibikile ifyakulya pabapo na kapu pambali.
eng_translation: There is a plate that they use to give the dog food where it's putting it's head and there is also a cup on the sides.

bem_transcription: Ba shitatat bali nakamwana akamukashana baleangalila mu matipa.
eng_translation: Men are with a girl child playing in the mud.

bem_transcription: Aka mwana nakafwala na majombo pantu kalenyanta mumatipa eico kafwalile ama jombo.
eng_translation: The child is even wearing boots because she is stepping in the mud.

bem_transcription: Elo bonse fye nafwala ama jombo pakutila amakasa yabo yelamba.
eng_translation: They all are wearing boots so that their feet do not get dirty.

bem_transcription: Elyo nakabili bonse fye bashitata ukubikilako fye nakamwana nafwala futi utusote.
eng_translation: And all the men including the child are wearing hats.

bem_transcription: Cimbi cakutila bonse aba abakalamba nabalamba umulandu wakutila amatipa yalebasbukila.
eng_translation: The other thing is all the men are dirty because the mud is splashing on them.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo naikala panse yacikulwa.
eng_translation: A young man is seated outside a building.

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati umu ni mu cipatala pantu mukati kuli nabatu abekele!
eng_translation: It looks like this is a hospital because there are even people sitting.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ukutila kunuma kwa uyu umulumendo uwikele panse kuli icipampa ca fyebo?
eng_translation: Have you seen that there is a sign with words on it behind this young man?

bem_transcription: Ee ca cine nimbona pa cimpampa caka ena balemelepo ati ubunga ubusuma elyo kabili kumbali ya cibi balibikako no mwakuposa ifiko.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen. it is written in the sign; "good mealie meal", And there is a trash bin on the side of the door.

bem_transcription: Mukati sana akamuputule molemoneka abantu kwati balepokelela fimo.
eng_translation: There are people inside the room and it looks like they are recieving something.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo nanina kucikuulwa alewamya amawiindo.
eng_translation: A young man has climbed a building, cleaning the windows.

bem_transcription: Elyo pakuwamye wiindo acitampilako abikapo ipofu lyasopo elo nomba aamba ukupishapo akantu akakufumishako sopo.
eng_translation: To clean the windows, he put soap on them and then started wiping them with a squeegee.

bem_transcription: Nakabili kuli icilemwafwako ukutila epona, kuli intambo iyo aikakile naipita mumusana napacifuba.
eng_translation: There is a rope that he has tied around his waist and his chest that is helping him not to fall.

bem_transcription: Kunuma yakwe kuli motoka iilepita mumusebo elo kabili kwaliba ne cikuulwa icitali.
eng_translation: There is a vehicle passing in the road behind him and there is also a tall building.

bem_transcription: Nimbona, teifyo fyeka nakabili incende baliisunga bwino sana pantu pali ulunkoto ulwayemba sana.
eng_translation: Not only that, this place has been well kept and has beautiful grass.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo no mukashana nabekala balelishe filimba.
eng_translation: A young woman and and a young man are seated playing instruments.

bem_transcription: Umukashana afwele akashati akamakumbi makumbi nakasote, elo umulumendo afwele ishati ilyabuuta.
eng_translation: The young woman is wearing a blue shirt and a hat and the young man is wearing a white shirt.

bem_transcription: Pambali yamulumendo pali nakachola umo alonga icilimba cakwe cintu alelisha.
eng_translation: On the side of the young man is a bag where he keeps his instrument.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka bekele munshi yacimuti kabili kunuma yabo icimuti cakaena cilemoneka calikwata notumaluba utwakashika.
eng_translation: And they are sitting under a tree which even has red flowers.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo nankwe nafwala akasote akafiita.
eng_translation: The young man is also wearing a black hat.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo naiminina pe libwe mumbali yakashiba.
eng_translation: A young man is standing on a rock near pool.

bem_transcription: Nafwala na insapato shakashika elyo kabili nakaputula iyakashika mwapita nefya buuta.
eng_translation: He is wearing red shoes and short with white in it.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ukutila amenshi muli aka kena kashiba yalemoneka ayalengama bwino?
eng_translation: Have you seen that the water in this pool looks very clean.

bem_transcription: Ca cine nimbona, yalemoneka ayabusaka bwino sana kwati nakalimo tamwaba nalimbwe limbwe mukati yamenshi.
eng_translation: Yes it looks very clean as if there is no algae inside the water.

bem_transcription: Elo eko ashintilile umulumendo wakaena nikucilibwe icikalamba icashinguluka akashiba.
eng_translation: This young man is leaning on a big rock that surrounds this pool.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Uyu uuli kuntashi nakwate ngoma nakakulishishako ingoma.
eng_translation: The one in front had drums and what to use to play.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ifisote bafwele kumutwe ifyo filemoneka?
eng_translation: Have you seen how the hats on their heads are looking?

bem_transcription: Ee, nimbona, kwena fiemoneka ifyafiita elo ifyapala kwati fyakwata amasenkebele.
eng_translation: Yes they look black and they look like they have laces.

bem_transcription: Uyu uukwete ingoma ena afwele icakufwala icakashika elo aba bambi bena bafwele ifyakufwala ifyafiita.
eng_translation: The one with a drum is wearing red clothes while the others are wearing black.

bem_transcription: Umwaume nanina pacikocikala icikakilwe kuli bakabalwe babili.
eng_translation: A man is seated on a cart being pulled by horses.

bem_transcription: Elo abantu abalepita mumusebo balemoneka fye abakwebe ati tacibapapwishe tabaposeleko na mano nakalya.
eng_translation: The people in the road are not surprised and they are not even paying attention.

bem_transcription: Nga bakabalwe aba babili bushe naumona ifyo balemoneka?
eng_translation: Have you seen how these two horses are looking?

bem_transcription: Ee nimbona balemoneka ababusaka balibuuta tuutu.
eng_translation: Yes they are looking very clean and white.

bem_transcription: Kunuma kwacikocikala nasenda nabantu bambi abo aletwalapo kumo.
eng_translation: He is carrying some people in his cart that he is taking somewhere.

bem_transcription: Abakashana babili nabanina pamuulu wacikuulwa mukutamba umusumba.
eng_translation: Two young women are on top of a building to watch the city.

bem_transcription: Uyu umusumba waliba uwayemba nga nshi pakati palipita nakamumana elo kumbali yamumana kwalipita namayanda.
eng_translation: This city is very good looking. There is a river that runs in the middle of the city and there are houses on its sides.

bem_transcription: Elo amayanda yakaena yalitantama bwino ukushinguluka fye akamumana konse.
eng_translation: The houses are well arranged around the whole river.

bem_transcription: Elo kumbali yamayanda kulubali kwaliba utumilundu twalikwata nee fyani ifilemoneka katapakatapa.
eng_translation: And there are hills ok the sides of the houses which have beautiful green grass.

bem_transcription: Aba abakashana babili nakabili ifyakufwala bafwele kunshi filemoneka ifyapalana kwati bashitile mumo mwine.
eng_translation: Additionally the clothes that these two are wearing below look similar as if they bought from the same place.

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti ca bantu cileenda nacikolongana.
eng_translation: A crowd of people is gathered and walking.

bem_transcription: Ngoyu tata uutangile pali bonse bushe eulebatungulula?
eng_translation: What about this man in front is he the one leading them?

bem_transcription: Ee, eulebatungulula inshila yakwenda.
eng_translation: Yes he is leading the way.

bem_transcription: Ngoyo umbi umulumendo apapile chola nifinshi alecita?
eng_translation: What about this young man carrying a bag, What is he doing?

bem_transcription: Uyu umulumendo alekopa icikope abantu bene baleenda.
eng_translation: He is taking pictures of these people that are walking.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo nabemya fintu babomfya kukucilikilako inshila lintu balewamya umusebo.
eng_translation: Young men are raising barigates.

bem_transcription: Nabafwala nefya kubombelamo ifyapalana, fyonse ifyo bafwele fili ifyakatapa katapa elyo ne nsapato bafwele shili ishafiita.
eng_translation: They are wearing similar green work suits and black shoes.

bem_transcription: Pamushili palemoneka kwati imfula yacilaloka pantu palemoneka apaboomba boomba.
eng_translation: The ground looks like it was raining because it looks wet.

bem_transcription: Kabili kumbali yamusebo kuli abantu abaleculuka umusebo, bambi baleya uku lubali kabili bambi balebwelela ukulefuma abanabo.
eng_translation: And there are people crossing the road on the side. Others are moving from one end to the other and others are coming from that end to the other one.

bem_transcription: Aba bene bantu balepala kwati nabomfwe mpepo pantu nabafwala bonse ifyampepo ifyatikama.
eng_translation: These people look cold because they are all wearing jerseys.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo bali mucibansa baleteye cangalo camupila wakuminwe.
eng_translation: Young men are in a court playing basketball.

bem_transcription: Uyu uuleingisha umupila afwele ifyabuuta mwapita nefyamakumbi makumbi elo kabili panuma yakwe pali namashiwi ayalembekwe mufyakashika.
eng_translation: The one throwing the ball in the basket is wearing black with white in it and there is something written on his back in red.

bem_transcription: Elo abantu abengi nabesa mukutamba uko aba bantu baleteya ici icangalo.
eng_translation: Many people have come to watch this game.

bem_transcription: Kuli umulumendo umo uuli munuma ya uyu uulefwaya ukwingisha umupila cipalile nao alefwaya ukupoka umupila uyu wine alefwaya ukwingisha.
eng_translation: There is a young man behind this one who wants to score and it's like he is trying to get the ball so that he scores instead.

bem_transcription: Elo icibansa balicikuula bwino sana pantu mumbali mwalipita nomo amalaiti yaka.
eng_translation: This court is well built with lights around it.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo nafule shati elo aletolokela pamenshi.
eng_translation: A young man is shirtless and is jumping into the water.

bem_transcription: Nomba pa menshi yakaena mumbali mwaliba amabwe elo nga aliponene kuti aya ponena pamabwe aicena nokuicena.
eng_translation: There are rocks on the sides of the water and if he fell on them, he would hurt himself.

bem_transcription: Cishinka nimbona, amabwe yali mupepi sana napapene umulumendo alefwaya ukutolokela.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen. The rocks are closed see are close to where the young man is jumping from.

bem_transcription: Elo kumbali yamumana kumbali kwaliba impili ishitali sana.
eng_translation: And there are tall mountains on the sides of the river.

bem_transcription: Elo umumana ulemoneka uusuma sana kabili uwatekanya ukwabula namabimbi.
eng_translation: This river looks beautiful and calm without waves.

bem_transcription: Abana abli basano nabekala mumbali ya musebo.
eng_translation: Five children are seated on the roadside.

bem_transcription: Elyo ubushiku ubu bekele mu mbali ya musebo.
eng_translation: It looks like they are sitting there in the night.

bem_transcription: Umo pali bena nakwata ifya kulya mu cipepala elyo abankwe balemulomba.
eng_translation: One of them has food in a paper bag and the friends are asking for some.

bem_transcription: Cimbi abana bonse aba nabafwala ifya kufwala ifya fita.
eng_translation: Additionally all these children are wearing black clothes.

bem_transcription: Elyo aba abana balunfwisha uluse nakalimo bana banshiwa abekala fye mumbali ya musebo
eng_translation: These children look like they are orphans and street kids.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo naimya icipepala ku minwe ale-enda mu musebo.
eng_translation: A young man has a paper in his hands and is walking in the road.

bem_transcription: Elyo uyu umusebo kulapita sana imyotoka pantu kuli imyotoka ishingi.
eng_translation: This road looks like many drivers use it because there are a lot of cars behind.

bem_transcription: Nomba uyu umulumendo waka ena ale-endela pakati aa musebo pantu uku lubali kuli imyotokakabil no ku ulubali kulemoneka ifipe. Teti bamupunka?
eng_translation: This young man looks like he is walking in the middle of the road because there is a vehicle on his side and some materials on the other side. can't he be run over?

bem_transcription: Awe teti bamupunke muntu umukalamba sana tekumona fye na kasote afwele kalemoneka fye aka cikulile cikulile!
eng_translation: No he can't be bashed, he is an elderly person, you can tell from the hat he is wearing.

bem_transcription: Eya awe niwe walanda naulungika elo kumbali ya musebo balibikako no tushimbi uto bacingilila umusebo.
eng_translation: You are right, and they are some metal rods on the side of the road used to demarcate it.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo batatu nabeminina umo alelya ice cream elo babili balepanga
eng_translation: Three men are standing are standing, one is eating ice cream while two are making it

bem_transcription: Umo pali aba balumendo ufwele ifya fita eulepima fintu babomfya pakupanga ice cream.
eng_translation: The one in black is the one doing the measurements as they make the ice cream.

bem_transcription: Elo babili pali aba batatu ebaposeleko amano ukulolekesha mukwebati bamone efyo alecita umunabo.
eng_translation: The two are paying attention to what the other one is doing.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati alebambilisha ifya kupanga ice cream emulandu wine baposeleko amano.
eng_translation: It seems he is teaching them to make ice cream and that's why they are paying attention.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili abalumendo baka ena bonse umu babelele balikwata imishishi ishafita nga nshi elyo ishitali nakalimo kwati te balumendo.
eng_translation: And all of them have long black hair as though are not men.

bem_transcription: Uku niku citesheni ukwikilila abantu aba pusana pusana nga bafuma ukwa pusana pusana.
eng_translation: This station is full of people that come from different places.

bem_transcription: Ku citesheni uku bonse abantu nabakwata utufyola bambi elyo baleya mukunina elyo bambi elyo balebwela.
eng_translation: This station is full of people with bags, some are about to board while others are dropping off.

bem_transcription: Elyo nga walolekekesha bambi nabekalako pa fyola fyabo elyo bambi bekelepo fye panshi baletusha.
eng_translation: Others are sited on their bags while others are sited on the floor.

bem_transcription: Aba abekele cilemoneka kwati balelolela bashi ukutila ingesa mukubasenda.
eng_translation: It seems the ones sited are waiting for a bus to come and pick them.

bem_transcription: Kuli aba bene bekele kuli na mayo umo uwikele na bana bakwe uku lubali kuli umwana umulumendo elyo uku lubali kuli umwana umukashana.
eng_translation: Among the ones sited is a lady with her kids, on one side is a boy while on the other is a girl.

bem_transcription: Umu ni mumbali ya musebo elyo balibikamo utumabwe utwa yemba sana.
eng_translation: This is along the road side where they have put small rocks that beautify it

bem_transcription: Elyo apalepwila utumabwe balibikapo akakulwa akanono umo batumina ba lamya.
eng_translation: There's a small phone booth mounted  just at the edge of the rocks.

bem_transcription: Mulya mwine batumina lamya muli shitata ifi uwiminemo nakalimo alefwaya kutuma lamya.
eng_translation: There's a man in a phone booth that wants to make a call.

bem_transcription: Elyo bushe naumona ifyo uyu wine shitata afwele?
eng_translation: Have you seen what this man is wearing?

bem_transcription: Ee nimbona afwele ishati lya kwata utubokoshi utwa buta kabili mwapita no twakashika.
eng_translation: I have it a white and red boxed shirt

bem_transcription: Abalumendo babili balesamba pakati ya mumana.
eng_translation: Two young men are bathing in the middle of the river.

bem_transcription: Balemoneka abansansa sana cilepala kwati bacunfwa sana ukukaba lelo amenshi yabomfwishako bwino
eng_translation: They seem very happy, it must be they fel so cold but the water has made them feel better.

bem_transcription: Kumbali ya mumana wine kwaliba ulupili ulukulu nga nshi!
eng_translation: There's also a huge mountain on the river side.

bem_transcription: Elyo pa muulu walupili paliba ifimuti ifingi sana.
eng_translation: They are lots of trees on top of the mountain

bem_transcription: Kabili icakulundapo fye mumbali ya mumana mwine mwaliba ne fimbawe ifikalamba nga nshi.
eng_translation: More to that, they are very big rocks on the river banks.

bem_transcription: Umukashana naikata isabi ku ndobo yakwe.
eng_translation: A lady has fish on her hook.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka ne nsansa pantu aka sabi aka akekete fye mu menshi ayali kunuma yakwe.
eng_translation: He looks happy because he got this fish from the water behind him.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili kumbali ya menshi yene kwaliba ifimuti ifingi nga nshi.
eng_translation: There's water on the side and lots of trees.

bem_transcription: Elyo umumana waka ena ulemoneka kwati tawapelela fye apapene walyendelela ukuya kuntanshi.
eng_translation: The river doesn't seem to end here but goes very far from here.

bem_transcription: Uyu umukashana alikwata imishishi ishitali nga nshi elo nafwala nakashati akafita.
eng_translation: The lady has long hair and is wearing a black shirt.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alepepa fwaka.
eng_translation: A man is smoking a cigarette

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu muntu, muntu wamusango shani?
eng_translation: What sort of person is this?

bem_transcription: Uyu muntu mushilika.
eng_translation: He is a soldier.

bem_transcription: Ngoku eminine ni kwisa?
eng_translation: Where is he standing?

bem_transcription: Nipamuulu wacikulwa.
eng_translation: On top of a building.

bem_transcription: Umukashana naikala eleimona mucilola.
eng_translation: A lady is sited while looking at herself in the mirror

bem_transcription: Elyo alemoneka kwati alebika fimo ifya buta ku menso yakwe.
eng_translation: She seems to have applied something white on her face.

bem_transcription: Kumbali yakwe uku lubali nabikako aka chola elyo kabili panshi nabikako utubotolo umo alefumya ifi ifya buta.
eng_translation: There's a mirror on one side and a bottle on the floor where she's getting the white stuff from.

bem_transcription: Mwati naumona ifya kufwala fintu afwele? Filemoneka shani?
eng_translation: Have you seen the clothes she's wearing, how do they look like?

bem_transcription: Filemoneka fye bwino pantu nafimucinga umubili onse ku muulu nawafwala akashiti akafita kalefika na mu mukoshi elyo kumolu akalitoloshi aka makumbi makumbi ne nsokoshi.
eng_translation: They look nice covering her body, she's wearing a black pole neck, a blue trousers and socks.

bem_transcription: Umukashana naimina pakati ya musebo nafwala amagalashi elyo alikwata ne mishishi ishitali.
eng_translation: A lady is standing on the road wearing glasses and has long hair.

bem_transcription: Elo eminine fye mupepi na motoka cilepala ni motoka yakwe.
eng_translation: She is standing next to a car, it seems that's her car.

bem_transcription: Kumbali ya motoka kulemoneka kuli notu maluba utwakashikila.
eng_translation: They are some red flowers on the side of the vehicle.

bem_transcription: Pantanshi ya motoka akasuba nakalotoka emualndu wine uyu umukashana afwalile na magalashi.
eng_translation: The sun is hitting the face of vehicle and that's why she's wearing glasses because it's sunny.

bem_transcription: Ca cine nakalotoka, eico cilepala kwati nakukaba nga nshi ecilengele afwale nakashati aka afwele.
eng_translation: Yes she has jumped and it looks like it is hot that is why she is wearing that mall shirt.

bem_transcription: Abakashana babili baleangala mumenshi.
eng_translation: Two women are playing in the water.

bem_transcription: Tebena fye beka kuli nabambi abali kunuma yabo abaleangalila mu menshi umu mwine.
eng_translation: There are not alone but there are other people too playing in the water.

bem_transcription: Elo kumbali kwaliba napakwikala ecilengele eico icilengele bambi bekaleko mumbali ya menshi.
eng_translation: There are seats around this water that is why others are sitting.

bem_transcription: Ici icishiba bacipangilafye ukwakwangalila abantu abalefwaya ukusamba.
eng_translation: This pool has been made for people who want to swim.

bem_transcription: Kabili kuli iyi yine incende kwalifula nefimuti, eico nangu ulefwaya ukutushisha munshi yacimuti kuti watuusha.
eng_translation: There are a lot of trees in this place such that you can rest under any of them if you want to.

bem_transcription: Namayo nalela umwana wakwe naikala pa mwinshi wang'anda.
eng_translation: A woman has her baby on her laps and is sitting on the entrance of the house.

bem_transcription: Elyo umwana wakwe amufwalike ifyakashika kumuulu na kunshi.
eng_translation: The child is dressed in a red top and bottom

bem_transcription: Bonse babili pali uko balelolesha nakalimo bamona cimo.
eng_translation: Both are looking somewhere, it's like they have seen something.

bem_transcription: Elyo nafuti ing'anda yakaena yashingulukwa namaluba.
eng_translation: And this very house is surrounded by flowers.

bem_transcription: Eico cine cilelenga ukwebati napamwinshi pene pabikepo iluba.
eng_translation: That is why there is even a flower on the entrance.

bem_transcription: Umukashana nafwala ifyakufwala ifyakwata amakaala yapusana pusana.
eng_translation: A young woman is wearing something with different colours.

bem_transcription: Nimbona uyu muntu nafwala kumutwe abikileko kaala imbi, kumaboko kuli kaala imbi, kumenso kuli kaala imbi.
eng_translation: I have seen she has a different color on her head, arms and face.

bem_transcription: Elo nga walolesha nakwata napintu kukanwa iyamakumbi makumbi.
eng_translation: If you look closely he even has a green whistle in the mouth.

bem_transcription: Kunuma yakwe kulemoneka naba baluni abapusana pusana, abayemba bwino sana.
eng_translation: There are a number of nice different balloons behind him.

bem_transcription: Kabili kunuma yakwe kwine balicingililako ne fisalu ifyakatapakatapa.
eng_translation: There are cloths put behind her.

bem_transcription: Banamayo babili nabeminine panse yacikuulwa baleshimika, elo shitata umo nakwata namaluba muminwe.
eng_translation: Women are standing outside a building chatting, and there is a man holding flowers.

bem_transcription: Ici icikuulwa cilemoneka kwati licalichi pantu shitata emo aleingisha aya amaluba emishe kuminwe.
eng_translation: This place looks like a church because it is where this man is taking these flowers.

bem_transcription: Banamayo bakaena bonse babili bafwele ifyabuuta elo shitata afwele shati lyabuuta.
eng_translation: Both women are wearing white where as the man is wearing a white shirt.

bem_transcription: Ici cine icikuulwa cakuulilwa fye mumbali yamusebo pakutila cilebangukila abantu ukucisanga.
eng_translation: This building is just on the roadside so people can easily find it.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili icikuulwa cakaena cilemoneka cikalamba sana mukati na kunse.
eng_translation: The building looks very big both inside and outside.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo bali mucikuulwa, bambi baleimba elo bambi balelisha ifilimba.
eng_translation: Young men are in a building, others are singing while others are playing instruments.

bem_transcription: Uuleimba pali aba ni uyu uufwele icakashika elo kunshi afwele itoloshi yafiita.
eng_translation: The one singing if these is the one wearing a red shirt and a white trousers.

bem_transcription: Na ulya wine uuli akatalamukila uufwele icabuuta nao wine aleimba elo napacibumba pali icikope.
eng_translation: Even the one at a distance wearing white is also singing. There is also a picture on the wall.

bem_transcription: Aba babili abekele panshi bena balelisha ifilimba fyansaale.
eng_translation: The two seated below are playing stringed instruments.

bem_transcription: Pantashi ya aba bene abalumendo abalelishe filimba balibikapo ne tebulo epo babikile ifipepa.
eng_translation: In front of where these men playing instruments are is a table where they have put papers.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo abengi bali mucibansa baleteya umupila wakuminwe.
eng_translation: Young men are in a pitch playing rugby.

bem_transcription: Mucibansa baleteyelamo, cibansa icamatipa pantu nabalamba bonse.
eng_translation: This pitch is muddy because they are dirty.

bem_transcription: Mumbali yacibansa muli abalumendo abeminine balekopa icikope.
eng_translation: There are young men standing and taking pictures ok the ends of the pitch.

bem_transcription: Aba bakateya nababuungana pamo pakutila bengapangana fintu balacimfya ici cangalo.
eng_translation: The players have gathered to plan how they will go about the game in order for them to win.

bem_transcription: Kunse yacibansa kwaliba noko abantu bengabika imyotoka shabo aba bantu abeshile mukutamba ubu bwangalo.
eng_translation: There is a car park outside this pitch.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo babili baleangala ubwangalo bwakucimfyanya namacinga.
eng_translation: Two young men are in a cycling competition.

bem_transcription: Uyu uuli kuntashi cilepala kwati ewalawina pantu nacofesha sana.
eng_translation: The one in front looks like he will win because he is leading.

bem_transcription: Kunuma ya uyu uuli panuma ya uyu uuli pantashi kuli abantu abaletamba.
eng_translation: There are people that are watching that are behind these two.

bem_transcription: Elyo muntu balecofela aya yene amacinga nimumusebo fye, balepita namufikuulwa ifyo bakuula.
eng_translation: They are cycling on the road, and passing by buildings.

bem_transcription: Muli uyu wine umusebo balibikamo notushimbi utwakucingilila aba abalecofa amacinga pakutila tabafumine munshila.
eng_translation: They have put metal bars on the side of this road to protect the cyclists from going off track.

bem_transcription: Uyu ni shitata ali pamuulu walupili nafwala nefya makumbi makumbi.
eng_translation: This one standing on a mountain wearing blue clothes is a man.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka nanaka sana pantu pamuulu ali patali sana
eng_translation: He looks tired because where he is is very high.

bem_transcription: Mumbali yalupili mulemoneka nakamumana akanoono kaliya kalipita.
eng_translation: There is a small stream on the side of the mountain.

bem_transcription: Elyo kulya ukulolele akamumana kulemoneka impili shimbi ishilemoneka fye na fube fube.
eng_translation: There seems to be other mountains where this small stream heads though they are covered by mist.

bem_transcription: Pamuulu walupili pene palemoneka palitalala pantu nafwala necampepo elyo ne cimpompo kumutwe.
eng_translation: The top of the mountain looks cold because he is wearing a jersey and a helmet.

bem_transcription: Abantu nabeminina pamushili uwabeeka.
eng_translation: People are standing on a shinny ground.

bem_transcription: Bushe ninshi umushili ulebeekela?
eng_translation: Why is it shiny?

bem_transcription: Umushili ulebeekela kumulandu wakuti imfula yaciloka.
eng_translation: It is shiny because it was raining.

bem_transcription: Ngeyi ntemba ili kunuma yabo bushe ni ntemba yanshi?
eng_translation: What about that booth behind them. What sort is it?

bem_transcription: Iyi incende bemininepo yakushita ifyakulya.
eng_translation: The place where they are standing is for buying food.

bem_transcription: Bawishi no mwana nabeminina pabulalo.
eng_translation: A father and a child are standing on a bridge.

bem_transcription: Bonse nabafwala utumagalashi bushe kuti twaba twanshi utu?
eng_translation: They are both wearing glasses, what could they be for?

bem_transcription: Bafwalile amagalashi kumulandu wakushupikwa na menso mulusuba.
eng_translation: They are wearing glasses because of eye problems when it is sunny.

bem_transcription: Uko beminine kulemoneka nakuwama, kulemoneka impanga mpanga, nga cilya icili kunuma icilemoneka white white bushe nicinshi?
eng_translation: The place looks and has a forest. But what could that whitish thing behind be?

bem_transcription: CIlya cili kunuma icilemoneka icabuuta cipooma camenshi.
eng_translation: That whitish thing behind is a falls.

bem_transcription: Na mayo ali na shitata bale-enda.
eng_translation: A woman is walking with a man.

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati uko baleya kuli ifisuma pantu nabendesha balekumpauka pa kwenda.
eng_translation: It looks like there is something nice where they are going because they are moving at a fast pace.

bem_transcription: Na mayo afwele ishati lya fita elyo ne toloshi liya makumbi makumbi elyo kabili shitata afwele ishati ilya buta ne toloshi ilya makumbi makumbi
eng_translation: A woman is wearing a black shirt and a blue trousers while a man is wearing a white shirt and a blue trousers

bem_transcription: Pantu balenyanta palemoneka pali amenshi eco kanshi pafwile ukutelela emualandu wine babikilepo ne cipampa icakubeshibisha ukutila bafwile ukwenda bwino.
eng_translation: There is water where they are stepping and it is slipperly that is why there is a sign telling them to walk carefully.

bem_transcription: Elo umu ni mukati ya cikulwa elyo ku cibuimba balibikako ne cikope.
eng_translation: This looks like inside a building and there is a picture on the wall.

bem_transcription: Bashitata babili na namayo umo baletema ifimuti.
eng_translation: Two men and a woman are cutting trees.

bem_transcription: Uyu na mayo alemoneka nanaka aiminina kumbali pakutila engayololako.
eng_translation: This woman looks tired and that is why she is standing on the side so that she can stretch a bit.

bem_transcription: Ukubaletema ifimuti ni kumbali ya musebo elyo pa musebo nabikapo ne cakulesha imyotoka ukupita.
eng_translation: They are cuttung trees near the road and they have put a sign to stope vehicles from passing.

bem_transcription: Aba bonse batatu nabafwala ma sheti yakatapa katapa.
eng_translation: All three are wearing green shirts.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Umulumendo naiminina na papa naka chola paciteshini.
eng_translation: A young man is standing at the station with a big on his back.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilepala kwati alelolesha aba bantu abali kuntanshi yakwe abalelolesha kuli ena.
eng_translation: It looks like he is looking at these people in front of him that are facing torwards him.

bem_transcription: Elo kabili kunuma ya aba bene batatu abalelolesha umulumendo ku na bantu na bambi abengi.
eng_translation: There are also other people behind these three that are looking at the young man.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ifya kufwala ifyo umulumendo afwele?
eng_translation: Have you seen the clothes this young man is wearing?

bem_transcription: Ee nimbona nafwala akasote abikapo ne campepo cilemoneka nakalimo nakutalala sana
eng_translation: Yes he is wearing a jersey and a hat. It looks like it is cold.

bem_transcription: Umukashana ali mu muputule wa kwipikilamo.
eng_translation: A young woman is in the kitchen.

bem_transcription: Ifya kulya fintu aleipika fingi sana pantu impoto aleipikilamo ikalamba.
eng_translation: She is preparing a lot of food because she is using a very big pot.

bem_transcription: Tempoto fye iyo aleipikalamo ikalamba neyo iyo abikile ku kulyo nayo ine ikalamba.
eng_translation: The pot on her right too is big.

bem_transcription: Mu muputule umu namwisula icushi cileya na mumalata
eng_translation: There is a lot of smoke in the room going to the roof.

bem_transcription: Elyo uleipika wine nafwala icitambala ku mutwe pakweba ati imishishi shilaponena mu fyakulya aleipika.
eng_translation: And the one cooking has a head wrap so that hair doesn't go into the food she is preparing.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Elo cilepala kwati kwaciba ifikansa ifyakakala sana pantu kuli no mulilo.
eng_translation: It seems there was a lot of violence and fighting because there is even fire.

bem_transcription: Pamulandu wakuti kwaciba umulimo cilemoneka kwati ifintu ifingi nafipya.
eng_translation: It seems things have been burnt because of the fire.

bem_transcription: Elo bakapokola aba beshile mukulesha ifyongo pantu amayanda ayengi nga nayatobeka.
eng_translation: These police officers are here to stop the riots because a lot of houses have been demolished.

bem_transcription: Kunuma ya balumendo babili naku numa ya myotoka kuli na bambi abantu abalebutuka nakali nabo balebuka bakapokola.
eng_translation: Behind these two men and behind the vehicles there are people running from the police.

bem_transcription: Umukashana ali ku ncende ya kwangalilako naikata ne mbwa iyo akakile mu mukoshi
eng_translation: A young woman is at a play ground with her dog on a leash.

bem_transcription: Elyo uyu wine umukashana cilemoneka kwati afuma mukusamba pantu afwele kaputula iya fita.
eng_translation: It looks like this young woman is from swimming because she is in a black bikini.

bem_transcription: Kuntu ali kuli umucanga uwingi sana.
eng_translation: There is a lot of sand where she is.

bem_transcription: Kuntanshi yakwe kulemoneka na kayanda umo abantu bashita ifya kulya elo bambi nabalala pa mucanga pene.
eng_translation: There is a small house in front of her where people buy food. Other people are sleeping on the sand.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Umukashana naikala pakapuna mu muputule uwa kulilamo.
eng_translation: A young woman is seated on a chair in the dining room.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilepala kwati uku kulubali kuli umuntu umbi uo ali nankwe pantu nabakobekako ne cakufwala ku mupuando.
eng_translation: It looks like she is with someone on the other side because there is a clothe that has been hang on a chair.

bem_transcription: Muli uyu wine umuputule balikamo utupuna natumbi uto abantu bengekalapo  abalefwaya ukuwisa mukulya.
eng_translation: There are other chairs in this room where people who want to come and eat can sit.

bem_transcription: Elyo mu mutule waka ena icibumba cakulilwa nama tafwali eyo baoca bwino nomba cilemoneka ica fiko pantu tacapentwa
eng_translation: The wall of this room is built using well burnt bricks but it looks dirty because it hasn't been painted.

bem_transcription: Uyu umukashana wikele wine afwele isheti ilya makumbi makumbi elyo amakapu yali pali tebulo yali ayabuta.
eng_translation: The same woman who is sitting is wearing a blue shirt while the cups that are on the table are white.

bem_transcription: Shitata nalala munshi ya cimuti.
eng_translation: A man is sleeping under a tree.

bem_transcription: Cilepala nanaka pantu mukote kumona fye nemfwi kukanwa isha buta tutu
eng_translation: He looks tired because he is old as can be seen from the grey beards.

bem_transcription: Nabika nakasote kakwe akabuta pambali elyo nekoto yakwe nayo nabika pambali.
eng_translation: He has even put his white hat and his walking stick on the side.

bem_transcription: Nomba fintu alelele, alelele nalolesha kumuulu wa cimuti nakalimo alependa amabula.
eng_translation: He is lying facing above like he is counting the leaves of the tree.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Shitata naiminina pakayanda eko bakulila ne mbao.
eng_translation: A man is standing on a wooden house.

bem_transcription: Elo cilemoneka akasuba nakamuma emulandu wine afwalile akasote aka kalamba ako akalemucingilila ku kasuba.
eng_translation: It looks like the sun hit him badly that is why he is wearing that dirty hat to protect himself from the brazing sun.

bem_transcription: Uyu wine shitata nafwala ishati lya buta kabili ne toloshi ilya fita.
eng_translation: This man is wearing a white shirt and a black trousers.

bem_transcription: Aka akayanda kantu bapopa ne mbao kashingulukwa ne fimuti ifikalmba nga nshi.
eng_translation: This wooden house is surrounded by big trees.

bem_transcription: Iyi ine incende ilemoneka yalibela ukuntu ukwafisama sana.
eng_translation: This place looks isolated and hidden.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo no mukashana nabeminina nabekata ne minwe.
eng_translation: A young man and a young woman are standing holding hands.

bem_transcription: Elo Bonse babili kuli ifyo balelolesha kuntanshi yabo cilepala kuli icintu ico bapapwishe.
eng_translation: It's like there is something they both are looking at in front that has surprised them.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona fintu bafwele?
eng_translation: Have you seen what they are wearing?

bem_transcription: Nombona leka ndande pa umulumendo, umulumendo afwele kaputula umupitile utwafita notwa kashika notwabuta elo kumuulu afwele ica mpepo ica fita mwapita no twakshika.
eng_translation: I have seen. let me start with the young man. He is wearing a short with black, red and white stripes and a black jersey with red stripes.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Namayo naikala aletamba.
eng_translation: A woman is watching while seated.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka naposa sana amano kufintu aletamba bushe kuti fyaba nifinshi?
eng_translation: It looks like she is concentrating on what she is watching. What could it be?

bem_transcription: Aletamba ubwangalo bwakumakasa.
eng_translation: She is watching a football game.

bem_transcription: Ngeshi intambo ekete kuminwe bushe nintambo shanshi?
eng_translation: What are these ropes she is holding in her hands for?

bem_transcription: Naikala alepikula, entambo ekete muminwe.
eng_translation: She is kneating. That is what those ropes are for.

bem_transcription: Shitata alikucibansa aleteya icangalo ca golf.
eng_translation: A man is playing golf.

bem_transcription: Elo uyu shitata cilemoneka alishibishe ci cangalo pantu nakontama bwino lintu aleuma.
eng_translation: This man looks like he knows the game  because he has a good posture as he is playing.

bem_transcription: Ici icibansa cisuma sana, balicisunga icabusaka sana.
eng_translation: This pitch is very nice and well kept.

bem_transcription: Nakabili cilemoneka kwati betilila cila bushiku pakutila cilemoneka icayemba, bushe naumona ukutila kuli ne fimuti?
eng_translation: It looks like it is watered daily so that it can look beautiful. Have you noticed that there are trees?

bem_transcription: Ca cine nimbona, elo ifimuti fyakaena nafyo fingi.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen and the trees are many.

bem_transcription: Shiata naimya umwana wakwe muminwe.
eng_translation: A man is holding a baby in his arms.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka kwati kuli ifyo aleipusha umwana wakwe pantu naisula akanwa.
eng_translation: It's like he is asking the baby something because his mouth is open.

bem_transcription: Nomba umwana wakwe uwakaena alemoneka nafulwa pantu pamenso palemoneka apafulwa.
eng_translation: But the baby looks angry on its face.

bem_transcription: Emulandu wine cilemoneka kwati wishi alemunyengelela pakutila engasekako.
eng_translation: That is why the man might be trying to make the baby laugh.

bem_transcription: Shitata yu alemoneka ali mu n'ganda no mwana pantu mulemoneka nomutenge.
eng_translation: It looks like this man is in the house with the baby because there is a roof.

bem_transcription: Abantu abengi bali mumusebo elo bonse nabakwata nemyanfuli.
eng_translation: Many people are on the road with umbrellas.

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati temumusebo mu, mwati naumona ukutila uku kumbali kuli nefyo baleshitisha?
eng_translation: It looks like this is not a road. Have you seen that theres even something they are selling on the side?

bem_transcription: Eya, niwe wasaso, tamulemoneka nga mumusebo, camoneka kwati nikumaliketi.
eng_translation: Yes you are right. Its not clear if it is on the road. It looks like a market.

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati imfula ileloka pantu bonse nabakwata imyanfuli kuminwe yabo.
eng_translation: It looks like it is raining because they are all holding umbrellas.

bem_transcription: Elo bonse abantu bali umu imyanfuli shabo nashibe shapusana, kuli abakwete ishakashika, ishabuuta neshafiita.
eng_translation: They all have different umbrellas. Some have red ones, others black, and others white ones.

bem_transcription: Shitata umo fi naikala pantu balungishisha amacinga.
eng_translation: A man is sitting where they repair bicycles.

bem_transcription: Uyu shitata tekele fye alelungisha incinga pantu incinga shonse shilemoneka nabashifulamika.
eng_translation: This man is not only sitting, but also repairing bicycles because they are all upside down.

bem_transcription: Nakuba tali eka pantu ndemona kuli naumbi shitata uwikele uku lubali.
eng_translation: And he is not alone. There is another man on the side.

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati iyi kampani balungishako fye incinga sheka sheka.
eng_translation: It looks like they only repair bicycles at this company.

bem_transcription: Elo bashitata bonse babili aba bekele bafwele ifyafiita.
eng_translation: Both men who are seated are wearing black.

bem_transcription: Shitata naiminina kumbali yamusebo naikata nefipepa.
eng_translation: A man is standing on the side of the road holding papers.

bem_transcription: Uyu shitata cilepala kwati kuli ifyo alelondolola pantu naasamuna akanwa.
eng_translation: It looks like this man is explaining something because he is opening his mouth.

bem_transcription: Elo cilepala kwati alelangisha abantu umutengo wamapepa pantu naimya ukuboko.
eng_translation: It looks like he is showing people the prices for the papers because he is raising his hands.

bem_transcription: Uyu uko aleshitishishe fipepa fyakwe nimukalale umu.
eng_translation: He is selling his papers in town.

bem_transcription: Ca cine nimukalale pantu kunuma yakwe kulepite myotoka, kuli nefikuulwa ifitali.
eng_translation: It is true that this is in town because there are cars passing and there are tall buildings.

bem_transcription: Shitata ali pamuulu wacikuulwa naikata necisalu icitali.
eng_translation: A man is on top of a building holding a big cloth.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka kwati alefwaya ukucifungulula pakuti abantu balemona ifyalembwapo.
eng_translation: It's like he wants to unfold it so that people can read what's written on it.

bem_transcription: Pamuulu wacikuulwa ici cine pantu eminine paliba notushimbi uto batantalika.
eng_translation: There are also metal bars lined up where his standing.

bem_transcription: Utu tushimbi balitukuula ukushinguluka fye icikuulwa conse pakuti umuntu taponene.
eng_translation: These bars are put all around the building so that a person may not fall.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Abalumendo bali mucibansa baleteya umupila wakumoolu.
eng_translation: Young men are in a pitch playing football

bem_transcription: Nomba cilepala kwati uyu kalisha wamupila eo bola yumine.
eng_translation: But it's like the ball has hit the referee.

bem_transcription: Ee, euyumine, pantu bonse abaleteya umupila eo balelolesha balemoneka nakalimo nacibapapusha.
eng_translation: Yes it is true because everyone is looking at him and theyharr surprised.

bem_transcription: Mwati naumona ifyo icibansa camupila ciiswile?
eng_translation: Have you seen how full this stadium is?

bem_transcription: Nimbona, awe kwena naciisula abantu nabesa mukutamba abengi, elo icibansa cakaena caliwama nga nshi cilemoneka icabusaka.
eng_translation: I have seen that it is full. A lot of people have come to watch the game. This particular stadium is beautiful too.

bem_transcription: Abana batatu bali mu n'ganda nabekala napacipuna.
eng_translation: Three children are in a house seated on a chair.

bem_transcription: Elyo uwikele pakati nafimba abanakwe pamenso.
eng_translation: The one seated in the middle has covered the others eyes.

bem_transcription: Elo kunuma yabo balitantikako namabuuku ayengi sana.
eng_translation: There are a lot of books parked behind them.

bem_transcription: Uyu wikele pakati cilepala kwati kuli ifyo alelolesha kuntashi ifyakutiinya pantu nabifya pamenso.
eng_translation: it looks like the one in the middle is looking at something horrifying in front because of the face she has made.

bem_transcription: Kabili kunuma yabo pewiindo palemoneka pali ne mbwa iilelengela.
eng_translation: Behind them is a dog peeping on the window.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo ali pakati ya musebo alekunkulusha incinga.
eng_translation: A young man is in the middle of the road carrying his bicycle.

bem_transcription: Elyo kunuma ya ncinga nakakililako fimo ifilemoneka ifyafina sana.
eng_translation: There is something he has tied to the back of the bicycle which looks heavy.

bem_transcription: Kabili uku kwine ali nga twalolesha akatalamukila kuli namotoka iyo beminike.
eng_translation: There is also a parked vehicle at a distance if we look closely.

bem_transcription: Temotoka fye yeka kuli napakwikala apekele umuntu umo mupepi fye namotoka.
eng_translation: There is also a sitting place where one person is seated near the vehicle.

bem_transcription: Elo kuncende yakaena kulemoneka kwalifule fimuti pantu nafifulisha.
eng_translation: And there seems to be a lot of trees in the same place.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo batatu bali mu cibansa ca fyangalo.
eng_translation: Three young men are in a play ground.

bem_transcription: Nomba cilemoneka kwati umo pali aba acisangwa mu busanso elo napona.
eng_translation: It looks like one of them was in an accident and fell.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka uyu umulumendo ufwele ifya buta aya mukumwafwako ukwima.
eng_translation: And it looks like the young man in white is going to help him.

bem_transcription: Elyo kuli na umbi uyu uwabutukilako mukumwafwa pantu naimyako na fimo kwati ka chola umuli umuti ku maboko.
eng_translation: And there is another one going to help him who is carrying a bag with medical supplies.

bem_transcription: Nga twalolekesha bwino mucibansa caka ena tamuli na bantu aba kweba ati bengatamba ubu ubwangalo.
eng_translation: When we look closely, there are no people in this stadium that are watching the game.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu nakwela pe horse.
eng_translation: An old man is riding a horse.

bem_transcription: I horse line lilemoneka nalima bushe lilefwaya ukuposa shikulu bantu panshi?
eng_translation: The horse has jumped. Is it the old man it wants to throw out of its back?

bem_transcription: Ee lilfwaya ukuposa panshi ku mulandu wakweba ati alilikapa ubwembya.
eng_translation: Yes it want to throw him because he hit it with a whip.

bem_transcription: Nomba ninshi alelikapila. Bushe finshi limucitile?
eng_translation: But why did he whip it. What did it do?

bem_transcription: Acilalikapa pa mulandu wakuti lubutuke.
eng_translation: He whipped it so that it runs faster.

bem_transcription: Umukashana naiminina panse yacikulwa alepepa fwaka.
eng_translation: A young woman is standing outside a building smoking.

bem_transcription: Elyo panse yacikulwa pali nakapuna ka kwikalapo.
eng_translation: There is even a chair outside the building.

bem_transcription: Elyo pantu eminine uku kukulyo nabikako ne fyakulya fintu alelya.
eng_translation: On her right is where she has put the food she's eating.

bem_transcription: Nomba panse pa mushili palemoneka apa fiko fiko notushiki twa fwaka utwingi sana.
eng_translation: The ground outside the building looks dirty with a lot of cigarette butts.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili panse pene bali byalikapo notumaluba utusuma sana.
eng_translation: There are also beautiful flowers outside.

bem_transcription: Umukashana ali mucibansa aleangasha umupila uwafita.
eng_translation: A young woman is in the pitch playing with a black ball.

bem_transcription: Elyo pakati kacibansa paba fye umucanga weka weka.
eng_translation: There is only sand in the middle of the pitch.

bem_transcription: Elyo nga naulolekesha bwino mumbali ya cibansa emwaba ifyani.
eng_translation: If you have noticed the grass is on the edges of the pitch.

bem_transcription: Nimbona elyo cilemona kwati ifi fine ifyani balafitapilila cila bushiku pakutila filemoneka bwino sana.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen and it looks like the grass is watered daily to continue looking good.

bem_transcription: Ku ncende yaka ena kulemoneka kabili kwaliba ifimuti ifingi ifya katapa katapa.
eng_translation: There also seems to be alot of green trees around the place.

bem_transcription: Shitata ali mu muputule emo bapimina ifintu ifya pusana pusana.
eng_translation: A man is in a room where they measure different things.

bem_transcription: Elyo ni mbona alelolesha muli mashini imo ilya iikusha utuntu tunono ukutulenga ukumoneka ifikalamba.
eng_translation: And I have seen that he is looking into a microscope.

bem_transcription: Kabili petebulo apa mashini nabikapo na amapepa kabili nama buku.
eng_translation: He has even put books and papers on the table where the machine is.

bem_transcription: Kabili pali notubotolo umo abikile fintu alepima.
eng_translation: There are even bottles where he had put what he is testing.

bem_transcription: Kabili ku cibumba kulemoneka balikulilako apakubika umuti mutu pepala.
eng_translation: There is something built on the wall where they put medicines in small sacks.

bem_transcription: Umukashana naiminina pakati ya musebo.
eng_translation: A young woman is standing in the middle of the road.

bem_transcription: Elyo kuminwe yakwe naikata icakufwala ica fita.
eng_translation: She is holding a black clothe in her hands.

bem_transcription: Ku numa yakwe kulisa umulumendo uninine pali Honda.
eng_translation: Their is a young man on a motorcycle coming from behind her.

bem_transcription: Nimbali ya musebo mwaliba utumuti uto batantamika mu muline umo wine.
eng_translation: There are trees lined on the sides of the road.

bem_transcription: Kumbali uku kuli na bantu abalepita.
eng_translation: There are also people passing on the sides of the road.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo batatu bali mwituka elyo bashitishamo ifyela fya ku njinga.
eng_translation: Three young men are in a shop where they are selling bicycle spares.

bem_transcription: Nimbona pantu ku muulu nbakobekako nama taila ya njinga elo nefibombelo fye fimbi.
eng_translation: Yes I have see because there are even bicycle tires that have been hang on top together with other things.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Uyu umulumendo uwimine mupepi nowikete lamya ku minwe alemoneka uwa sekelela cilepala kwati emwine we tuka.
eng_translation: The young man who is standing next to the one with a phone looks very happy. It's like he is the owner of the shop.

bem_transcription: Elyo umulumendo uwikalile mupepi ne window ena taposeleko na mano kufilecita abankwe ekele fye eka mumbali.
eng_translation: The other one seated near the window is just sitting there minding his own business.

bem_transcription: Umulumenndo umo ali mundeke eylo umbi aleangala icangalo cakushelela.
eng_translation: One young man is in a plan while another is skating.

bem_transcription: Uyu uli mundeke alemoneka nakwata icakukopelako uyu muntu uli panshi uleshelela.
eng_translation: It looks like the one in the plane has a camera for capturing the one slidding below.

bem_transcription: Indke yaka ena ilemoneka iya makumbi makumbi kabili mwapita ne fyabuta.
eng_translation: The plane looks blue with a bit of white.

bem_transcription: Elyo umulumendo ena uli mundeke afwele icakashika ku muulu elyo kunshi afwele itoloshi lya fita.
eng_translation: The young man in the plane is wearing a red shirt and a black trousers.

bem_transcription: Uyu uleshelela cilemoneka natoloka sana alishibisha ici icangalo.
eng_translation: The one sliding looks like he knows this game well because he has jumped high.

bem_transcription: Abana besukulu nabaya mukutamba ifyangalo ifya pusana pusana.
eng_translation: School children have gone to watch various games.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka bali mumabumba aya pusana pusana pantu bambi nafwala fimo fine ifya buta bambi bafwele ifya katapa katapa.
eng_translation: And it looks like they are in different teams because some are wearing green and others are wearing white.
