eng_translation: They are not at the house but at the forest where they went to rest.

bem_transcription: Nga balya abalumendo abali ku ntanshi yabo emukuti bali bonse nagu bali fye beka?
eng_translation: Are they with those young men in front or they are on their own?

bem_transcription: Balumendo balya kuti ba bana ba ba shikulu na bashitata aba abekele.
eng_translation: Those young men could be this old man and these men's children

bem_transcription: Umwana umunono uyu naikupika imbeketi ku mutwe.
eng_translation: A young child has out the head in a bucket.

bem_transcription: NOT FOUND
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Aikupike fye umwana uyu aleunfwa bwino ukucitwika aleangal.
eng_translation: He is enjoying playing with his head in the bucket.

bem_transcription: Nga cilya icilemoneka panshi nge minwe bushe kuti shaba shabakulu ngu mwana umunono naena?
eng_translation: What about those hands there? Could they be for an adult or another child?

bem_transcription: Ishi iminwe kuti shaba minwe shabafyashi ba mwana uyu.
eng_translation: Those hands could be for the childs parents.

bem_transcription: Umwana umwaume umunoono aleelela pamwela natomboka.
eng_translation: A young boy has jumped into the air.

bem_transcription: Ngeyi ntambo ili panshi yabo nayena bushe baleangala nayena?
eng_translation: Are they also playing with that rope down there?

bem_transcription: Iyi tentambo iyo litumbo lipitamo amenshi, abana aba balelyangasha.
eng_translation: That is a horse pipe that they are playing with.

bem_transcription: Bushe pantu bali nipa n'ganda nangu nikuncende imbi?
eng_translation: Are they at their house or just some other place?

bem_transcription: Ni pa n'ganda yabafyashi babo abana aba echo baleangalila mumsango wa so.
eng_translation: They are at they house with their parents that is why they are playing like this.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabana nalikolongana liletungululwa nomukalamba.
eng_translation: A group of children is being led by an adult.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ekuti aba abana nabatemwa ukumona umusungu uyu?
eng_translation: Are these children happy to see a white person?

bem_transcription: Nabatemwa ukumona aletoloka.
eng_translation: The are happy to see a white person jumping.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ili ibumba lyabana lilefuma mumpanga nangu nikumayanda lilefuma?
eng_translation: Is this group if children coming from the forest or they are coming from houses?

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabana ili lyafumine ukwapusana elo bakolongana baamba ukukonka umusungu yu.
eng_translation: They came from various places and gathered to follow this white person.

bem_transcription: Amakii nayengila kukabokosi isula.
eng_translation: Open it the keys are already in the box.

bem_transcription: Bushe akabokoshi kamusango yu kabombe nshi?
eng_translation: What is the use of this kind of box?

bem_transcription: Akabokoshi kaifi kabombamo ukubika amalata ayalefuma ukwapusana ayo babikamo abaleta amakalata.
eng_translation: It is used for putting letters that are coming from various places.

bem_transcription: Bushe akabokoshi kaifi kaba pa n'ganda nangu apali ponse kalasangwa?
eng_translation: Are these boxes only found at houses or they can be found anywhere.

bem_transcription: Akabokoshi aka kalaba muncende ishapusana pusana kulaba utusangwa mumayanda notusangwa panse yamayanda.
eng_translation: They are found in different places. Some are in the houses and others are outside.

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti cabalumendo nacibungana cileteya umupila wakuminwe uo beta ati rugby.
eng_translation: A group of young men is gathered playing rugby.

bem_transcription: Ngoyu umulumendo uukonteme ninshi afwalileko ifyapusana kubanankwe?
eng_translation: Why is this bent young man dressed differently?

bem_transcription: Uyu umulumendo uupuseneko aleteya kwi team limbi ilipusene kuli aba bantu.
eng_translation: Because this young man is of a different team.

bem_transcription: Nga cakuti uyu umupila bateya amabumba yabili ayapusana ngo yu shikulu bantu uufwele ica yellow alecite nshi?
eng_translation: If this game is played by two different teams what is this old man in yellow doing?

bem_transcription: Shitata muntu uulelokesha pamafunde yamupila ukukonka ati aba abaleteya baleyakonka.
eng_translation: He is a referee.

bem_transcription: Umwana umunoono ali mucimpelwa alepeluka.
eng_translation: A young child is swinging in the swing.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ekuti uyu umwana aikwelele fye eka?
eng_translation: Could he have gotten on the swing by himself?

bem_transcription: Iyo umwana uyu teti aikwelele eka, ali nabafyashi bacimubikapo.
eng_translation: No this child can't do that. He is with the parents.

bem_transcription: Ukulolesha nefyo alemoneka bushe namwentula nangu alelila?
eng_translation: Looking at his face, could we say he is smilling or crying?

bem_transcription: Namwentula uyu umwana naumfwa bwino ukulapeluka.
eng_translation: He is smiling. He is enjoying swinging.

bem_transcription: Abantu bali pamaliketi balebomba umulimo wakushitisha bambi baleshita.
eng_translation: People are selling at the market and others are buying.

bem_transcription: Bushe ifi baleshitisha mumabotolo nifinshi?
eng_translation: What are these things they are selling in bottles?

bem_transcription: Ifi ifili mwibotolo ifyo baleshitisha bwalwa nangula molokoso.
eng_translation: That is beer.

bem_transcription: Bushe apa nipa musebo nangu bali mukati yacikuulwa?
eng_translation: Is this on the street or they are inside a building?

bem_transcription: Apa temukati iyo nipamusebo fye bali apo batantike, nga nimucikuulwa nga kuli icintelelwe.
eng_translation: This is not inside but outside. There would have been a shade if it was inside.

bem_transcription: Abana abakashana baleshana.
eng_translation: Young girls are dancing.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici bemininepo nicinshi?
eng_translation: What is this thing they are standing on?

bem_transcription: Bali pa stage balesengelela abantu abaleisa kucikuulwa cine ici.
eng_translation: They are on the stage welcoming people that are coming to this building.

bem_transcription: Bushe icinkupiti ca bantu ici cishana ifyapala ifyaso bacita ati shani?
eng_translation: What do they call this group of people that dance like this?

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti camusango yu bacita mucingeleshi ati cheerleader.
eng_translation: It is called cheerleaders.

bem_transcription: Umwaume ali pakubeya yamwaune munankwe alekopa.
eng_translation: A man is on another man's shoulders taking pictures.

bem_transcription: Nicinshi cingalenga ukulakopela pakubeya kwamubiye?
eng_translation: Why would he be taking pictures from a person's shoulders?

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti cabantu califulisha ifyakwebati umulumendo teti akope bwino ifntu alefwaya ukukopa efyo aninine pakubeya kwamunankwe ukwebati akope bwino.
eng_translation: Because there are a lot of people and he can't get photos clearly that is why he is on his friends shoulders.

bem_transcription: Nga ko kalemoneka akakashika kashika mumukoshi wakwe nikanshi?
eng_translation: What is that reddish thing around his neck?

bem_transcription: Aka kantu, kantu beta ati flag, flag yi yacalo.
eng_translation: That is a national flag.

bem_transcription: Shikulu banru alemwentula nafwala namagogo.
eng_translation: An old man is smilling and wearing goggles.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Ifilelenga bantu baiminine kuntashi yakwe amagogo aya yalebomba kwati ni mirror.
eng_translation: People are standing in front of him because these goggles are serving as a mirror.

bem_transcription: Nifinshi fingalenga ukuti amwentule uyu musango?
eng_translation: Why would he be smiling like this?

bem_transcription: Alemwentwila abalemukopa pakuti nga aisa alelosha icikope inshita imbi aimona ukwebati ali uwasangalala
eng_translation: He is smiling for the cameras so that he looks happy on the pictures.

bem_transcription: Imbwa shibili shilecena.
eng_translation: Two dogs are playing.

bem_transcription: Ngefyo umushili ulemoneka uwabuuta buuta epo shilecenena?
eng_translation: Why is the ground whitish where the dogs are playing from?

bem_transcription: Pamushili uyu pali ifyo beta ati snow ifiloka nga nakutalalisha
eng_translation: Because it was snowing.

bem_transcription: Kucimonwa cobe kuti watila ati iyo iyafiita naisumisha iinankwe pamukoshi iyo iyamabalawila?
eng_translation: From the look of things can you see the black one has bitten hardly the spotted one?

bem_transcription: Naulungika, imbwa iyo iyafiita nailume iinankwe pamukoshi.
eng_translation: You are right. The back one is bitting the spotted one on the neck.

bem_transcription: Banamayo babili bali no mulumendo umunoono balemutamba ilyo aleangasha bola.
eng_translation: Two women are watching a young man as he plays with the ball.

bem_transcription: Bushe kuti caba ukuti uu umwana umulumendo tenda bwino?
eng_translation: Could it be that this young man is crippled?

bem_transcription: Umulumendo uyu alenda fye bwino efyo asalile fye ukwangala alepanga ifyo beta ati amasitailo na bola.
eng_translation: No he walks just fine. He is just doing some foodball styles.

bem_transcription: Bushe uku kuncende bali kuti babako fye beka?
eng_translation: Could they be alone in this place?

bem_transcription: Iyi incende ilemoneka kwati nikunuma yan'ganda yabo kuti caba ifyo fine ati baliko fye beka.
eng_translation: This looks like their backyard so it's possible they could be alone?

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu naikala pamupando aletusha.
eng_translation: An old man is seated on a chair resting.

bem_transcription: Bushe ukumona kucimone cabe kuti wati nipa n'ganda yakwe nangu nimumbali yamusebo?
eng_translation: Could you say this is his house or he is on the roadside?

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu uyu ali fye mumusebo, cipalile kwati aleenda elo anaka ati ekaleko atuushe
eng_translation: This man is on the roadside. It is like he was walking then he got tired and decided to rest.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka alemwentula, mwati kuti aleisekela fye eka?
eng_translation: He is smiling. Could he just be smiling alone?

bem_transcription: Alifye eka lelo alimona ifintu ifyamusekeshe ifyo alemwentwila.
eng_translation: He is just alone but he saw something that made him happy.

bem_transcription: Shitata nanamayo nabekala balelisha inyimbo.
eng_translation: A man and a woman are sitted playing music.

bem_transcription: Ngoto tuntu babikile pakubeya, bushe nitunshi inshina?
eng_translation: What is the name of those things in their shoulders?

bem_transcription: Utu tuntu, tuntu beta ati ama violin mucingeleshi twakulisishako inyimbo.
eng_translation: Those are violins.

bem_transcription: Bushe uku balelisisha inyimbo kuti baba beka nangu kuli abalebatamba?
eng_translation: Could they be alone in this place or there are people watching?

bem_transcription: Aba bantu kuti babako fye beka pantu iyi ni n'ganda.
eng_translation: They could be alone because this looks like a house.

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti ca bantu icikalamba nacikolongana.
eng_translation: A group of people is gathered.

bem_transcription: Ngefyo ifilemoneka ifyapuutwa bushe kuti fyaba nifinshi?
eng_translation: What are those things that look blown?

bem_transcription: Ifi fintu, fintu beta ati ama hot air ballon mucingeleshi, fyakuninamo abantu elo caya mumuulu.
eng_translation: Those are hot hair balloons. You board them then they go up in the sky's.

bem_transcription: Nomba kuti fyasenda shani abantu, kuti baikala mwi?
eng_translation: But how could these carry people? How could they even sit?

bem_transcription: Ici cintu cilakwata akabokoshi kunshi uko abantu bengilamo, lelo abantu bafwile fye baba fye abanoono.
eng_translation: It has a box at the bottom where a few people can go in.

bem_transcription: Shitata naiminina naikata nakumutwe.
eng_translation: A man is standing and putting his hands on his head.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici abikile mumukoshi icileselela kuti caba nicinshi?
eng_translation: What is that thing that is around his neck and moving?

bem_transcription: Ici cintu, cintu beta ati Kamera, cakukopelako ifikope.
eng_translation: That is a camera for taking pictures.

bem_transcription: Cinshi cingalenga ukwikata kumutwe nge fyo alemoneka kwati nalimo nacimupapusha icintu amwene?
eng_translation: What could make him touch his head like that as if he is surprised?

bem_transcription: Iyo, umuntu uyu alinakafye ne ncito alebomba uku ukwimya amaboko emukutila ayololeko.
eng_translation: No this person is just tired and is stretching his hands.

bem_transcription: Shitata naikala alelya.
eng_translation: A man is seated and eating.

bem_transcription: Finshi ifi shikulu bantu uyu alelya?
eng_translation: What is this old man eating?

bem_transcription: Uyu shitata alelya umupunga ne nkoko.
eng_translation: He is eating rice and chicken.

bem_transcription: Nge fyo fili mutubolo tuli mupepi nankwe bushe kuti fyaba nifinshi?
eng_translation: What could be in those bottles near him be?

bem_transcription: Utubotolo utu pali ifyalekanalekana, tumbi tulesunga ifyo beta ati sauce elyo tumbi tusungile dulinki.
eng_translation: There are different things in them. Others have source and others have drink in them.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo babili baleangala, baleteya umupila uwakuminwe.
eng_translation: Two young men are playing hand ball.

bem_transcription: Bushe ubu ubwangalo babuteya shani? Bwakutoloka mumuulu?
eng_translation: How do they play this game? Does it involve jumping high up in the air?

bem_transcription: Ubu bwangalo bwalikwata uuba mucipanda eo basukushila umupila, nga afilwa ukwikata umupila yu ninshi bapenda ati baingisha.
eng_translation: It is just like football only it is played with the hands. There's a goal and a goal keeper and the players try to score.

bem_transcription: Bushe umupila babomfya nga bakulasa teti ukalipe?
eng_translation: Does the ball they use not hurt when they hit you?

bem_transcription: Kuti wakalipa lelo balamona apakuposela elo nabekata balishiba ifyakwikata.
eng_translation: It can hurt. But they know how to throw and the goal keepers too know how to catch.

bem_transcription: Umwana umwaume alepoose libwe mukamana.
eng_translation: A young boy is throwing a Stone into the river.

bem_transcription: Bushe nomba ninshi alepoosela amabwe mukamana?
eng_translation: But why is he throwing stones into the river?

bem_transcription: Aleumfwa bwino iciunda nga aposamo ilibwe.
eng_translation: He likes the sound it's making.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ukuboko kumbi kulemonekela ukwabuuta ukucila ukunankwe?
eng_translation: Why is the other hand whiter than the other?

bem_transcription: Kasuba kamusanike kukuboko kumbi.
eng_translation: It is the sun that had shone on the other hand.

bem_transcription: Abakashana babili nabekala petebulo.
eng_translation: Two young women are sitting on a table.

bem_transcription: Ee nabekala petebulo, nomba cinshi bekalilepo, cinshi balelolesha petebulo?
eng_translation: Yes. But why are they sitting there? What are they looking at?

bem_transcription: Bekele petebulo baleteya injuka.
eng_translation: They are seated on the table playing cards.

bem_transcription: Ukulolesha kuli uyu uufwele icafiita cilemoneka nasakamana, bushe cinshi asakamanine?
eng_translation: The one wearing black looks troubled. What could be the problem?

bem_transcription: Nasakamana kumulandu wakwebati nabamuwina utwingi utupendelo.
eng_translation: It is because she has lost a lot of games.

bem_transcription: Abakashana babili nabekala patupuna mupepi netebulo.
eng_translation: Two young women are seated on chairs near the table.

bem_transcription: Finshi efyo balecita aba abakashana babili abekele pamatebulo?
eng_translation: What are these young women doing?

bem_transcription: Aba abakashana balebumba ifibuumbo ifyamaloba.
eng_translation: They are making dolls from clay.

bem_transcription: Ninshi emukuti ifi ifibumbo balashitisha nga bapwa?
eng_translation: Do they sell these dolls when they make?

bem_transcription: Namulungika, ifi ifibuumbo fyakushitisha.
eng_translation: You are right they sell them.

bem_transcription: Abakashana babili nabekala mupepi namenshi, shibantu ena natalamukilako.
eng_translation: Two young women are sitting near the water but the man is at a distance.

bem_transcription: Abakashana balemoneka baleangala mwiloba, ninshi kwikalila mupepi na menshi, ukwangala mwiloba kulomfwika bwino?
eng_translation: They are playing in the soil. Is sitting near the water and playing in the soil enjoyable?

bem_transcription: Abakashana aba baleumfwa bwino ukwangasha iloba ilibombele nokulatamba ibemba lya menshi uko lileima.
eng_translation: They are enjoying playing with the wet soil and watching the waves.

bem_transcription: Ninshi efyo alecita yu shikulubantu uyu umbi wikele akatalamukila?
eng_translation: What is this man seated at a distance doing?

bem_transcription: Uyu shikulu bantu naililwa nokulanda nobo alelanda nabena pali lamya.
eng_translation: He is carried away in a conversation on the phone.

bem_transcription: Umwana ali nabanyina kumpela nangula kuntendekelo yamenshi.
eng_translation: A child is with the mother at the river.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu umwana nabanyina kuti baya mukucite nshi kukamana?
eng_translation: What could this child and mother be doing at the river?

bem_transcription: Uku bali nikuncende kumpela yakamana ukuba imicanga uko beta ati kubeach abantu balayako mukwangala.
eng_translation: They are at the beach where people go to have a good time.

bem_transcription: Bushe banyina kuti baowa no mwana uyu umunoono?
eng_translation: Can the mother swim with this young child?

bem_transcription: Iyo teti bowe no mwana umunoono yu bayafye ukwikala baletamba amenshi nokulaontela akasuba.
eng_translation: No she can't swim with the child. She just goes to watch the river and sun bathe.

bem_transcription: Umukashana natoloka ibaka.
eng_translation: A young woman has jumped high.

bem_transcription: Ninshi uyu umukashana atolokele fi?
eng_translation: Why has she jumped like this?

bem_transcription: Umukashana uyu aleteya ubwangalo bwakucilikana ukutoloka, eco balamukopela nabaleukopa.
eng_translation: She is in a jumping competition that is why there are even people taking pictures of her.

bem_transcription: Ninshi uyu umukashana afwalile utupimpinya utu?
eng_translation: Why is Young woman wearing these skimpy clothes?

bem_transcription: Utupimpinya utu afwele twakumulenga ati apepuke aletolokesha.
eng_translation: This is so that she's not weighed down by her clothes as she jump.

bem_transcription: Abantu babili nabanina pamuulu ya bwato ubunoono.
eng_translation: Two people are on a small boat.

bem_transcription: Bushe kuli ici balemoneka balefwembela kuti caba nicinshi?
eng_translation: What could this other thing be?

bem_transcription: Ici balefwembelako cibwato icikulu ico beta mucingeleshi ati ship.
eng_translation: That other big thing is a ship.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ekutila icibwato conse ici cine beta ati ship cilakula ngefi fine?
eng_translation: Are all ships that big?

bem_transcription: Ifibwato fi filaba ifikalamba sana icakwebati nefimbayambaya kuti fyaingilapo ifingi.
eng_translation: These ships are mostly very big that they can even carry a number of vehicles.

bem_transcription: Abana batatu abakashana babili nomulumendo umo bali mumpanga.
eng_translation: Two young girls are with a young boy in the forest

bem_transcription: Bushe impanga iyi balimo teti balube?
eng_translation: Cant they get lost in this forest?

bem_transcription: Abana aba tabaile mumpanga iyi beka bali nabakalamba abalebalolekeshapo.
eng_translation: These children are not alone but they are with parents who are looking after them.

bem_transcription: Cinshi cingalenga impanga yi ukulamoneka iyauma-uma?
eng_translation: Why could this place be looking this dry?

bem_transcription: Iyi iyauma-uma pantu imfula yaliya kale yalekolepo so ifimuti kale fyamwenepo amenshi.
eng_translation: It is this dry because it hasn't been raining in a very long time.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo natoloka pacintu beta ati skateboard.
eng_translation: A young man has jumped with a skateboard.

bem_transcription: Bushe iyi ine skateboard yenda shani ilapupuka?
eng_translation: How does this same skateboard move? Does it fly?

bem_transcription: Iyo, iyi skateboard yalikwata amawilo yakulashelelapo nga uleisunka.
eng_translation: No it has wheels so it moves when he pushes it.

bem_transcription: Nomba uyu umulumendo ifi afulile ishati nga apona taicene?
eng_translation: The way this young man is without a shirt can't he hurt himself if he falls?

bem_transcription: Ukuicena kwena kuti aicena uyu umulumendo yu pantu ninkanda fye ukufikila panshi.
eng_translation: He can hurt himself because his skin will directly hit the ground.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo nomukashana nabeminina baleshana.
eng_translation: A young man and young woman are dancing.

bem_transcription: Bushe ukushana uku bakwita shani?
eng_translation: What is this dance called?

bem_transcription: Ukushana kwaleshana umulumendo nomukashana yu kushana beta ati salsa.
eng_translation: This dance is called salsa

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Ukushana baleshana kulaba ukwapusana, kulaba wamusunkila apatali futi wamubwesha wamuleta mupepi.
eng_translation: The dancing is different. Sometimes you push your patner away and then again you pull them.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu nafwala akasote kabili nakwata necefu icikulu.
eng_translation: An old man is wearing a hat and has long beards.

bem_transcription: Nifinshi ekele alecita uyu shikulu bantu?
eng_translation: What is this old man doing?

bem_transcription: Ifyo alecita shikulu bantu uyu teti fishibikwe, lelo kwishiba fye ati naikata akamuti akanoono muminwe.
eng_translation: We can't know for sure. All we know is this old man has a small stick in his hands.

bem_transcription: Aka akamuti ali nakena muminwe, bushe alecite nshi nakena?
eng_translation: What is he doing with that small stick?

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu uyu atemenwe fye ukuketa akantu aka muminwe, alekangasha.
eng_translation: He is just enjoying playing with it in his hands.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabakalisha bamaoma nalikolongana lilelisha.
eng_translation: A group of drummers is gathered.

bem_transcription: Bushe teti cibe cakuti aba nibakopokola?
eng_translation: Could these not be cops?

bem_transcription: Kuti baba olo iyo teti twishibe pantu nabalisha fye nabatebakapokola bafwala ifya ifya ififine.
eng_translation: They can be or not because even just regular drummers dress in the same manner.

bem_transcription: Ninshi cilye cinkupiti ca bantu cishile mukutamba aba bene bantu balelisha?
eng_translation: Is that group of people here to watch these drummers?

bem_transcription: Ifyo cilepala kwati beshile ukutamba aba bene abalelisha nga teifyo aba balelisha amaoma ebaishile kuncende iyi.
eng_translation: That is how it looks like. Or it is these drummers that came to where these people were.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabalumendo nabasenda idalamu.
eng_translation: A group of young men is carrying a drum.

bem_transcription: Bushe ninshi balemonekela abafiitulukila fiitulukila?
eng_translation: Why are they not clear?

bem_transcription: Balemonekela ukufiituka pantu ubu bushiku akasuba kaleya mukuwa.
eng_translation: They look like this because it is evening and the sun is setting.

bem_transcription: Ngo ku baleninika idalumu ili nikwisa?
eng_translation: Where are they putting this drum?

bem_transcription: Balekweleka idalamu pamutenge wacimbayambaya.
eng_translation: They are putting it on the roof if the vehicle.

bem_transcription: Umuntu aleenda kumbali yalupili eka.
eng_translation: A person is walking alone on a mountain side.

bem_transcription: Umu alepita mulemoneka fye nge nshila yapangwa nabantu bushe kuti caba nicho?
eng_translation: This path looks man made, does it?

bem_transcription: Naulungika inshila ishi balapanga pakuti abantu baleninapo nga baumfwa ukunina impili.
eng_translation: Yes these paths are made so that people can pass through when they want to climb mountains.

bem_transcription: Bushe umu mumapili umu kuti kwaba mupepi namayanda?
eng_translation: Could these mountains be near where houses are?

bem_transcription: Iyo amayanda nolupili tafipalamana, lelo amayanda yalatalamulukako.
eng_translation: No. Houses are not built near mountains.

bem_transcription: Bakemba ba nyimbo nabeminina baleimba inyimbo.
eng_translation: Singers are standing and singing.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu uusunsumene, nicinshi ekete ico muminwe?
eng_translation: What is this person who is squatting holding in the hands?

bem_transcription: Uusunsumene ekete cibanjo echo alisha.
eng_translation: He is holding and playing a banjo

bem_transcription: Bushe uyo shikulu ulemupalamina uyo uusunsumene na suti yafiita bushe nao aleimbako nangu alepita fye?
eng_translation: Is this old man in a black suit who is moving closer to the one squatting singing too?

bem_transcription: Teti cishiibikwe naena nga aleimbako olo alepitafye ico twingeshibafye cakwebati naena alikuncende iyi ali nabo abantu aba
eng_translation: We can't know if he is also singing or just passing by. All we know is he is at the same place as those singing.

bem_transcription: Malonda aleenda mumusebo pakati yamayanda.
eng_translation: A guard is moving on the road between the houses.

bem_transcription: Bushe naushinikisha ukuti mayanda nelo fikuulwa fyamakwebo?
eng_translation: Are you sure these are houses or business buildings?

bem_transcription: Iyo aya mayanda pantu nayakwata ifntini fyakupoosamo ifisooso, nayakwata nefidishi ifyo batambilako T.V.
eng_translation: These are houses because they have trash buns as well as TV antennas.

bem_transcription: Bushe ifi ifikuulwa kuti fyaba fyavuteko nangu fyamuntu fye?
eng_translation: Could these buildings be for an individual or they are for the government.

bem_transcription: Teti fishibikwe iyo but ukulolesha pafikuulwa ifi umine ni umo pantu fipentelwe nakala iyapalana.
eng_translation: We can't tell. But the owner is one because they are even of the same colour.

bem_transcription: Umwanakashi naikala alelolesha mucakukopelako.
eng_translation: A woman is seated looking into something used to capture.

bem_transcription: Bushe kuti caba nicinshi cilya alekopa?
eng_translation: What could that thing be?

bem_transcription: Cilya tacilemwenekesha teti twishibe iyo.
eng_translation: It is not clear so we can't know for sure.

bem_transcription: Bushe uku kuncende kuti abapo eka nangu nabantu?
eng_translation: Could she be alone here or with people?

bem_transcription: Uku kuncende kuti abako eka lelo futi kuti kwaba nabambi abantu abashalemoneka.
eng_translation: She could be alone or maybe there are people whom we can't see.

bem_transcription: Umukashana naiminina naloshako icanuma.
eng_translation: A young woman is standing facing her back here.

bem_transcription: Kuboko kwamuntu kulya kuntashi yakwe?
eng_translation: Is that someone's hand in front of her?

bem_transcription: Kuli umuntu uyu wimishe ukuboko uushalemoneka bwino bwino mucikope.
eng_translation: There's a person who is raising the hand though he is not very visible.

bem_transcription: Nincende nshi iyi baliko?
eng_translation: Where is this place?

bem_transcription: Aba bantu bali mucikuulwa cakushitishamo ubwalwa, nga mwalolesha petebulo pali ibotolo lyabwalwa.
eng_translation: These people are in a bar because there is even a bottle of beer on the table if you look closely.

bem_transcription: Umulondo we sabi alelobe sabi mucungulo bushiku.
eng_translation: A fisherman is fishing in the evening.

bem_transcription: Ninshi alemonekela umuntu uwafiitulukila uyu?
eng_translation: Why is this person not clear?

bem_transcription: Inshita bakopele icikope ici kwali ukwafiita so umulondo uyu teti amonekele bwino bwino.
eng_translation: It is because the picture was taken when it was dark.

bem_transcription: Akasuba kalewa nangu olo kaletula?
eng_translation: Is that sunrise or sunset?

bem_transcription: Akasuba aka kalewa, pantu ukuwa kwakasuba elo kumoneka ifi ukwakashika kashika.
eng_translation: It is sunsets because because the sun looks red at sunsets.

bem_transcription: Umwana naikala muli plemu.
eng_translation: A child is sitting the plem

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu umwana alelila nangula iyo?
eng_translation: Is that child crying or not?

bem_transcription: Umwana uyu talelila iyo lelo tali no wansansa.
eng_translation: The child is not crying but is happy.

bem_transcription: Bushe apa ali cileenda balemusunka kuli ulya kunuma nangu naciminina?
eng_translation: Is the one behind pushing the plem or is it stationery?

bem_transcription: Teti twishibe bwino bwino nga caleenda nangu iyo but ukulolesha umuntu walikunuma kuti twalanda ukweba ati balemusunka yaleenda.
eng_translation: We cant know for sure. But looking at that person behind he can say the plem is being pushed and is moving.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alecofe ncinga pamusebo.
eng_translation: A young man is riding a bicycle on the road.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici cikuulwa alepitapo apa cikuulwa cakushitisha ifyakulya nangula iyo?
eng_translation: Is that a food place that he is passing through or not ?

bem_transcription: Ici icikuulwa bashitishamo ifyalekanalekana, but ifintu ifyafulamo fyakulya.
eng_translation: They sell many different things in that building. But most if it is food.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Bushe iyi incinga ninshi amataila yaleba ayapusana?
eng_translation: Why are this bicycles tyres different.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu nalikolongana liletamba abaleshana.
eng_translation: A group of people is gathered watching dancers.

bem_transcription: Bushe aba bene baleshana ninshi balemonekela ababuuta pamenso?
eng_translation: Why are these dancers white on their faces.

bem_transcription: Aba abaleshana nabaipenta balefwaya ukumoneka kwati ciwa.
eng_translation: They have painted themselves to look like ghosts.

bem_transcription: Balemoneka abakote bushe nindungika?
eng_translation: They look old. Am I right?

bem_transcription: Eya mukwai aba bacikulile.
eng_translation: Yes they are elderly.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabalumendo baleteya bola yakuminwe iyo beta basketball.
eng_translation: A group of young men is playing basketball.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu wine umupila babamo banga mukati?
eng_translation: How many are they in a pitch when playing basketball?

bem_transcription: Uyu umupila yu babamo ikumi, balakana pakati baba fisano kumo nokukumbi fisano.
eng_translation: They are ten on the pitch, five on each side.

bem_transcription: Bushe yu umupila nga wapantila kumakasa ninshi ekutila walusa nangula iyo?
eng_translation: What happens when you kick the ball with your feet?

bem_transcription: Amafunde yalakanya, kwaba kalolekesha wamafunde uupanika abapanta kumoolu.
eng_translation: That is against the rules. The referee would punish you for that.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo aleteya tennis.
eng_translation: A young man is playing tennis.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo wine afwele ifyakufwala fyonse ifyabuuta bushe efyo bafwala?
eng_translation: This man is wearing all white. Is that how they dress?

bem_transcription: Awe nakalya efyo asalile fye umwine.
eng_translation: No that is just what he wants.

bem_transcription: Nga cilya icilemoneka icafiita panshi yakwe?
eng_translation: What is that black thing down there?

bem_transcription: Cilya icilemoneka icafiita cinshingwa cakwe.
eng_translation: That looks like his shadow.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici cinkupiti cilesefya nangu cileshinshimuna?
eng_translation: Is that group celebrating or it is worshiping?

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu umulumendo uli pantashi apa euletungulula ibumba?
eng_translation: Is that young man in front the leader of the group?

bem_transcription: Ngo yu umunoono aleangala alenina kwiuulu.
eng_translation: What about this young child climbing the top?

bem_transcription: Bushe nga atelela uyu umwana teti apone?
eng_translation: Can't he fall?

bem_transcription: Kuti awa nga tatencenjele.
eng_translation: He can if he's nit careful.

bem_transcription: Bushe kuti caba ukuti uyu umwana ele fye eka uku kufyulu?
eng_translation: Could this child have gone alone to these hills?

bem_transcription: Kuti caba ati nafyuka umwana aya kuchuulu eka olo ali nabafyashi mupepi abalemulolekeshapo.
eng_translation: It could be that the child escaped and went to these hills or he's with the parents.

bem_transcription: Shitata naikala eka alebelenga.
eng_translation: A man is sitting alone reading.

bem_transcription: Bushe pantashi pakwe apa ekele kuti paba amenshi?
eng_translation: Could there be water in front of where he is sitting?

bem_transcription: Awe amenshi tapali lelo umu ifyani fikulile mufwile ukuba amenshi but tamuli.
eng_translation: There's no water. Though there is supposed to be water there where the grass had grown.

bem_transcription: Bushe pancende apa ekele kuti paba ni pan'ganda yakwe nangu ekele fye mumusebo?
eng_translation: Could this place be his house or is just sitting on the streets?

bem_transcription: Apa pancende ni pa n'ganda yakwe nga namulolekesha kuli nolupango.
eng_translation: This is his house. There is even a fence if you look closely.

bem_transcription: Bakabomba batatu nabeminina nabafwala nefimpompo kumutwe.
eng_translation: Three workers are standing wearing helmets.

bem_transcription: Bushe ifi ifimpompo bafwele fibombe nshi?
eng_translation: What is the use of these helmets they are wearing?

bem_transcription: Ifimpompo ifi fyakubacingililako ku fili fyonse fingacitika pancito nangula balebomba elo amabwe yabaponena mumutwe teti baicene.
eng_translation: These are to protect them from any falling objects.

bem_transcription: Bushe aba bene abalumendo ebensha icimbayambaya cili pantashi yabo?
eng_translation: Are these young men the ones who drive that vehicle parked there?

bem_transcription: Kuti cabe fyo fine pali aba bene abalumendo pali umo uwensha, nangula uwensha naena naibela.
eng_translation: It is possible the driver is among these three or not.

bem_transcription: Umwaume naiminina mucikuulwa icayemba alelolesha pawiindo.
eng_translation: A man is standing in a beautiful building looking at the window.

bem_transcription: Bushe ukupula pamagalashi yali kuntashi yakwe kulya, bushe kamana kali kuntashi?
eng_translation: If we look passed those glasses is that a river there?

bem_transcription: Kamana kalya akalemoneka nako tekamana akanoono awe, kamana akakalamba sana eko beta ati ocean.
eng_translation: That is an ocean.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici cikuulwa cakwa shikulubantu wine yu?
eng_translation: Is this man the owner of the building?

bem_transcription: Umwine wacikuulwa teti eshibikwe kuli ifwe lelo kuti caba ati emwine nolo uyu umulumendo aliishibana no mwine.
eng_translation: We can't know. It could be that he is the owner or he just knows the owner.

bem_transcription: Nakulu bantu ali ne mbwa naikakila nakuntambo.
eng_translation: An old woman has a dog on a leash.

bem_transcription: Bushe iyi imbwa nga yakakulukwa kuti yabutuka?
eng_translation: Can the dog run if it managed to get out of the leash?

bem_transcription: Awe nakalya, imbwa ishi shilaba namano icakwebati shalishiba umwine, nangu ingabutuka kwangala fye apatali futi yabwela.
eng_translation: No these dogs are intelligent enough to know their owners. Even if it ran it would just play for a while and come back.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici cimbi akobekele mumukoshi eco ekete kukuboko kwakukuso nicinshi?
eng_translation: What is this thing around her neck that she is  holding in her left hand?

bem_transcription: Ici ekete nakulu bantu cikopelo icakukopelako ifikope.
eng_translation: That is a camera.

bem_transcription: Kapokola ali pali honda aleensha kumbali yakwe kuli namotoka.
eng_translation: A cop is riding a motorcycle and there is a vehicle on his side.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Ifi fidoli nga mwalolekesha mwalasanga ukwebati tafiminine na bwino bwino ififwile ukwiminina umuntu.
eng_translation: These mannequins are not even standing the way a person is supposed to stand.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici icimbayambaya cili mupepi nakapokola kuntu abebele muli namutekenya nangula iyo?
eng_translation: Does that vehicle near the police officer have a driver in it or not?

bem_transcription: Ici icimbambaya tacikwete namutekenya uulecensha so tacileenda efyo ciminine kumbali yakumusebo.
eng_translation: That vehicle doesn't have a driver that is why it is parked there.

bem_transcription: Bashimaini bali pamugodi balebomba.
eng_translation: Miners are working underground.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu mugodi nangula balewamya balebika amabwe umupita ishitima?
eng_translation: Is that underground or they are repairing and putting stones where the train passes?

bem_transcription: Kuti waba mugodi pantu nakufiita kumuulu nangula kuyi waba umukoshi mulya umupite shitima.
eng_translation: It could be underground because it is dark above or it could be the neck where trains pass

bem_transcription: Bushe ici icilesansa amabwe cileisansila fye nangu kuli umuntu uulecisanshisha?
eng_translation: Is there someone making this machine spread stones or it is just in its own?

bem_transcription: Ici teti cisanse amabwe palwaciko lelo nacikwata namutekenya uulecikontolola.
eng_translation: It can't spread stones in its own. It has a driver operating it.

bem_transcription: Umwana umunoono naikala pali shofolo.
eng_translation: A young child is sitting on a shovel.

bem_transcription: Bushe iyi shofolo ekelepo teti imucene nakalya iyo?
eng_translation: Can't this shovel hurt him?

bem_transcription: Nakalya ali abafyashi bakwe abalelolekesha pali ena balelolekesha ukwebati teti imucene.
eng_translation: No the child is with the parents that are looking after him.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka uwamwentula bushe cinshi cingalenga?
eng_translation: Why could he be smiling?

bem_transcription: Naumfwa bwino naikala pali shofolo balemwimya nabafyashi bakwe, ulemona kwati bwangalo baleteya?
eng_translation: He is happy he is sitting in the shovel and the parents are lifting him. He thinks they are playing a game.

bem_transcription: Namayo naikala pacipuna aletinika kompyuta.
eng_translation: A woman is seated on a chair pressing the computer.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka naposako amano, bushe kuti fyaba nifinshi efyo engalacitapo?
eng_translation: She is concentrating. What could she be doing?

bem_transcription: Namayo yu cilepala kwati alebomba pali iyi ine kompyuta yi efyo alemonekela naposako sana amano.
eng_translation: It looks like she is working using this computer that is why she looks focussed.

bem_transcription: Nicinshi cilya ekete kukuboko kwakukulyo eco alesesha?
eng_translation: What is that thing in her right hand that she is moving?

bem_transcription: Nacilya icintu ekete muminwe namayo yu cintu beta ati mouse, cibomba ukulakontolweko kompyuta.
eng_translation: That is a mouse. She is using it to operate the computer.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu naikala pamupando.
eng_translation: An old man is sitting on a chair.

bem_transcription: ngo yo umbi shikulu bantu uulemwikata kunsapato bushe finshi alecita?
eng_translation: What about this other old man man touching his shoes? What is he doing?

bem_transcription: Uyo umbi alemuwamye insapato.
eng_translation: The other one is cleaning his shoes.

bem_transcription: So iyi intemba iyi nintemba yakuwamishapo insapato?
eng_translation: So this is a shop for cleaning shoes?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Namulungika, pakuwamishe nsapato
eng_translation: Yes you are right. It is for cleaning shoes.

bem_transcription: Umushilika naiminina naikata ne mfuti muminwe.
eng_translation: A soldier is standing and holding a gun in his hands.

bem_transcription: Ngefyo filemoneka ifiletata kucituuli cakwe ici?
eng_translation: What are those things moving on his gun?

bem_transcription: Ifi nibalunshi bakolongane kumfuti yakwe.
eng_translation: Those are flys on his gun.

bem_transcription: Nicinshi balunshi aba baletatila kumfuti yakwe?
eng_translation: Why are the does his gun have flys?

bem_transcription: Umu ali umushilika uyu nimumpanga, kuti caba ati bacipaye nama elo umulopa waya kumfuti eyo balunshi balekonka.
eng_translation: This soldier is in the forest. Maybe they killed an animal and some blood pilled on his gun and that is why it has flys.

bem_transcription: Bashitata batatu nabekala elyo shitata umo naiminina balelola mucobeta ati binoculars
eng_translation: Three men are seated while one is standing and they are looking into a binoculars.

bem_transcription: Bushe iyi binoculars ibombe nshi?
eng_translation: What is the function of the binoculars?

bem_transcription: Iyi binoculars ibomba ukulolesha ukumone fintu ifili apatali ifyo amenso yeka yeka teti yamone.
eng_translation: It is used to view objects that are very far away that we cannot see with our naked eyes.

bem_transcription: Bushe ukumona kufyo balemoneka bushe aba kuti baba bashilika nangu bantu fye bambi bambi ababombe ncito shimbi?
eng_translation: Looking at these people could they be soldiers or just ordinary people with ordinary jobs.

bem_transcription: Iyo aba tebashilika, aba nibalya bantu abatemwa ukutamba ifintu ifyapangwa na Lesa.
eng_translation: No these are not soldiers. They just love watching creation.

bem_transcription: Banamayo abfwele ifyakashika nabeminina.
eng_translation: Women wearing red are standing.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Banamayo aba baleimba, kabili nga namulolesha baletota ne minwe.
eng_translation: These women are singing and clapping their hands.

bem_transcription: Bushe umu baleimbila kuti mwaba nipanse nangu nimukati yacikuulwa?
eng_translation: Could this place they are singing from be inside or outside?

bem_transcription: Banamayo aba bali panse, nga mwalolekesha nakasuba nakabasanika.
eng_translation: This is outside as the sun has even shone on them.

bem_transcription: Abana nabanina pafimpelwa balepeluka.
eng_translation: Children are swinging on a swing.

bem_transcription: Bushe ifi ifimpelwa fyapangwa shani teti bapunkane nakalya iyo?
eng_translation: How are these swings made? Cant they collide?

bem_transcription: Awe teti bapunkane, ifi ifimpelwa filola kumo tafibwelela kunuma iyo.
eng_translation: No they can't collide. These swings just move in one direction. They don't go back.

bem_transcription: Bushe aba abana bali kusukulu nangula nakalya iyo?
eng_translation: Are these children in school or not.

bem_transcription: Awe aba abana tekusukulu bali fye balifye kuncende yakwangalilako nga namumona nga baciba kusukulu nga bacifwala ifyapalana.
eng_translation: No they are not in school but just playing at some place. Had they been in school, they would have been in uniforms.

bem_transcription: Shitata ali nabana abanoono alelenga pamaloba
eng_translation: A man is with young children drawing on the soil.

bem_transcription: Bushe finshi engalemba panshi apa?
eng_translation: What can he write there?

bem_transcription: Ifilelemba shitata uyu teti fishibikwe kuti limbi aleangala fye nabana olo pali ifyo alebalanga.
eng_translation: We can't tell what he is writing. Maybe he is just playing with the children or he is actually writing something.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu shikulubantu kuti aba niwishi waututwine twana?
eng_translation: Could this man be the father of these children?

bem_transcription: Kuti caba ifyo fine ati ewishi wabana olo pali fye ifyo alebafunda abana aba.
eng_translation: He could be the father of these children or maybe he is just teaching them something.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu nalikolongana bambi nabekala bambi nabeminina.
eng_translation: A group of people is gathered. Some are standing and others are sitting.

bem_transcription: Bushe ili ibumba lilecite nshi umu mumuputule?
eng_translation: What are these people doing in this room?

bem_transcription: Ili ibumba lili muncende yakubombelamo, balebomba pamakompyuta aya bali nayo.
eng_translation: These people are in a work place. They are working on their computers.

bem_transcription: Nga balya abeminshe amaboko, bushe cilelola mwisa?
eng_translation: What about those raiding their hands what does it mean?

bem_transcription: Ukwimya ukuboko balefwaya uwali kuntashi abamone ukwebati pali ifyo balefwaya ukulanda.
eng_translation: They want the one in front to see that they want to say something.

bem_transcription: Umukashana mwideleshi ilyafiita natoloka.
eng_translation: A young woman in a black dress has jumped.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu umukashana umu aletoloka mufyani teti aicene ukwabula insapato kumakasa?
eng_translation: This young woman is jumping barefoot in the grass. Can she bit hurt herself?

bem_transcription: Kuti aicena bwino bwino fye lelo limbi nincende eyo ekalapo eyo aishiba bwino bwino.
eng_translation: She can hurt herself but maybe this is where she stays and she knows the place well.

bem_transcription: Bushe cinshi cingalenga uwisafye mukutolokela mucani nokwabule nsapato?
eng_translation: What could make someone to come jumping in the grass barefooted?

bem_transcription: Naumfwa bwino umukashana uyu limbi acipokelela ilyashi ilisuma sana ilimusansamwishe.
eng_translation: This young woman is happy. Maybe she recieved some very good news.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo aleangala ubwangalo ubo beta ati cricket.
eng_translation: A young man is playing cricket.

bem_transcription: Nomba ninshi bafwalile ifi ifisote ifyapusana umo cilemoneka icakosa umo cilemoneka fye icanaka?
eng_translation: Why are they wearing different hats? One looks hard and the other one looks soft.

bem_transcription: Nafipusana pantu uyu uufwele icakosa balamupoosela kabola elo uyu uufwele akanaka euposa  pantu so uyu afwele icakosa pantu kuti kamulasa kumutwe.
eng_translation: They are different because the one in a soft hat is the one throwing the ball where is the one in a hard hat is the one whom the ball is thrown at. That is why it is hard because the ball can hit him.

bem_transcription: Nomba ifi uulele panshi alefulukuta mwiloba ninshi ekutila emwingila kabola mwiloba?
eng_translation: This one below turning in the soil does it mean it is where the ball has gone?

bem_transcription: Iyo, kabola nga baposa umbi aleya aleshunguluka, nomba pakwebati uwakulya kumbi ku team aleshe umunankwe ukushunguluka afwile aisa iminina apa.
eng_translation: No. When one throws the ball, another starts running so for the person on the other team to stop him, he has to stand there.

bem_transcription: Abana balebutauka kuncende iya maluba maluba.
eng_translation: Children are running in a flowerly place.

bem_transcription: Bushe iyi incende balebutukamo abana teti mwaba ifyakuicena?
eng_translation: Can there be things that can hurt them in this place?

bem_transcription: Ukuicena kuti baicena lelo nabafwala insapato ishakulenga ati teti baicene.
eng_translation: They can hurt themselves. But they are wearing shoes that are protecting them.

bem_transcription: Bushe aba bana ninshi ebeshile baleensha ifimbayambaya filya filemoneka kulya kunuma?
eng_translation: Could these children be the ones that came with those vehicles behind there?

bem_transcription: Iyo, abana aba beshile nabafyashi babo ebacilaensha ifimbayambaya ifi kabili abana nabacepesha teti benshe ifimbaya mbaya.
eng_translation: No they are too young to drive. Their parents are the ones whek were driving.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo umunoono alecofe ncinga pakati yafikuulwa.
eng_translation: A young boy is riding a bicycle in between buildings.

bem_transcription: Ninshi uyu wine umulumendo eufumine mukulenga uyo munwe uli pacibumba?
eng_translation: Is this young man the one who was drawing that hand on the wall?

bem_transcription: Iyo, umunwe yu kale walembwa, umwana yu teti afike napamuulu apo wambile umunwe yu.
eng_translation: No this hand has been there for a long time. Infact this young man can't even reach where this hand is starting from.

bem_transcription: Umusebo aleenseshamo incinga yakwe mwati kuti bapitila napamo na motoka ilya iileisa kuntashi.
eng_translation: Is it possible for him to ride his bicycle as the vehicle is coming in this same road?

bem_transcription: Kuti bapita lelo motoka ifwile yamutalukako pakweba ati imupunka.
eng_translation: It is possible but the vehicle has to leave him some space.

bem_transcription: Bawishi no mwana baleowa mukamana.
eng_translation: A man and his son are swimming in a river.

bem_transcription: Abantu bene balemoneka abansansa bushe cinshi bengatemenwa so?
eng_translation: These people look happy what could be the reason?

bem_transcription: Bali aba nsansa pamulandu wakuti amenshi nayawama.
eng_translation: They are happy because they are enjoying the water.

bem_transcription: Ngo mwana ici afwele mumukoshi bushe canshi?
eng_translation: What is this thing that the child is wearing around the neck?

bem_transcription: Ico umwana afwele mumukoshi cakukana nwina.
eng_translation: It is a floater to prevent him from drowning.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alipancinga naikata na shofolo alelanda nabamayo abekete icibaala.
eng_translation: A young man is on a bicycle holding a shovel and speaking to a woman who is holding a wheel barrow.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu umulumendo alecofa naikata nokuboko kumo bushe teti apone awililile nabanakulu aba bene?
eng_translation: The young man is riding with one hand. Can't he fall on this very woman?

bem_transcription: Iyo, nga walishiba sana ukucofe ncinga kuti wacofa nangu tawiketeko, so umulumendo yu aliishibisha.
eng_translation: No. When you know how to ride very much you can even ride without holding the hand bar. So he can't fall on the woman

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Uku bali kuncende nipetuuka, temupepi namayanda iyo.
eng_translation: This place they are at is a shop and is not near houses.

bem_transcription: Bakateya babili abateya umupila uo beta ati basket ball nabatoloka mumuulu.
eng_translation: Two basketball players have jumped high into air.

bem_transcription: Nomba ekuti ubu ubwangalo bwakutoloka fye mumuulu?
eng_translation: Does this mean this game is all about jumping?

bem_transcription: Iyo, tekutoloka fye iyo, batoloka fye nga baleposa bola mucipanda iciba pamuulu.
eng_translation: No it's not just about jumping. They only jump when they are throwing the ball into the basket.

bem_transcription: So ukulingana nokumona pali aba abalumendo babili, ninani uwaleposa bola?
eng_translation: So who of the two young men is throwing the ball?

bem_transcription: Uwaleposa bola ni yu uufwele ifyabuuta, uyu umbi alelwisha ukulesha umunankwe ukuposa.
eng_translation: I think it is the one in white. The other one is trying to prevent him from throwing.

bem_transcription: Bashitata batatu nabekala mwishitima.
eng_translation: Three men are sitting in a train.

bem_transcription: Nga waishiba shani ukuti lishitima bekelemo?
eng_translation: How do you know that this is a train that they are sitting in?

bem_transcription: Iwiindo lili kunuma yabo lilenga ukuti nimwishitima na akashimbi kalemoneka pe wiindo apa.
eng_translation: The window behind them and that metal bar on the window indicates that it is a train.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ekuti aba balumendo bali pamo?
eng_translation: Does it mean these men are together?

bem_transcription: Ifyo teti fishibikwe iyo, pantu abantu mwishitima lyaifi bekala mupepi, balapalamana so teti wishibe nga bali pamo.
eng_translation: We can't know because in such a train people usually sit close to one another wether they are together or not.

bem_transcription: Bakabomba babili nabeminina panshi ya mugodi.
eng_translation: Two workers are standing underground a mine.

bem_transcription: Ngefyo ifisote fili kumutwe fyanshi?
eng_translation: What are those hats for?

bem_transcription: Ifi fimpompo fyakufwala kumutwe ifyo bashimaina bafwala fyakubacingilila ukucenekwa kumutwe.
eng_translation: Those are helmets that protect their heads.

bem_transcription: Ukumona ngefyo ulya umo alelangilila umunankwe ninshi ekutila ebwana wakwe?
eng_translation: Looking at how that one is giving directions to the other person, does it mean he is the boss?

bem_transcription: Endita mukwai uyu alelangisha ba boss bakwe ifya kubomba ifyo alebomba.
eng_translation: Yes this one is showing the boss how he is working.

bem_transcription: Bashitata babili nabeminina pe wiindo baleisha elo umo namayo nalala.
eng_translation: Two women are standing by the window chatting while one woman is sleeping.

bem_transcription: Bushe ekuti bonse aba batatu abantu bali pamo?
eng_translation: Could these three people be together?

bem_transcription: Iyo umo shitata uyu uufwele akasote aishile fye mukutandala.
eng_translation: No. This other man with a hat just came to visit

bem_transcription: Bushe pewiindo beminine palya kuti paba patali?
eng_translation: Could where they are standing be very high from the ground?

bem_transcription: Apa pabelele ing'anda yabo pamuulu so patali ukufuma pamushili.
eng_translation: Yes because their house is high up from the ground.

bem_transcription: Bakabomba batatu ebo beta ati ama fire fighters baletrainer.
eng_translation: Three fire fighters are training.

bem_transcription: Nomba cinshi bafwalile ifimpompo ifi kumutwe?
eng_translation: Why are they wearing these helmets on their heads?

bem_transcription: Ifi ifimpompo bafwele fyakubacingilila amenso yabo amagalashi nga yaletomboka.
eng_translation: They are to protect their eyes from the splashing glasses.

bem_transcription: Ngechi cintu bakwete kuminwe yabo bushe nicinshi, cibombe nshi?
eng_translation: What is this thing that they have in their hands and what is its function?

bem_transcription: Ici nimashini cakulepwilako amalata ico babomfya nga balefwaya ukuputula motoka iifonfokene.
eng_translation: It is a machine they use to cut metal plates if there is a vehicle that is damaged.

bem_transcription: Imbwa shibili iyafiita imo naimbi iyakashika shili mumenshi.
eng_translation: Two dogs, a black one and a light one are in the water.

bem_transcription: Amenshi aya shileangalilamo teti shisendwe nakalya iyo?
eng_translation: Cant they be taken by this water ?

bem_transcription: Amenshi aya apo imbwa shileangalila tapali apalepa sana so teti shisendwe.
eng_translation: No where the dogs are playing from is not very deep and so they cannot be taken.

bem_transcription: Imishipi shili mumikoshi shambwa shibombe nshi?
eng_translation: What is the function of those belts in the dogs necks?

bem_transcription: Ishi imishipi esho babikako amashina yambwa abene bambwa, elo esho bakakilako intambo yakwenseshako imbwa ukuilanga ukwakuya.
eng_translation: That is where dog owners write the names of the dogs and that is where they connect the dog leashes when taking them for a walk.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo umunoono aletunkula mucimuti.
eng_translation: A Young man is pressing the tree.

bem_transcription: Bushe cinshi cingalenga ukutunkula mucimuti?
eng_translation: Why is he pressing the tree?

bem_transcription: Umulumendo uyu natumupapusha utu utufimbile kucimuti so aletuntukula ukutumfwa ifyo tuleumfwika.
eng_translation: Because the bubbles that have formed on the tree have surprised him and so he wants to feel them.

bem_transcription: Nga cilya cilemoneka muminwe akwete bushe kuti caba nicinshi?
eng_translation: What is that thing that he has in his hands.

bem_transcription: Tacishibikwe iyo, cilepala kwati nici toy ca mwana uyu.
eng_translation: We can't tell but it looks like a child's toy.

bem_transcription: Shitata alelenga ifyo beta ati tatoo pakuboko kwamubiye.
eng_translation: A man is putting a tattoo on another man's arm.

bem_transcription: Kwaliba nokulemba pamubili pankanda yamunobe?
eng_translation: Is there such a thing as writing on your friends skin?

bem_transcription: Eya mukwai kulaba ukuilemba ifyo ulefwaya ukulemba pankanda yobe.
eng_translation: Yes you can write why ever you want on your skin.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ekuti nga wasamba na sopo filafuma ifi fintu?
eng_translation: Do they rub off when you bathe with soap?

bem_transcription: Awe tafifuma, ifi fintu balatunkula mukati fiba panshi yankanda elo filemoneka fye kwati fili pamuulu.
eng_translation: No it doesn't rub of because it is inside the skin.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo netoloshi lyamutuntula napilabuka mumuulu.
eng_translation: A young man in a yellow trousers is spinning in the air.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
Naulungika ici icinkupiti cabantu cishile mukutamba uyu wine uulepilabuka pantu filemoneka bwino nga balepilabuka, abaishiba.
eng_translation: Yes you are right this group is here to see this young man spinning in the air because it is fun to watch.

bem_transcription: Abantu balemoneka abamwentula ninshi uku ukupilabuka kuntu kwayemba sana?
eng_translation: People are smiling. Is this spinning that beautiful?

bem_transcription: Kulaba ukwayemba ukupilibuka uku abene abaishiba ukupilibuka nga balepilibuka so abantu balomfwa bwino.
eng_translation: Yes when professionals are spinning it's very beautiful and enjoyable to watch that is why people are smiling.

bem_transcription: Banamayo babili nabafwala ututambala twapakanwa.
eng_translation: Two women are wearing face masks.

bem_transcription: Balemoneka bali ne ncito iikankala sana bushe nifinshi balepanga?
eng_translation: The look like they are doing something important. What are they making?

bem_transcription: Balepanga ifyakulya ifiitwa ati biscuit.
eng_translation: They are making buscuits.

bem_transcription: Uyu umukashana afwele icakashika bushe aleshana?
eng_translation: Is this young woman in red dancing?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya alesenda biscuit iipwilishiwe ukupangika.
eng_translation: No she is carrying the baked biscuits.

bem_transcription: Akabwa akanoono kaleenda pacikopa.
eng_translation: A small dog is walking on a plank.

bem_transcription: Ninshi aka akabwa kalelwisha ukuculuka ilinga?
eng_translation: Is it trying to jump the fence?

bem_transcription: Iyo ukubelele ilinga nakulepa, akabwa aka kaleendafye pacikopa apa pene.
eng_translation: No it is just walking on the plank, the fence is far from where it is.

bem_transcription: Bushe apa kaletantala tepakwagala abantu iyo?
eng_translation: Is where it is walking nit supposed to be where people play from?

bem_transcription: Apa kaletantala kantu pangalila imbwa, imbwa shilaninapo nokwendapo elo shaikila.
eng_translation: No it is a playing place for dogs. The walk on it and get off.

bem_transcription: Abakashana abali four bali mumenshi baleangala.
eng_translation: Four young women are playing in the water.

bem_transcription: Bushe cinshi cingalenga ukuti bafwale ifyakufwala fimo fine?
eng_translation: Why would they be wearing the same clothes?

bem_transcription: Iyo, ifyakufwala bafwele tafilemoneka, teti twishibe nga bafwele ifyapalana, lelo bafwele fye utwakumitwe utupalene.
eng_translation: No we can't say they are wearing the same clothes because we can't see their clothes. They are only wearing the same hair nets.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ifi baleimya amaboko mumuulu ninshi ekuti baleya mukunwina nangu kuli fimbi ifyo balecitile fi?
eng_translation: Does the raising of hands mean they are drowning or it's signaling something else?

bem_transcription: Abakashana aba baleshana, amasha yabo efyo yaleeba ati kwimya amaboko.
eng_translation: They are dancing. That's how they dance with their hands in the air.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Ninshi uyu umutundu balemonekelamo ninshi efyo bonse bopana ifi fine?
eng_translation: Is the way these two are getting married how everyone does it?

bem_transcription: Ninshi utu utukashana imishanine ishi tuleshana yakulwisha ukuikontola?
eng_translation: The way these girls are dancing are they trying to break themselves.

bem_transcription: Nomba ninshi ubu bwangalo baleshana bwakucilikana ifi bafwele fimo fine?
eng_translation: Are they in a competition since they are wearing the same thing?

bem_transcription: Bushe cinshi cilengele aba abankashana babili ukufwala amagoogo mumutwe?
eng_translation: Why do these young women have goggles in their head?

bem_transcription: Uyu umukashana ulemoneka pamenso bushe cinshi aledonsa mumukoshi?
eng_translation: This girl we are seeing here, what is she pulling in her neck?

bem_transcription: Bushe finshi alebafunda?
eng_translation: What is she teaching them?

bem_transcription: Nga balya bambi abeminine nabo kunuma bushe nibakafundisha?
eng_translation: What about those standing behind there, are they also teachers?

bem_transcription: Ninshi ekuti aba abalumendo bekala mumabwe?
eng_translation: Does it mean these young men live in caves?

bem_transcription: Efyo bafwele filemoneka nakutalala bushe nindungika?
eng_translation: By their dressing we can tell that it's cold. Are they poachers?

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu shikulubantu nga apona teti aicene?
eng_translation: Won't that old man hurt himself when he falls down?

bem_transcription: Bushe ukukwela uku alekwela bwangalo cause kulemoneka naumbi kuntashi kulya?
eng_translation: Is this climbing that he is doing a game? Because I can see another one in front there.

bem_transcription: Bushe ninshi ekuti uyu umwaume ekala mumpanga?
eng_translation: Does it mean that this man lives in the forest?

bem_transcription: Ninshi ifyakulya fine alongele mu bag?
eng_translation: Has he put the food in the bag?

bem_transcription: Bushe iyi ntambo nga yaputuka cinshi cingacitika kumulumendo uyu?
eng_translation: What would happen to this young man if this line cut?

bem_transcription: Bushe intambo iyi akwikileko ninshi ekuti kuli abaikete kuntashi kumuulu?
eng_translation: Does it mean there is someone up holding this rope?

bem_transcription: Umwana umwaume nalala pamusebo.
eng_translation: A young boy is sleeping on the road.

bem_transcription: Nomba cilemoneka kwati acipona pancinga bushe kuti caba efyo?
eng_translation: It looks like he fell from a bicyclenot so?

bem_transcription: Ee, kwena cipalile kwati napenuka pa ncinga.
eng_translation: Yes it is like he fell from the bicycle.

bem_transcription: But ukumoneka talemoneka kwati naicena sana bushe aletusha fye?
eng_translation: But he doesnt like like he has hurt himself too much. Could he just be resting?

bem_transcription: Ee, endita e, cimoneke kwati aletushafye.
eng_translation: Yes. It looks like he is just resting.

bem_transcription: Bushe cinshi cingalenga ukulailolesha?
eng_translation: Why could someone be looking oneself?

bem_transcription: Bushe apa ali ni pa n'ganda nangu nipa cikuulwa pakushite fyakufwala?
eng_translation: Is this place a house or a store where they sale clothes?

bem_transcription: Shitata alebutuka naikata ne mbwa.
eng_translation: A man is running and holding a dog.

bem_transcription: Nga aba bantu bali pantashi yakwe balecite nshi?
eng_translation: What are these people in front of him doing?

bem_transcription: Aba bantu nibakashimya bamulilo baleikisha umutanto, ebashimyo mulilo nga ulepya nokupususha abantu mubusanso.
eng_translation: These people are firefighters who are bringing down their ladder. They put away fire and rescue the survivors.

bem_transcription: Emukuti ici icimbayambaya bakwete ecikwata amenshi?
eng_translation: Is the vehicle they have the one with water?

bem_transcription: Eya nukwai ici icimbayambaya cilakwata amenshi mukati kunuma.
eng_translation: Yes this vehicle has water inside.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo naikala apakutanta.
eng_translation: A young man is sitting on the stair case

bem_transcription: Ngo yu umubi uulele uko kumbi emuti nanaka nangu tauleumfwa bwino nalwala?
eng_translation: What about that one sleeping on the other side. Could he be sick or could he be just tired?

bem_transcription: Uyu muntu alemoneka kwati nibalya balala mumusebo, nanaka limbi aletuusha.
eng_translation: This guy looks like he's homeless. Maybe he's just tired and is resting.

bem_transcription: Bushe ifi fikuulwa kuti fyaba fyamusango shani?
eng_translation: What could these buildings be?

bem_transcription: Iyi incende ni ncende yama offices ilemoneka kwati cilye camilandu.
eng_translation: These are offices. This looks like the courts of law.

bem_transcription: Umwana naingila muli cishofolo camuli matakamaka.
eng_translation: A child is in the tipper.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu umwana nga tabamumwene teti baye bamuposele kumo nefi ifiko bakusa?
eng_translation: Can they not throw the child together with the trash in an event they do not see him?

bem_transcription: Kuti bamuposa bwino bwino fye lelo ici cilemoneka kwati caliiminina fye pa n'ganda.
eng_translation: They can throw him without a doubt. But it's like this has been parked home.

bem_transcription: Bushe cinshi aingilile muli ici icine cintu uyu umwana?
eng_translation: Why is this child in this even?

bem_transcription: Umwana yu aleangala emo aishile salile fye ukwangala.
eng_translation: The child just chose to play from there.

bem_transcription: Amenshi pamumana nayasabuka.
eng_translation: Water has splashed from the river.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici cine cintu cisabwishe amenshi nicinshi?
eng_translation: What is this thing that has splashed water?

bem_transcription: Ici cintu tacilemwenekesha bwino bwino cilemoneka kwati kuti aba muntu.
eng_translation: This thing is not clear. It could be a person.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Kuti yansanswa fye bwino bwino lelo abengilapo balacenjela ukumona ati balemona bwino bwino balelolekesha.
eng_translation: It can easily be. But those that go in look carefully.

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti ca bantu nacibungana cishile mukutamba abamyotoka nangula abafimbayambaya.
eng_translation: A crowd of people have come to watch those with cars.

bem_transcription: Nge fyo ifyabuuta fili kunuma yacimbayambaya cine ici nifinshi?
eng_translation: What are those white things behind this very car?

bem_transcription: Ifyushi filefuma kuma taila yafimbaya mbaya kaili yaleshunguluka lelo motoka taileenda.
eng_translation: It is the smoke coming from the tires that are moving even though the vehicle is not moving.

bem_transcription: Bushe icimbaya mbaya camusango ici baceensesha kuli finshi?
eng_translation: For what do they drive this kind of a vehicle?

bem_transcription: Icimbaya mbaya ca so baceensha nga balecilikanamo.
eng_translation: They drive this kind of car when they are racing.

bem_transcription: Imbwa naimya icimuti.
eng_translation: A dog has lifted a stick.

bem_transcription: Bushe emukuti iyi imbwa ikala umu mwine?
eng_translation: Is that the dogs house?

bem_transcription: Teti twishibe iyo takulemoneka bwino bwino uku nga kuti kwaba nikumpanga olo niku n'ganda.
eng_translation: We can't know. It's not clear where this could be a house or a forest.

bem_transcription: Ninshi iyi ine incende ilemonekela iyabuuta?
eng_translation: Why is this place looking white?

bem_transcription: Kuncende nakupona snow, snow cintu cipona kufyalo ifyatalala.
eng_translation: Because there is snow which rains in cold places.

bem_transcription: Umukashana umunoono aleangala ne mbwa alebutuka.
eng_translation: A young girl is playing with a dog and is running.

bem_transcription: Nga ilya imbi iilemoneka kunuma yakwe kulya bushe kuti aba nayena?
eng_translation: What about that dog behind there could it also be hers?

bem_transcription: Iyi nayo ali nayena lelo pali ifyo yamwene ifyaisansamwise ifyo yamwene ifyo ilefwaya ukutola.
eng_translation: She is with it but it's like it has seen something interesting that it wants to pick.

bem_transcription: Bushe imbwa shine ishi teti shimusume uyu wine umukashana?
eng_translation: Can't these dogs bite this young girl?

bem_transcription: Iyo teti shimusume imbwa shakwe shalimwishiba nokumutemwa.
eng_translation: They can't because they are her dogs and they know and love her.

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti cabantu icikalamba nacibungana nabatantama mumalaini.
eng_translation: A crowd of people is gathered and are in a line.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici cine cinkupiti kuti cilecite nshi?
eng_translation: What could this crowd be doing?

bem_transcription: Ifyo balecita tafilemoneka bwino bwino lelo kuti baba nibakamaching'a balishile ukucilika ukumaching'a.
eng_translation: We can't see clearly what they are doing but they could be in a marching competition.

bem_transcription: Emukuti nibakalisukulu elo iyo?
eng_translation: Does it mean they are school goers?

bem_transcription: Iyo abantu aba balemoneka abacikulile ukuba bakasukulu.
eng_translation: No they look too old to be school goers.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo uukopa ifikope naiminina mumusebo alekopa.
eng_translation: A young man is in the road taking pictures.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ekuti uyu umulumendo alekopa uyu shitata nanamayo?
eng_translation: Is this young man taking picture of this man and woman?

bem_transcription: Iyo shitata namayo uyu balemoneka kwati baleyendela fye umulumendo uyu balekopa ifikuulwa.
eng_translation: No it's like this man and woman are just taking a walk. The young man is taking pictures of buildings.

bem_transcription: Bushe temulandu ukulakopa ifikuulwa ifyo taupelwe insambu?
eng_translation: Is it not a crim to take pictures of a building without permission.

bem_transcription: Kuti caba ati mulandu lelo apo alekopela pali patali ifyakwebati teti bamumone abene bafikuulwa.
eng_translation: It could be a crime but he is at a distance from the buildings so the owners of the buildings cannot see him.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alecofa akacinga ketaila limo.
eng_translation: A young man is riding a unicycle.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo wine uulecofa akacinga bushe akwete fye ukuboko kumo?
eng_translation: Does this man riding the unicycle only have one hand?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya nakwata yonse, lelo lyena akacinga ifyo kapangwa kwikatafye nokuboko kumo.
eng_translation: No he has both hands but this unicycle is meant to be held with only one hand.

bem_transcription: Ulya wiminine kunuma yakwe bushe aletamba umulumendo uyu wine uulecofa akacinga?
eng_translation: Is that one standing behind watching this young man?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya taletamba bali bonse pamo.
eng_translation: No he is not watching but they are together.

bem_transcription: Abana abanoono baleteya umupila uwakumakasa.
eng_translation: Young children are playing football.

bem_transcription: Bushe aba abana kuti bateya mucibansa icikulu icilingene nge citeyamo abakulu?
eng_translation: Can these children play in a large football field?

bem_transcription: Bwino bwino fye abana aba nabo kuti bateya mucibansa iciteyelamo abakulu lelo kuti banaka icapela nga nshi.
eng_translation: Yes they can play in a large field though they can be tired to the bone.

bem_transcription: Bushe utu utu utusapato bafwele bushe eto bateyela umupila nabakulu bene?
eng_translation: Are those shoes they are wearing the same kind as the ones adults use?

bem_transcription: Iyo utusapato utu teti tuteyelemo abakulu iyo utusapato nato natuibela fyepalwatuko.
eng_translation: No adults cannot play in those shoes. Those are just unique.

bem_transcription: Icimbayambaya nacibutuka nacitelela.
eng_translation: A vehicle is speeding and skidding.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici icimbayambaya ninshi citelelele?
eng_translation: Why is this vehicle skidding?

bem_transcription: Icimbayambaya cilekoneka pakona cishelele pantu calibutwike.
eng_translation: Because it was speeding as it was making a turn that is why it was skidding.

bem_transcription: Bushe icimbayambaya ici cine camusango shani?
eng_translation: What kind of a vehicle is this?

bem_transcription: Icimbayambaya cimbayambaya babomfya nga ulecilikana.
eng_translation: It is w race car.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo babili baleteya ubwangalo bwakuifuntula panshi.
eng_translation: Two young men are playing judo.

bem_transcription: Nomba ubu ubwangalo bwakuifuntula panshi teti bakucena nga bakuponya namaka?
eng_translation: But can't hurt yourself when they drop hard in this game?

bem_transcription: Kuti bakucena bwino bwino, lelo abantu aba balapita mumafundisho ayakusambilisha ifyakucita.
eng_translation: You can get hurt but these people have been well trained.

bem_transcription: Bushe ifyo bafwele mumatwi filebomba shani?
eng_translation: What is the use of those things in their ears?

bem_transcription: Ifi fyakwebati beicena kumatwi ilyo baleifuntula.
eng_translation: It's to protect them from injuring the ears as they play.

bem_transcription: Shitata naikala pacitesheni banininapo amabasi.
eng_translation: A man is sitting at a bus station.

bem_transcription: Nga mucimbambaya cine ici ninshi mubelele fye umuntu umo?
eng_translation: Why is there only one person in the vehicle?

bem_transcription: Muli umo pantu bambi nabekila nabafumamo mucimbayambaya.
eng_translation: There's one because people have dropped off.

bem_transcription: Uyu wine muntu uulimo nahsinta mushinku, ninshi asakamanine?
eng_translation: This person on the bus has his head leaning on the palm. What could be the problem?

bem_transcription: Shitata yu nanaka alefwaya ukufika bwangu uko aleya, aleya atuushe.
eng_translation: This man is tired and wants to quickly reach his destination and rest.

bem_transcription: Abashilika balecofola imicanga mu desati.
eng_translation: Soldiers are shoveling sand in the desert.

bem_transcription: Bushe cinshi bengala ukuya mukucofwela fye imicanga umu mwine muntu?
eng_translation: Why would they choose to be shovelling sand from the desert.

bem_transcription: Aba abashilika baile mukutrena, nga namumona pali nefitaila kunuma yabo.
eng_translation: These soldiers went for training. If you notice there are even big tires there.

bem_transcription: Ninshi bonse abashilika balapita kuli uku kwine ukutrena?
eng_translation: Do all soldiers undergo this training?

bem_transcription: Namulungika, balapitamo bonse.
eng_translation: You are right they all do.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu lileenda mumusebo nefipampa muminwe.
eng_translation: A group of people is walking on the road with signs in their hands.

bem_transcription: Ngo yu shikulu bantu ali pantashi yabo, bushe umo muli bene?
eng_translation: Is this old man in front also part of the group?

bem_transcription: Naena alinabo nangula alemoneka, wamatontonkanya yakwe nankwe.
eng_translation: He is with them the he seems to be carried away in his own thoughts.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu umusebo baleendelamo tabacilike imyotoka?
eng_translation: Are they not blocking cars in this road?

bem_transcription: Nabashiminike myotoka, imyotoka shileminina nga shamona ibumba lya so.
eng_translation: They have. Cars stop when there is such a crowd.

bem_transcription: Umwana naiminina nafwala nelaya ilyabuuta pantashi yacibumbile icilefumya amenshi.
eng_translation: A child is standing in front of a water fountain and is wearing a white dress.

bem_transcription: Incende iyi alipo ni n'ganda yakwe nangu ali kuncende kumbi?
eng_translation: Is this place his/her house or it's just someone else's place?

bem_transcription: Iyo apa pantu beta ati pa paki eko baya abantu mukutuusha nangu ukwikala muleisha, abana nabo baleangala.
eng_translation: No this is a park where people go to rest and chat and where children play.

bem_transcription: Uyu umwana ele eka kuncende ku nangu ali nomuntu umbi?
eng_translation: Is this child alone or with someone?

bem_transcription: Ali nabafyashi bakwe abalemukopa.
eng_translation: The child is with the parents who are taking pictures.

bem_transcription: Umwana alepepeka ifyuni.
eng_translation: The child is chasing birds.

bem_transcription: Bushe ifi ifyuni fyamusango shani?
eng_translation: What kind of birds are these?

bem_transcription: Ifyoni filemoneka kwati fibaata.
eng_translation: These birds look like ducks.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu umwana ifi ifibaata alepepeka alefwaya ukufipaya?
eng_translation: Is the child trying to kill these ducks that the child is chasing?

bem_transcription: Iyo teti afipaye aleangala fye nafyo aleumfwa bwino.
eng_translation: No the child cannot kill them. He/She is just enjoying playing with them.

bem_transcription: Umukashana nanina pe hosi.
eng_translation: A girl is on a horse.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu umushipi afwele ubombe nshi?
eng_translation: What is the use of this belt she is wearing?

bem_transcription: Uyu umushipi wakukaka pakwebati epona ilyo ihosi lileenda.
eng_translation: This is so that she doesn't fall from the horse.

bem_transcription: Ili ihosi akwelelepo lyapamyabo nangu lyakuncende fye kumbi?
eng_translation: Is this horse theirs or it's just from another place.

bem_transcription: Iyo teti cishiibikwe nga lyapamyabo nangula iyo.
eng_translation: No we cannot tell if it's theirs or if it's from another place.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo abanoono nabeminina pafisooso.
eng_translation: Young boys are standing on litter

bem_transcription: Bushe ifi ifisooso bemininepo teti fibalwalike ifi bali nenkasa?
eng_translation: They are not even wearing shoes. Will this litter not make them sick?

bem_transcription: Kuti fyabalwalika fye bwino bwino.
eng_translation: It can make them sick.

bem_transcription: Bulwele nshi bengalwala ukwiminina pafisooso apa?
eng_translation: What disease can they contract from standing on litter.

bem_transcription: Kuti balwala amalwele ayalekanalekana ifyapala cholera.
eng_translation: They can get different diseases such as chorela.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alekwela pamutanto.
eng_translation: A young man is climbing the ladder.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo wine bushe ewacilatema ifimuti ifi ifiponene panshi?
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Emukwai, umutanto eo alebomfya ukuya mukufitemena.
eng_translation: Is this the same young man who cut down these trees down here?

bem_transcription: Nge fi ifikumkumbiti fyakashika alefibomfeshe nshi?
eng_translation: What is he using these red containers for?

bem_transcription: Emuli amafuta ayakubika muco aletemena cimashini.
eng_translation: That's where there is fuel for the cutting machine.

bem_transcription: Shitata aleenda mumusebo nomukashi wakwe no mwana.
eng_translation: A man is walking in the road with his wife and child.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu umukashi wakwe ninshi afwalile icitambala umusango yu uwakuifimba konse kumenso?
eng_translation: Why is this woman have a head covering which is even covering her face?

bem_transcription: Uyu afwele icitambala mumusango waso pantu etambi shakuntu apepa.
eng_translation: Because that is the tradition in her religion

bem_transcription: Nga nintambi shabo ishakufwala icitambala uyu umusango ninshi tafwikile umwana wakwe ififine?
eng_translation: If it's their tradition to wear a head covering like this, why is the child not dressesd in the same manner?

bem_transcription: Uyu umwana talakula ukufika pamushinku uo bamba ukukaka icitambala.
