eng_translation: the child has not yet reached that age of putting on a head covering.

bem_transcription: Bashitata babili abafwele ifyakashika nabeminina nashitata uufwele ifyafiita.
eng_translation: two men wearing red a standing with a man wearing black.

bem_transcription: Cinshi baleikatila uyu umunanbo panuma bushe alelosha?
eng_translation: Why are they touching their friends back is he morning?

bem_transcription: Iyouyu shitata umbi alekontama ukulanga ukutootela.
eng_translation: No this other man is bending showing thankfulness.

bem_transcription: Ngecho cilemoneka icabeeka pantashi yabo mwisamba sambako umu bushe nicinshi?
eng_translation: What is that shiny thing below?

bem_transcription: Ici cilepala icimbayambaya.
eng_translation: That looks like a vehicle.

bem_transcription: Shitata aleenda mumbali yamusebo
eng_translation: A man is walking on the side of the road.

bem_transcription: Bushe shitata uyu ewingalemba ifyo ifili apo apakutusha abantu?
eng_translation: Could this be the man that wrote those things on the resting place?

bem_transcription: Iyo shitata uyu akulisha ukulalenga ifi kucibumba abengacite fi bana abanoono.
eng_translation: No this man is too old for that it should have been kids.

bem_transcription: Bushe temulandu nga bakwikata ulelemba lemba?
eng_translation: Is graffiti not a crime?

bem_transcription: Mulandu uwakula nga nshi, balatwala nakumacelo
eng_translation: It is a big crime you can actually be jailed for it.

bem_transcription: Shitata naiminina naikata nakumutwe.
eng_translation: A man is standing and is holding his head.

bem_transcription: Uyu shitata alemoneka ngo mubomfi bushe nindungika?
eng_translation: This man looks like your worker. Am I right?

bem_transcription: Endita mukwai, shitata uyu mubomfi wabuteko.
eng_translation: Yes you're right he's a government worker.

bem_transcription: Nincito nshi abomba uyu shitata?
eng_translation: What kind of work does he do?

bem_transcription: Incito abomba teti ishibikwe bwino bwino.
eng_translation: We can't know for sure what work he does.

bem_transcription: Abana abanoono abakashana nabekala baleangala.
eng_translation: Young girls are seated playing.

bem_transcription: Bushe ubu ubwangalo baleangala bwangalobwamusango shani?
eng_translation: What kind of game are they playing?

bem_transcription: Bwangalo baleangala tabwakwate shina baleumfwa fye bwino baleseka.
eng_translation: this game doesn't even have a name they're just enjoying laughing.

bem_transcription: Bushe aba abana kuti baba nibamunyina?
eng_translation: Could these children be siblings.

bem_transcription: Endita e, aba bena nibamunyinane, pali abaice, nomwaiceko nomwaice sana.
eng_translation: Yes they are siblings there is a young, the younger one and the youngest?

bem_transcription: Shitata naiminina mumusebo naikata necakulisha.
eng_translation: A man is standing on the road and is holding something to play.

bem_transcription: Ninshi alelishisha mumusebo?
eng_translation: Why is it playing on the road?

bem_transcription: Alefwaya abantu abalepita baleumfwa ifyo alelisha pakutila pamupeleko kalusangu.
eng_translation: He is playing for the passerbys so that they can give him some money.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ekuti nabene bacikuulwe ci nabamusuminisha ukwimininapo?
eng_translation: Does it mean the owner of the building has allowed him to stand there?

bem_transcription: Iyo abene bacikuulwe ci tabakwetepo insambu pamusebo kuti alisha.
eng_translation: The owners of the building don't have any rights there he can play from there.

bem_transcription: Umukashana naiminina pamusebo naimya na flag.
eng_translation: A young lady standing on the road holding a flag.

bem_transcription: Nga aba bakapokola beminine kwati balecingilila abantu ukukanapita, bushe kuti cabe fyo?
eng_translation: Are these cops trying to stop people from going through?

bem_transcription: Aba abashilika balecingilila abantu ukwingila mucikuulwe ci ngefyo fine.
eng_translation: Yes this soldiers are denying people entry into this building.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici cine cikuulw kuti caba cikuulwa camusango shani?
eng_translation: what kind of building is this even?

bem_transcription: Cikuulwa umusangwa ama offices ya bantu bamubuteko.
eng_translation: It is a beauding with government offices.

bem_transcription: Bashitata nabeminina.
eng_translation: Men are standing.

bem_transcription: Ishi iminwe sha aba bantu abali kuntashi shilemoneka ishikalamba ne mibili yabo, bushe bantu nabo?
eng_translation: The hands and bodies of these people in Front look very big. Are they human?

bem_transcription: Aba bantu nabo, imikopele fye yacikope eilelenga bamoneka abakulu ukucila bambi.
eng_translation: They are humans too. They are looking like this because of how the picture was taken.

bem_transcription: Aba bantu aba balemoneka balecite nshi?
eng_translation: what does it look like these people doing?

bem_transcription: Efyo balecita tafiishibikwe bwino bwino.
eng_translation: We don't know what they are doing.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo baleteya umupila wakumoolu eobeta ati bola.
eng_translation: young men are playing football.

bem_transcription: Bushe pali aba abalumendo babili abaleteya ninshi umo ewishile nabalya bantu abaletamba kulya?
eng_translation: Did one of these two young men come with those people that are watching?

bem_transcription: Endita amukwai, pabaleteya bola mukati ebali naba abaletamba.
eng_translation: Yes those people came with one of these young men.

bem_transcription: Bushe ici cani baleteyelamo tacilepele ukuteyelamo bola nangu ici cine nacilinga?
eng_translation: Is this grass not too tall for playing football?

bem_transcription: Icani ici nacilinga fye cili fye bwino.
eng_translation: No the grass is just ok.

bem_transcription: Shitata nanamayo nabekala pe bench mumusebo baleisha.
eng_translation: A man and a woman are sitting on a bench along the road to chatting.

bem_transcription: Bushe aba abantu babili kuti baba bakashi nabalume?
eng_translation: Could these two be husband and wife?

bem_transcription: Kuti caba lelo ukulolesha fye ififine teti twishibe.
eng_translation: We can't tell by just looking but it's possible.

bem_transcription: Bushe kuti waba umulandu ukuteme fimuti ifi?
eng_translation: Could it be a crime to cut these trees down?

bem_transcription: Kuti waba mulandu uukalamba nga nshi pantu ubuteko ebwabyalika ifimuti ifi.
eng_translation: It could be a very big crime because these trees were planted by the government.

bem_transcription: Abakashana balepenta pacibumba.
eng_translation: young women are painting on the wall.

bem_transcription: Ninshi balepenta abakashana aba bene?
eng_translation: What are these young women painting?

bem_transcription: Balepenta amamapu yafyalo.
eng_translation: They are painting maps of countries.

bem_transcription: Ninshi bapusanine ukulepa bambi balemoneka abatali bambi balemoneka abepi.
eng_translation: Why are they different in height? Some look tall and others look short.

bem_transcription: Baleafwana ukupwisha bwangu bambi balepenta ukuya kwisamba amamapu bambi balepenta ukuya kumuulu.
eng_translation: They are working together to finish fast. Some are painting the top part and others are painting the lower part.

bem_transcription: Abakashana nabatoloka mumuulu kumbali yamumana.
eng_translation: Young women have jumped high on a river bank.

bem_transcription: Ninshi aba abakashana baletolokela mukamana nangula iyo?
eng_translation: Are they trying to jump into the river or not?

bem_transcription: Iyo abakashana aba batolweke kumbali fye yakamana tabaletolokela mukamana iyo.
eng_translation: No they're just jumping on the river bank they are not jumping into the river.

bem_transcription: Kuti caba ukuti epo baletolokela pepi nangu patali?
eng_translation: Is where they are jumping from very far from the river?

bem_transcription: Tapalepele iyo, nga bati balufyanye fye akanoono namukamana kuti baponena.
eng_translation: No it's not. If they are not careful they can even fall into the river.

bem_transcription: Umukashana kasukulu aleenda kumbali yamusebo afuma kusukulu.
eng_translation: A girl is walking on the roadside from school.

bem_transcription: Apa pantu aleenda palemoneka kwati pakuculukila, ninshi nipa bridge?
eng_translation: It looks like that's where people Cross from. Could it be a bridge?

bem_transcription: Palemonekele fyo pantu pakuchulukila nifyo fine pa bridge.
eng_translation: Yes it is a bridge.

bem_transcription: Kuti caba ukuti amayanda yalya ayalemoneka kuntashi yakwe eko aleya?
eng_translation: Could it be that she's going to those houses in front of her?

bem_transcription: Namulungika, eko alelola.
eng_translation: You are right. That is where she is going.

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti cabantu nacikolongana.
eng_translation: A crowd of people is gathered.

bem_transcription: Bushe cinshi cikolonganine ici cine icinkupiti cabantu?
eng_translation: What had caused these people to gather like this?

bem_transcription: Efyo cikolonganine icinkupiti ici teti fishibikwe.
eng_translation: We can't know for sure.

bem_transcription: Ngo yu umulumendo uufulile shati ninshi alecita?
eng_translation: What is this shirtless young man doing?

bem_transcription: Uyu umulumendo aleangala mumenshi aleshunguluka, aleumfwa bwino.
eng_translation: This young man is enjoying playing in the water.

bem_transcription: Umwana ali panshi naikala nabanyina nabamukumbata.
eng_translation: A child is sitting down with the mother hugging her.

bem_transcription: Cinshi bafwalile utusapato bonse utu utwatwa panshi?
eng_translation: Why are they both wearing shoes that are sharp on the base?

bem_transcription: Utusapato bafwala nga baleangala ubwangalo beta ati skating ubo bashelela pali ice.
eng_translation: These are the shoes they were when they are ice skating.

bem_transcription: Nomba ninshi uyu umwana bapakatile alelila?
eng_translation: Does it mean that this child is crying for her to be held like this?

bem_transcription: Kwena uyu napona naicena efyo banyina bamupakatila.
eng_translation: She fell and hurt herself that is why she's been held like this.

bem_transcription: Umwana ali nabawishi baleangala.
eng_translation: A child is playing with the father.

bem_transcription: Bushe ubu bwangalo baleangala, bwangalo bwamusango shani?
eng_translation: What kind of game are they playing?

bem_transcription: Baleensha utumyotoka utunoono mumisebo batantike nomwana yu.
eng_translation: They are driving toy cars on the road.

bem_transcription: Umwana alemoneka uwamwentula sana ninshi ubu ubwangalo busuma sana?
eng_translation: The child has bright smile. Is this game very enjoyable?

bem_transcription: Abana abaume balomfwa bwino ukwangala ne myotoka so umwana yu naumfwa bwino sana.
eng_translation: You boys enjoy playing with cars that is whey he is very happy.

bem_transcription: Umwana ali panshi yamenshi aleowa.
eng_translation: A child is swimming under the water.

bem_transcription: Nomba uyu umwana alecita nokumwentula mumenshi teti anwine nakalya iyo?
eng_translation: This child is even smilling in the water. Can he not drown?

bem_transcription: Iyo umwana uyu alishiba ukowa nangula amwentula amenshi teti yamwingile mukanwa.
eng_translation: No this child knows how to swim. Even when he smiles water cannot enter.

bem_transcription: Kuti caba nibanani balemukopa? Mwine uibikile mumenshi kamela nangu kuli umuntu uulemukopa?
eng_translation: Who could be capturing him? Did he set the camera alone or there is someone else capturing him.

bem_transcription: Pali umuntu walemukopa pantu mumenshi tapali epo cingekala icakukopelako.
eng_translation: There is someone who was capturing him because there is nowhere to set the camera there.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu lileenda nalimya nefipampa muminwe.
eng_translation: A group of people is walking and raising sign posts in their hands.

bem_transcription: Ngoyo shikulubantu ulemoneka? ALemoneka uwasakamana, bushe cishi cilengele?
eng_translation: What about that old man? He looks troubled. What could be the problem?

bem_transcription: Nasakamana shikulu bantu yu pantu ificitike ifyalenga bemye fipampa ifi tafiweme iyo.
eng_translation: It is because he doesn't like what happened and that is why they are protesting.

bem_transcription: Nga aba bantu abashimisheko ifipampa abaleendafye, bushe bali naba bene abantu?
eng_translation: What about these people not holding sign posts are they together with them?

bem_transcription: Namulungama bonse bali pamo.
eng_translation: Yes they are all together.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu ali mumpanga yafimuti.
eng_translation: An old man is in a forest with a lot of trees.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu shikulu bantu finshi alecita palya ali?
eng_translation: What is this old man doing there?

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu uyu kwati aleteme cimuti.
eng_translation: He is cutting down a tree.

bem_transcription: Bushe umu mpanga shikulu bantu teti asumwe ne nsoka?
eng_translation: Can't this old man be bitten by a snake in this forest?

bem_transcription: Kuti asumwa ilelo nafwala amajombo.
eng_translation: He can be. But he is wearing boots.

bem_transcription: Namayo ali mwituuka no mwana muli pulemu.
eng_translation: A woman is in a shop with a child in a prem.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ifintu aleshita aleshitila uyu wine umwana?
eng_translation: Is she buying things for the child?

bem_transcription: Namulungika, namayo yu aishile mukushita ifyamwana.
eng_translation: You are right. This woman is buying something for the baby.

bem_transcription: Ngefyo ifipampa fili ifya mutuntula mutuntula ifyo bakobeke mumuulu fileiminine nshi?
eng_translation: What do those yellowish signs they have hung on top stand for?

bem_transcription: Ifyo fipampa filelanga umutengo wafintu.
eng_translation: They are price tags.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu baikala pa kompyuta aletinika.
eng_translation: An old man is seated pressing the computer.

bem_transcription: Bushe aya amakompyuta yamusango yu yasangwa mu n'ganda nangu kuncito?
eng_translation: Are these type of computers found at home or at work?

bem_transcription: Yalasangwa fye ukuli konse cilinga fye kumuntu uushitile uko atemwa ukuibika.
eng_translation: They can be anywhere. It just depends on where the person who has bought wants to put it.

bem_transcription: Ukulingana nefyo alemoneka alelolesha pali kompyuta isa, payakukulyo nangu kukuso?
eng_translation: Looking at how is seated, is he looking at the computer on his right or left?

bem_transcription: Alelolesha paibelele kukuso.
eng_translation: He is looking at the one on the right.

bem_transcription: Bakapokola ne fimpompo kumutwe.
eng_translation: Cops with helmets.

bem_transcription: Bushe ninshi bakolonganina abantu abengi pamo so?
eng_translation: Why are all these people gathered here?

bem_transcription: Bafuma mukulumba umupila.
eng_translation: They are from watching a football match

bem_transcription: Ngefi ifimpompo fifwele bakapokola bushe fyanshi?
eng_translation: What about these helmets that cops are wearing. What are they for?

bem_transcription: Ifimpompo bafwele ifi fyakuicingilila imitwe shabo nga baamba ukupoosa amabwe abantu.
eng_translation: They are for protecting their heads in case people start throwing stones.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu lya bantu nabekala nabatabilila itebulo.
eng_translation: A group of people is seated around the table.

bem_transcription: Ibumba line likolonganine panse elo cilemoneka napatalala, bushe ninshi bengekalila panse?
eng_translation: They are seated outside and it looks cold. Why would they sit outside?

bem_transcription: Bekalile panse kumulandu wakuti inamba nalikula ilye bumba teti bakwane mukati.
eng_translation: It is because they are many and cannot fit inside.

bem_transcription: Awe nausosa bushe ifi ifili pa tebo filyo?
eng_translation: You are right. Is that food on the table?

bem_transcription: Ee filyo, bakumanine ubushiku ukutila balile pamo pantu bena mupalamino.
eng_translation: Yes it is food. They are having dinner together because they are neighbors.

bem_transcription: Namayo no mulumendo nabemya umuseke uusungile ifintu ifyakashika.
eng_translation: A woman and a boy a carrying a basket with red things inside.

bem_transcription: Bushe ifi ifintu fyakashika basendele kuti fyaba nifinshi?
eng_translation: What could these red things be?

bem_transcription: Ifi kuti fyaba nintungulu.
eng_translation: That is afromomum africanum.

bem_transcription: Ngoyu uukonkele panuma bushe kuti aba umo pali bene?
eng_translation: Is the one behind also with them?

bem_transcription: Endita mukwai, uyu uwalekonkamo naena ali nabo.
eng_translation: Yes this one behind is with them

bem_transcription: Abakashana nabalumendo bali mumuputule wakwipikilamo balepange fyakulya.
eng_translation: Young men and young women are in the kitchen preparing food.

bem_transcription: Bonse nabafwala nefyapalana, utusote twabuuta kabili namashati yabuuta.
eng_translation: They are wearing similar clothing. White shirts and white capes

bem_transcription: Elyo bushe ulemona kwati finshi ifi baleipika?
eng_translation: What do you think they are cooking?

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati balepanga umukate.
eng_translation: It looks like they are making bread.

bem_transcription: Nimbona naine nasumina, mukate yu balepanga, elo naufula sana.
eng_translation: I agree. They are making bread and it's a lot.

bem_transcription: Bakapokola babili nabeminina nabekata namaboko mumatumba.
eng_translation: Two cops are standing with their hands in their pockets.

bem_transcription: Uku bali kulemoneka nikumpanga elo balemoneka abafulwa pamenso.
eng_translation: It looks like they are in the forest and they look angry on their faces.

bem_transcription: Cishinka, nimbona uyu uuli kukulyo kwesu ifyo alemoneka, pamenso nakaka ne nkanshi.
eng_translation: I have seen that this one on the right even has a frown on his face.

bem_transcription: Katwishi nga ninshi iibapapwishe pakuti bamone fi pamenso, elo namayo uyu kapokola naikata nacimo muminwe.
eng_translation: I don't know what has surprised them for them to look like this. The female cop is holding something in her hands.

bem_transcription: Elyo kunuma yabo kulemoneka ifimuti ifyakatapakatapa nafikwata namaluba ayakashika.
eng_translation: there seems to be green trees behind them with red flowers.

bem_transcription: Banamayo nabashitata nababuungana.
eng_translation: Men and women are gathered.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati bonse balefwaya ukumona uyu namayo uuli pakati pantu bonse balelwila ukumumona.
eng_translation: It's like they all want to see this woman in between.

bem_transcription: Nakabili cilepala kwati uyu namayo uuli mumagalashi yafiita eubetile ku elo balekutika kuli ena.
eng_translation: It's like this woman in black glasses is the one who invited them here because they all are listening to what she is saying.

bem_transcription: Kabili cilemoneka nakalimo ilyashi balelandapo taliweme pantu bonse balemoneka abafulwa.
eng_translation: It's like they all do not like what she is talking about.

bem_transcription: Nga ni uyu shitata ena naikata namumutwe uyu umbi afimbile pamenso cilepala kwati akasuba nakabooma sana.
eng_translation: This other man is touching his head and the other one is covering his face. It looks like the sun is too much.

bem_transcription: Shitata alelisha icilimba ca nsaale.
eng_translation: A man is playing the harp.

bem_transcription: Nafwala namagalshi yafiita abikapo neshati lyakashika kabili na ovuloshi yafiita.
eng_translation: He is wearing black glasses, a red shirt and a black overall.

bem_transcription: Elyo talelisha fye icilimba ceka cilemoneka aleimba nokwimba pantu naasamuna akanwa.
eng_translation: It appears he's playing as well as singing because his mouth is open.

bem_transcription: Kunuma yakwe kulemoneka kwaliba ne cikuulwa icitali sana.
eng_translation: There is a tall building behind him

bem_transcription: Nomba bashitata aba nabena ovuloshi bafwele kwati yabana.
eng_translation: This overall he is wearing looks like it is for a child.

bem_transcription: Shitata nabifya pamenso.
eng_translation: A man has a frown on the face.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka kwati nakalipa pantu nakaka ne nkanshi.
eng_translation: He looks angry.

bem_transcription: Elyo alemoneka kwati nifilya nabamuma icikoti elo cakalipa sana.
eng_translation: It's like someone has hit him with a whip and it is painting.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ati aliluka ne mishishi shakwe?
eng_translation: Have you seen that he has also plaited his hair?

bem_transcription: Nimbona aliluka tumukule na meno ayaboola.
eng_translation: He has braids with rotten teeth.

bem_transcription: Namayo ali n'ganda yakwe alewamya.
eng_translation: A woman is in her house cleaning.

eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

eng_translation: On top of a chair is a bag where she has put papers.

bem_transcription: ELo pantu alepukuta petebulo napamoneka bwino pamoneka apabusaka kabili apabeeka.

eng_translation: They are competing from a hill.

bem_transcription: Utu utumilundu nitulya utwakutila nga apishapo incinga, incinga yalaima mumuulu eifi tulemona amacinga nayema mumuulu.
eng_translation: These are the hills they use in these competitions such that when a bicycle goes through, it goes high up into the air.

bem_transcription: Elo kuntu balecimfyanishisha kwaliba no tumuti uwingi utwayemba nga nshi.
eng_translation: This place they are competing from has many beautiful trees.

eng_translation: But you need to be very good at cycling when playing this game otherwise you can fall and break your bones.

eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

eng_translation: The place where they are jumping from looks very good with green grass and beautiful flowers.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka kwati apa ni pa n'ganda fye pantu uko baloleshe kulemoneka ne cikuulwa icapale n'ganda.
eng_translation: This looks like it's a home because there looks to be a house behind.

eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati talolesha bwino emulandu wine alebomfeshe amagalashi pakutila engabelenga bwino.
eng_translation: It looks like he has a poor eyesight that is why he is using spectacles to read.

bem_transcription: Elo petebulo abikile icitabo nabikapo nakabokoshi kakubikamo amagalashi kabili ne citabo nacimbi.
eng_translation: On the table where he has put the book is where he has also put the box for glasses and another book.

bem_transcription: Elo uyu shikulu bantu alikwata ne pala pamena fye utumishishi utunoono.

bem_transcription: Namayo ali nashofolo mumicanga.

eng_translation: What is this greenish thing?

bem_transcription: Umo umwamfuli untu wakashika elyo umbi untu wafiita.

eng_translation: There are also beautiful small trees outside this building and big trees too.

eng_translation: She is outside a house that looks dirty.

eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

eng_translation: These men are going for a swim because they are carrying black bags where they out their swimming gear.

eng_translation: A young lady has opened her mouth eating buscuits.

eng_translation: By the way she is opening her mouth you can tell that this young lady loves eating.

eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

eng_translation: It's like what has been whispered to this woman is very funny because she is happy and laughing.

eng_translation: This place looks like Deep in the hills because I can only see a lot of trees behind them.

Nomba bushe naumona ukutila ici icangalo aleangala cakusheleleka?
eng_translation: Have you seen that the game he is playing involves sliding?

bem_transcription: Ee, nimbona elo icangalo cakaena nga tapooseleko amano kuti aicena ububi pantu kuti apona ifibi sana.
eng_translation: I have seen. And if he is not careful he can fall and hurt himself badly.

bem_transcription: Nomba pakutila nga cakutila aliponene aicena nafwala icakumucingilisha kumutwe nakumaboko.
eng_translation: But even if he fell he is wearing something to protect his head and arms.

bem_transcription: Akamwana akamukashana kali panse kaleangala.
eng_translation: A girl child is playing outside.

bem_transcription: Nakafwala necampepo icakaba sana, kabili netoloshi lyakaba sana kabili ne nsapato kafwele shine nasho shalikaba.
eng_translation: She is wearing a very warm jersey, a warm trousers and warm shoes.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ukutila kunuma yakwe kulemoneka bamotoka?
eng_translation: Have you seen that there are cars behind her?

bem_transcription: Ee, nimbona elo nasho shingi sana pantu nabashitantamika fye.
eng_translation: Yes and a lot of them.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati uku ni ncende uko abantu abengi basangwa nangula kucalichi.
eng_translation: This looks like a church or just a place where many people are found.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo nabakashana baleimba.
eng_translation: Young men and young women are singing.

bem_transcription: Elyo bambi abali kunuma balelishe filimba.
eng_translation: The ones behind are playing the instruments.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati abantu abengi nabesa mukubatamba ilyo baleimba.
eng_translation: It's like a lot of people have come to watch them.

bem_transcription: Elo kabili cilemoneka kwati ulwimbo lwakaena naluwama sana pantu balemoneka abansansa pamenso.
eng_translation: It also looks like the song is beautiful because they look happy on their faces.

bem_transcription: Nomba pantu baleimbila paliba amalaiti ayakisha sana.
eng_translation: There are a lot of bright lights where they are singing from.

bem_transcription: Akabwa kalefwaya ukunina pachuulu.
eng_translation: A dog wants to climb a hill.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili cilemoneka pali uukekete pantu nakakwate ntambo mumukoshi iyo bakakakile.
eng_translation: It looks like someone is holding it because it on a leash.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ukutila uwikete ntambo ali pamuulu pantu kalefwaya ukunina?
eng_translation: Have you noticed that the one holding the leash is in top? That's why it wants to climb.

bem_transcription: Ee nimbona, nomba umuntu wakaena talemoneka.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen but the person is not visible.

bem_transcription: Akabwa kakaena kakwata umucila uwapetekana.
eng_translation: The dog has a coiled tail.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo ali kululamba lwamumana.
eng_translation: A young man is at the beach.

bem_transcription: Naimya nokuulu kaili namaboko mumuulu.
eng_translation: He has raised his leg and both his hands.

bem_transcription: Elyo afwele ifyafiita kumuulu nakunshi.
eng_translation: He is wearing black top and bottom.

bem_transcription: Elo kabili pamumana pene pali necibwato icikulu sana.
eng_translation: There's a big boat in the sea

bem_transcription: Ici icibwato cilemoneka icabuuta mumbali elo pakati cilemoneka icamakumbi makumbi.
eng_translation: This boat looks white on the sides and blue in the middle.

bem_transcription: Akamwana akamwaume kali kuncende uko bangalila.
eng_translation: A young child is at the play ground.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Kunuma yakako balibikako nefimawilo ifyafiita.
eng_translation: Behind it are black tyres.

bem_transcription: Elo kunuma yamawilo kulemoneka ne fimuti ifyakatapakatapa.
eng_translation: And behind the tires are green trees.

bem_transcription: Pantu babika amawilo palemoneka palifulo mucanga uwingi sana.
eng_translation: It seems there's a lot of sand where theyve put the tires.

bem_transcription: Umukashana naikala pancende iyakulilapo.
eng_translation: A young lady is at an eating place.

bem_transcription: Incende aliko intu yayemba sana kabili balibikapo notupuna utwakwikalapo.
eng_translation: It is a very nice place and has chairs.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka kwati kuli ifyo alelolesha mukachola alelele pamoolu.
eng_translation: It's like there's something she is looking at in the bag on her thighs.

bem_transcription: Elyo petebulo lyakwe nabikapo notumakapu umuli efo alenwa.
eng_translation: On a table is a cup with something she is drinking.

bem_transcription: Umukashana wakaena alemoneka uwayemba sana no mushishi wakwe nasakula bwino.
eng_translation: The young lady looks very pretty with we'll combed hair.

bem_transcription: Imbwa shibili nashikala panse yang'anda.
eng_translation: Two dogs are sitting outside the house.

bem_transcription: Awe tashiikele bushe naumona ati shileangala imo iyafiita pali nefyo ikwete kukanwa?
eng_translation: No. Have you noticed that they are bit sitting but playing. One is black and has something in the mouth.

bem_transcription: Ee, namona cilepala kwati shilelwishanya pakutila shingapoka ici icili kukanwa.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen. It's like they are fighting for what this black dog has in the mouth.

bem_transcription: Elo kabili imbwa shakaena shine balishifwika no tuntu utwapalana mumukoshi, bushe naumona?
eng_translation: These dogs are wearing something similar around their necks have you noticed?

bem_transcription: Nimbona, elyo nakabili kunuma yashiko kulemoneka utumaluba utwayemba sana.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen and there are beautiful flowers around them.

bem_transcription: Namayo ali pamuulu wabwato.
eng_translation: A woman is in top of a boat.

bem_transcription: Elyo nakwata cimo icabulungana eco akakileko intambo eco aleingisha mumenshi.
eng_translation: Then she has something round with a rope tied to it that she is lowering into the water.

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati ici cintu aleingisha mumenshi cakafwo ubwato pakutila tabubundile.
eng_translation: It's like this thing is to help the boat nit to sink.

bem_transcription: Ubwato bwakaena bulemoneka tebukalamba sana awe iyo bulemoneka bwaliba fye ubwalinga.
eng_translation: The boat doesn't seem to be very big. It is of medium size.

bem_transcription: Nakabili nintemwa fintu ubwato bulemoneka, bulemoneka ubwabusaka kabili bulemoneka ubwabuuta.
eng_translation: I like how the boat is looking. It looks white and clean.

bem_transcription: Abantu nabeminina pancende yakushitapo ifyakulya.
eng_translation: People are standing at a place where they buy food.

bem_transcription: Bushe noyu umukashana naena aleisa pancende iyi ine?
eng_translation: Is this young woman also coming to this place?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya alepita fye mumusebo ena nashita akale.
eng_translation: No she is just passing. She has already bought.

bem_transcription: Uyu uufwele ifyabuuta bushe emwine wancende iyi, euleshitisha?
eng_translation: Is the one in white the owner of the place? Is he the one selling?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Abomba pancende ine iyi.
eng_translation: Yes he works at this place.

bem_transcription: Shitata nabana babili nabanamayo babili nabanina mumotoka.
eng_translation: A man with two children and two women are in the car.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ukutila uku ukwenda takuibelele fye, finshi ulemona ifilecitika?
eng_translation: Have you seen that this walk looks suspicious? What is happening?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Mumbali yamusebo mwaliba namayanda eyo bakuula lelo teyakalamba yanoono.
eng_translation: There are houses that have been built on the roadside but they are small.

bem_transcription: Abantu abalekana lekana baleenda mumusebo.
eng_translation: Different people are walking on the road.

bem_transcription: Elo umusebo wakaena wabela pakati yafikuulwa fibili.
eng_translation: The road is between two buildings.

bem_transcription: Ifi ifikuulwa filemoneka ifyayemba bwino sana.
eng_translation: These buildings look very beautiful.

bem_transcription: Elyo nabantu baliko uku nabafula nga nshi.
eng_translation: Even the people here are many.

bem_transcription: Cila muntu cilepala kwati napamfiwa kuli uko alebutukila.
eng_translation: Everyone looks like they are busy going somewhere.

bem_transcription: Akamwana kaleangala panse ya n'ganda elyo nakekata kutushimbi tuntu bakuulila mumbali ya n'ganda.
eng_translation: A child is playing outside the house and is holding the metal bars that gave been built around the house.

bem_transcription: Elo akamwana kakeana nakafwala akasote kakshika kabili ne shati ilyamakumbi makumbi.
eng_translation: The child is wearing a red hat and a blue shirt.

bem_transcription: Bushe finshi ulemona ifili kunum yakwe?
eng_translation: What can you see behind him?

bem_transcription: Kunuma yakako kwena kulemoneka kuli umuntu uulewamya akakwenseshamo umwana
eng_translation: Behind the child is someone repairing a prem.

bem_transcription: Nakabili pambali yakwe pali nakapuna apo babikile akachola kafiita.
eng_translation: On the childs side is a chair with a black bag on it.

bem_transcription: Banamayo nabashitata nabekala mucikuulwa.
eng_translation: Men and women are sitting in a building.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Nga ni uyu ena uukwete icamakumbi makumbi icakufwala alemoneka uwasekelela cilepala kwati fintu akwete muminwe nafimusekesha.
eng_translation: The one wearing blue looks joyous. It looks like what he is holding in his hands is making him laugh.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Aba banamayo bali kunuma yabo bena baleshimika fye.
eng_translation: The women behind him are chatting.

bem_transcription: Umwana umukashana naiminina naimya nafimo kuminwe.
eng_translation: A little girl is standing, holding something in her hands.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati baciya mukushite fintu, ifyo fine ifintu efyo balongele mufipepa fintu akwete kuminwe.
eng_translation: It's like they went to buy some things which are in the paper bags she is holding.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ifyo uyu umwana alemoneka?
eng_translation: Have you seen how this child is looking?

bem_transcription: Nimbona, uyu umwana alemoneka uwabusaka, pantu nafwala nakasote akabuuta kabili nakalilaya akabuuta mwapita nefyakashika.
eng_translation: This child looks clean, wearing a white hat and a white dress with red stripes.

bem_transcription: Insapato afwele shintu shabuuta ne ncende aliko ilemoneka iyabusaka sana.
eng_translation: The shoes she's wearing are also white and the place where she is is beautiful.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo natoloka ukufuma pe libwe alefwaya ukutolokela mumenshi.
eng_translation: A young man is jumping from a stone into the water.

bem_transcription: Elo pakutoloka pene alemoneka uwansansa, cilepala naumfwa pakutoloka aletoloka.
eng_translation: It looks like he is happy for jumping.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ifyo incende iyi ilemoneka?
eng_translation: Have you seen how this place is looking?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Ukulundapo nakabili, kumbali kulemoneka ifimuti ifyaputulwa bwino sana ifyo batantamika mumusango uwayemba.
eng_translation: Additionally there are well cut trees in the side that are well aligned.

bem_transcription: Motoka ili pakati ka menshi naibuunda
eng_translation: A car has sunk in the middle of the water.

bem_transcription: Elo amenshi yakaena yengi elo mukati kamotoka mulemoneka muli nabantu.
eng_translation: There is a lot of water and there seems to be people inside the car.

bem_transcription: Nomba cilemoneka kwati iiyi motoka taibundile fye ilefwaya ukutoloka aka akashiba ka menshi.
eng_translation: It looks like this car hasn't sunk but wants to get passed this water.

bem_transcription: Iyi incende yakaena tayakwata ubulalo eico icilelenga iyi motoka ilepita mumenshi.
eng_translation: There is no bridge here that is why the car is passing through the water.

bem_transcription: Incende yakaena kwalifule fimuti elo cilemoneka kwati nikumpili.
eng_translation: There are a lot of trees in this area and it looks like it's a mountain area.

bem_transcription: Namayo nashitata bali mumuputule balepekanye fyakulya.
eng_translation: A man and a woman are in a room preparing food.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Shitata nabika pani iikalamba pacitofu.
eng_translation: The man has put a big pan on the stove.

bem_transcription: Elyo namayo ena alemoneka kwati nakalimo eulepele fyakulya.
eng_translation: The woman looks like the one rolling the food.

bem_transcription: Elyo uyu umuputule ulemoneka tecikuulwa kantemba fye kantu bapoopa umo bashitishishe fyakulya.
eng_translation: This doesn't look like any other building but it's like a small stand where they sell food.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo naikala mumbali yamusebo aletinika lamya.
eng_translation: A young man is seated in the road side pressing his phone.

bem_transcription: Umu mumbali yamusebo balikuulamo nakantemba ako bashitishishapo ifyakulya.
eng_translation: There is even a stand where they sale food on the road side.

bem_transcription: Lubali lumbi kuli abalumendo abakwete cimashini balewamyo musebo.
eng_translation: On the other side are young men with a machine reparing the road.

bem_transcription: Elo kabili mumbali yamusebo mwine mulepita namotoka.
eng_translation: There is even a vehicle passing on the roadside.

bem_transcription: Uyu umusebo wabela mumbali yamayanda.
eng_translation: This road is near houses.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo nabakashana bonse nabekala patupuna mumuputule.
eng_translation: Young men and women are all sitting on a chair in a room.

bem_transcription: Aba abalumendo bakaena nabakashana cilemoneka nakalimo baletamba ifilecitika panse.
eng_translation: These young men and women look like they are watching something outside.

bem_transcription: Nakabili uyu umuputule ulemoneka wabela pamuulu sana icibangukile ukutamba fyonse ifilecitika panse.
eng_translation: This room is upstairs that is why they can easily see what is happening outside.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili panse yakaena palemoneka paliba ifikuulwa ifitali kabili namenshi.
eng_translation: There seems to be tall buildings and water outside.

bem_transcription: Nimbona pali nobulalo, mumbali mwalipita na menshi.
eng_translation: There is even a bridge with water on the sides.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo nomukashana nabakumbatana.
eng_translation: A young man and woman are holding each other.

bem_transcription: Uko beminine takulemoneka kwati kulekala abant bushe kuti kwaba nikwisa?
eng_translation: This place doesn't seem to be inhabited by people. Where could this be?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya takwikala abantu balayako fye abantu mukutamba.
eng_translation: No there are no people that live here. They just go for scenery.

bem_transcription: Apa beminine niapa chuulu?
eng_translation: Are they standing on a hill?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Beminine pa chuulu pakumona ifyo incende yapangwa.
eng_translation: Yes they are on a hill to see how this place is made.

bem_transcription: Akabwa kaleangala pancende iisuma sana.
eng_translation: A dog is playing at a very beautiful place.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili akabwa kakaena pali ifyo kalefwaya ukwanka ukubomfya akanwa.
eng_translation: There is something that this dog is trying to catch with the mouth.

bem_transcription: Nomba bushe naumona ukutila akabwa aka kalemoneka akayemba?
eng_translation: Have you seen how beautiful this dog is?

bem_transcription: Ca cine kalemoneka akayemba nga nshi pantu kaliba akabuuta elo mwapita nefyafiita.
eng_translation: Yes it's very beautiful. It is white and has black spots.

bem_transcription: Elyo incende kaliko intu yayemba nayo, balisungapo ulunkoto.
eng_translation: This place is beautiful with a lot of grass.

bem_transcription: Imbwa ili kuncende yakwangala ileangala.
eng_translation: A dog is at a playground playing.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati ilefwaya ukutoloka akamuti eko babikile.
eng_translation: It's like it is trying to jump a stick that that has been put.

bem_transcription: Elyo iyi incende bapangila fye ukutila imbwa shileya mukwangala pantu nefyakwangalipo fintu bakuulapo nangu fintu babikako fyakulinga fye imbwa.
eng_translation: This place is meat for dogs because even all the structures just fit dogs.

bem_transcription: Elo kabili icakulundapo fye kulemoneka kuli nabantu nabambi abali kunuma yambwa, kabili kuli necilimba nakalimo balelisha necilimba lintu imbwa shileangala.
eng_translation: There are also people behind these dogs and a speaker. It's like they are playing music as the dogs are playing.

bem_transcription: Nangu cilemoneka kwati imbwa balasgitwala uku kuncende pakutila shingaya mukucimfyanya.
eng_translation: Or maybe they take their dogs to this place so that they compete against each other.

bem_transcription: Namayo naikata umupila muminwe elo naiminina.
eng_translation: A woman is standing with a ball in her hands.

bem_transcription: Uyu namayo wakaeana afwele amagalashi ayakashika kabili nakakila nomushishi panuma.
eng_translation: This woman is wearing red glasses and had tied her hair behind.

bem_transcription: Nafwala akashati akabuuta nakabili akepi sana amaboko.
eng_translation: She is wearing a white shirt with very short sleeves.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Nomba cilemoneka kwati uyu namayo ali pabukulu pantu ulufumo lulemoneka ulwaina.
eng_translation: It looks like this woman is pregnant because she has a big stomach.

bem_transcription: Shitata alelisha icilimba.
eng_translation: A man is playing a radio.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Kunuma yakwe kuli ne fishimbi fintu baimika elo balikobekako nensalu ishikwete ifyakashika nefyafiita elyo nefyabuuta.
eng_translation: There are metal bars are behind where they have hang coths that have red, black and white.

bem_transcription: Elo kabili shitata umwine untu wafiita elo kabili ne mishishi shakwe shintu shayemba nga nshi elo nasho shalifiita.
eng_translation: This man is dark and his hair too is black and nice.

bem_transcription: Elo uyu shitata alyumpa, pantu kukuboko alibikako cilya cifwala bonse abaupa, elyo kumenso nabikako namagalashi.
eng_translation: This man is married because he has a ring and he is wearing glasses.

bem_transcription: Bashitata bali pacangalo cakucimfyanya icakucofa amacinga.
eng_translation: Men are on a cycling competition.

bem_transcription: Elyo nakabili nabafwala ifyakucofelamo incinga ifyayanguka.
eng_translation: They are wearing light clothes meant for cycling.

bem_transcription: Mumbali yamusebo balibikamo notushimbi uto utucingilila abalecofa.
eng_translation: There are metal bars on the roadside to protect the cyclists.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo babili nabekala panshi.
eng_translation: Young men are sitting down.

bem_transcription: Umo pali bena aletinika lamya elyo kabili umo alelolesha mumbali.
eng_translation: One is pressing the phone and one is looking on the side.

bem_transcription: Elyo nakabili bonse babili bafwele ifyamakumbi makumbi kumuulu.
eng_translation: Both are wearing blue clothes.

bem_transcription: Mupepi wa uyu uuletinika lamya pali akamupando apo abikile fwaka no bwalwa muli kapu.
eng_translation: Near the one pressing the phone is a table where they have a cigarette and bear in a cup.

bem_transcription: Pantu bekele palemoneka ni panse ya n'ganda pantu kunuma yabo kucibumba kulemoneka namaluba.
eng_translation: It looks like this is outside the house because there are even flowers around.

bem_transcription: Abana babili abalumendo nabanina pacimuti.
eng_translation: Two young boys are on a tree.

bem_transcription: Elo abana bakaena balemoneka abalamba pamenso.
eng_translation: The young boys are dirty on their faces.

bem_transcription: Elyo pali umukalamba no mwaice, uyu wikele panshi emukalamba elo uyu wiminine emwaice.
eng_translation: There's the older one and the younger one. The one seated is the older one while the one standing is the younger one.

bem_transcription: Kabili kunuma yabo kuli ne fimuti fibili ifyakatapa katapa ifikulu.
eng_translation: There are two big green trees behind them.

bem_transcription: Nomba umwaice bantu naasamuna mukanwa kwati nifilya bacimweba ati asama!
eng_translation: Now the dog is opening the mouth as if he has been told to do so.

bem_transcription: Shitata nanina pali kabalwe mucibansa ca fyangalo.
eng_translation: A man is on a horse in a play ground.

bem_transcription: Elo kabalwe wakaena natolokesha sana icakwebati shitata wakaena alefwaya nokupona.
eng_translation: The horse has jumped so high up that the man wants to fall.

bem_transcription: Nomba bushe naumona ukutila ici icibansa abantu nabafulisha abeshile mukutamba?
eng_translation: Have you seen that there are too many people in this ground that have come to watch.

bem_transcription: Nimbona, abantu bena nabafula, limbi nakalimo balibutemwa sana ubu ubwangalo.
eng_translation: Yes the people are many. Maybe they love this game very much.

bem_transcription: Elyo nga twalolekesha sana sana kunuma uku ukuli abantu kulepala kwati kulefuka ne chuushi cilepala kwati kuli ifyo baleocako.
eng_translation: When we look too far behind there is some smoke. It looks like they are burning something.

bem_transcription: Shitata naiminina aletinika lamya pakati kamusebo.
eng_translation: A man is standing on the road pressing his phone.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Nomba bushe naumona ifyo shitata uyu uuletinika lamya afwele?
eng_translation: But have you seen what this man who is pressing the phone is wearing?

bem_transcription: Ee, nimbona,filemoneka ifyamasenkebele nalimo fyakusekesha abantu elo bushe naumona ati kuli nakapokolauwiminine uulemulolesha?
eng_translation: Yes I have seen. it's a robe maybe to make people laugh. Have you seen that police officer standing there looking at him?

bem_transcription: Nimbona, nomba uyu kapokola cilepala kwati nacimupapusha ukumona fintu afwele.
eng_translation: I have seen. It's like this officer is amazed at what he is wearing.

bem_transcription: Bashitata bali pamulimo pakati kamusebo.
eng_translation: Men are working in the middle of the road.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Nomba bushe naumona ukutila pantu bali pamuulu wabo palipita umusebo naumbi?
eng_translation: Have you noticed that there is another road above them and there are people there?

bem_transcription: Ca cine, nimbona, elo umusebo wakaena uwapamuulu ulemoneka untu wayemba, bushe naumona kabili imyotoka ifyo shiminine?
eng_translation: True. I have seen. The road on top looks very nice. Have you seen how the cars are parked?

bem_transcription: Nimbona, nashiminina lubali lumbi uku, cilepala kwati bashebele ukutila shipita.
eng_translation: I have seen they are parked on the other end. It's like they have been told they will not go through.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo ali mupepi nakamana.
eng_translation: The boy is near the river.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo uyu tafwele ne shati, bushe alefwaya ukowa?
eng_translation: The boy is not even wearing a shirt. Does he want to swim?

bem_transcription: Ee, emapange yakwe yakutolokela mumenshi.
eng_translation: Yes he wants to dive into the water.

bem_transcription: Nomba umumana wine uyu ulemoneka uukulu sana, bushe teti anwine?
eng_translation: This river though looks very big. Will he not drown?

bem_transcription: Kuti anwina, echo alefwaila apaliko apepi.
eng_translation: He may drown. That is why he is looking for where it is not deep.

bem_transcription: Icikuulwa naciikata umulilo cilepya.
eng_translation: The building is on fire.

bem_transcription: Elo cilemoneka kwati nabeta nashilya imyotoka na bantu abesa mukubutukila lilya kwaba ubusanso bwamulilo.
eng_translation: It's like they have even called the fire brigade and ambulances.

bem_transcription: Kaili ishi shine imyotoka nashifula sana pantu shimbi shileposa amenshi ukufuma kunuma, shimbi shili kuntashi pakutila umulilo benga ushimya.
eng_translation: These are lots of vehicles, some are trying to extinguish the fire from the front others from the back.

bem_transcription: Nomba cilemoneka nakalimo uyu umulilo naushupa sana pantu ucili uleaka nelyo baleposako amenshi.
eng_translation: It looks like it's very difficult because they are trying but the fire is still on.

bem_transcription: Elyo ici cine icikuulwa cabela fye mumbali yamusebo, nomba pamulandu wa ubu ubusanso takuli motoka iilepitila kuli iyi incende.
eng_translation: This building is just along the road but due to this accident no vehicle is allowed to go through.

bem_transcription: Shitata naikala petebulo mucikuulwa.
eng_translation: A man is sitting on the table in the building.

bem_transcription: Naikata necitabo epo balenga umuntu.
eng_translation: He's holding a book where there are people.

bem_transcription: Umuntu wakaena untu balenga pacitabo nakwata namasengo.
eng_translation: The person drawn on the book even has a phone

bem_transcription: Elo shitata wakaena namwentula bwino sana, nakalimo balimweba ati balemukopa icikope.
eng_translation: The man has a very bright smile. its like he was told they were taking a picture of him.

bem_transcription: Nakabili alemoneka uwabusaka pantu nafwala icabuuta elo cilemoneka icabusaka.
eng_translation: He looks smart because he is wearing clean white clothes.

bem_transcription: Imbwa ilebutuka mulubansa.
eng_translation: The dog is running in the yard.

bem_transcription: Ulu ulubansa lwakaena lwabela fye pa n'ganda elo lulemoneka ulwabusaka.
eng_translation: This yard is around the house and it looks good.

bem_transcription: Cishinka lulemoneka ulwabusaka pantu no lukonto lulemoneka ulwayemba bwino sana ulwafuunda, cilepala kwati baletilila cila bushsiku.
eng_translation: Very true, the lawn too looks nice and healthy. It looks like they water it on a daily basis.

bem_transcription: Elo kabili mumbali yalubansa lwine bakulililamo nakapuna akakwikalapo ngo umuntu alefwaya ukutusha.
eng_translation: On the edges of the loan they have built a seat for someone who wants to rest.

bem_transcription: Imbwa ilemoneka iyabusaka sana nakabili baliifwalika nakantu mumukoshi.
eng_translation: The dog looks very clean and is wearing something around it's neck

bem_transcription: Shitata alelisha icilimba ca nsaale.
eng_translation: The man playing a harp

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili cilemoneka nakalimo umukashana uuli kunuma yakwa shitata nao alemwafwako ukwimba pantu shitata alemoneka kwati aleimba nokwimba.
eng_translation: It's like the lady behind him I'd backing him because it looks like this man is singing too.

bem_transcription: Iyi incende ilemoneka yalifula sana abantu pantu abantu balepusana fye, umbi aleya ukulefuma umunankwe.
eng_translation: It looks like there are a lot of people in this place. They are just crossing each other.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona shitata wiminine panuma ifyo alemoneka?
eng_translation: Have you seen how the man standing behind is looking?

bem_transcription: Nimbona uyu shitata alemoneka tapooseleko amano kuli uyu uuleimba, cilemoneka kwati nakwata fye amatontonkanyo ayengi sana.
eng_translation: This man is not focussed on the one singing. It's like his mind is somewhere else.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo batatu balewamya umusebo.
eng_translation: Three young men are mantaining the road.

bem_transcription: Elyo bonse umo babelele nabafwala nefyakufwala ifyapalana.
eng_translation: They are all wearing the same clothes.

bem_transcription: Ee, ifyakuwala bafwele fyakubombelamo pantu nabakwata utumpompo utwakubacingilisha nga cakutila ilibwe lyaliponene elyo nabafwala ne nsapato ishakutila amakasa yabo yengacingililwa.
eng_translation: Yes these are worksuits. They are even wearing helmets to protect them from falling objects and safety shoes to protect their feet.

bem_transcription: Ico cishinka wasosa, elo bushe naumona ukuti nabakwata namashofolo?
eng_translation: You are right. Have you noticed that they also have shovels?

bem_transcription: Ee, nimbona, pantu eyo balebomfya ukuwamya umusebo kaili cilepala kwati uyu umusebo wakaena walilepauka sana.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen. They are using the shovels to repare the road which has a lot of potholes

bem_transcription: Umulumendo ni fundi pantu nakwata imfuti kuminwe.
eng_translation: This boy has a gun. Is he a poacher?

bem_transcription: Ca cine ni fundi, elo uyu nifundi wanama, pantu naikata ne coni muminwe ico epeye ne mfuti yakwe.
eng_translation: You are right he is a poacher because he even has a bird in his hands which he has killed with his gun.

bem_transcription: Elyo naumfwa bwino kumona fye fintu amwentwile pantu naishiba ukutila alaya atobele supu iyanama.
eng_translation: You can tell from his smile that he is very happy because today will be a good meal. There will be meat on the table today

bem_transcription: Elyo kuntu ali kulemoneka nikumpanga, nomba impanga yakaena yabusaka.
eng_translation: The place where he is seems to be a very clean forest.

bem_transcription: Iyi impanga balalimako namataba pantu nimbona kunuma uko kuntashi yakwe kulemoneka ifimuti fyamataba.
eng_translation: They also farm maize crop in this area because I can see some maize crops behind him.

bem_transcription: Imbwa iyabuuta ili pamenshi.
eng_translation: A white dog is in the water.

bem_transcription: Ilemoneka nakalimo ilefwaya ukutoloka amenshi.
eng_translation: It's like it wants to jump

bem_transcription: Apa yafika palemoneka nipakati ka menshi.
eng_translation: It's now in the middle of the water

bem_transcription: Elo kabili kunuma yaiko kuntu yacifuma kulemoneka nakalimo kwaliba akachuulu elyo kabili ukubikapofye nefimuti.
eng_translation: There seems to be a hill and trees from where it is coming from.

bem_transcription: Nomba lintu iletoloka naimya utumolu tonse tubili utwakunuma elyo utumolu twakuntashi kamo akekete fye mumenshi.
eng_translation: As it is jumping, both hind legs are in the air but one of the front legs is touching the water.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo abalekanalekana bali mucikuulwa cimo.
eng_translation: Different young men are in one building.

bem_transcription: Umu mucikuulwa bali cilemoneka nalimo emo babomba pantu bonse bafwele ifyapalana
eng_translation: It's like this is their workplace because they are wearing the same clothes.

bem_transcription: Nimbona, cishinka, bambi nabafwala amajaketi yakashika elyo bambi bafwele fye amashati ayakashika.
eng_translation: I have seen, it is true. Some are wearing red jackets and others are wearing red shirts.

bem_transcription: Mucikuulwa cakaena mulemoneka umwabusaka kumona fye panshi efyo palemoneka apa busaka.
eng_translation: The building looks very neat.

bem_transcription: Kuntashi yabo kuli umulumendo uulepita kuli ulu ulubali nakwena kuli umukashana nabantu fye bambi abalepita
eng_translation: There's a young man passing in front and a woman on the side with other people.

bem_transcription: Umwana umulumendo alekweleka kucibumba.
eng_translation: A young boy is climbing the wall.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Elyo uku kulepala kwati nikulya kuncende uko basambilisha fye abana ifyakunina impili elo necibumba.
eng_translation: This looks like it is where children learn how to climb walls and hills.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona fintu afwele umwana wakaena?
eng_translation: Have you seen what the very boy is wearing?

bem_transcription: Nimbona nafwala icimpompo pakutila nga cakuti alipusumwike apona umutwe teti utobeke.
eng_translation: I have seen he is even wearing a helmet so that in case he falls he doesn't break his head.

bem_transcription: Imbwa ili kululamba lwamumana ilengala.
eng_translation: A dog is playing on the seashore.

bem_transcription: Ululamba lwakamana ulwakaena kwalifula imicanga.
eng_translation: There's a lot of sand on this seashore.

bem_transcription: Temicanga fye kwalifula namatipa pantu ne mbwa ilemoneka iyafiko umulandu wamatipa.
eng_translation: Apart from sand there's also a lot of mud because even the dog looks dirty.

bem_transcription: Elyo imbwa yakaena ilemoneka nakalimo ilefwaya ukutoloka amenshi ayalepita.
eng_translation: It's like the dog wants to jump the on coming water.

bem_transcription: Baliisambilisha bwino sana ifyakutoloka kumona fye fintu itolweke bwino.
eng_translation: looking at how it's jumping you can tell that it has been well trained.

bem_transcription: Imbwa shibili shileangala mwilinga lyamawaya.
eng_translation: Two dogs are playing in a wire fence.

bem_transcription: Ninshi umushili ulemoneka uwabuuta buuta kuncende shili imbwa ishi?
eng_translation: Why does the ground look whitish where these dogs are playing?

bem_transcription: Iyi incende nakuponena na snow.
eng_translation: It was snowing.

bem_transcription: Ilinga lyawaya ili bushe yakucingilila imbwa ukukana fuma?
eng_translation: Is this wire fence to protect the dogs from coming out?

bem_transcription: Eya mwalungika, baleshicingilila ukukana fuma ukuya ukutali.
eng_translation: You are right. It is to protect them from coming out.

bem_transcription: Nyina ali nomwana wakwe namwimya.
eng_translation: A mother has raised her child.

eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Kunuma yabo kuli ne cikuulwa opo balenga akamuntu.

bem_transcription: Icikuulwa cakaena cilemoneka cakale pantu cilemoneka icafiko.
eng_translation: The building looks old because it is very dirty.

bem_transcription: Amakumbi mumuulu yalemoneka bwino sana elyo akasuba nakabalika.
eng_translation: The clouds look very beautiful and the sun is shining.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo ali pamusebo alenina pa ncinga.

bem_transcription: Elyo nafwala ne shati ilya makumbi makumbi ilemoneka kwati kachola apapile
eng_translation: He is wearing a blue shirt which is the same color as his bag.

bem_transcription: Elyo uku kumbali mumusebo ali kwaliba ne cibumba ca mbao.
eng_translation: Besides the road where he is standing on is a wood fence.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ifyo afwele kunshi?
eng_translation: Have you you seen what he is wearing?

bem_transcription: Ee nimbona,nafwala kaputula yafiita abikapo ne nsokoshi shabuuta kabili no lusapato lwafiita.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen. He is wearing black shorts, white socks and black shoes.

eng_translation: It looks like they are married because the lady is pecking the man on the cheeks.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili shitata wakaena alemoneka naumfwa bwino sana pantu alemoneka fye uwatekanya filya pameso.
eng_translation: The man looks very happy and very calm on the face.

bem_transcription: Nomba nga walolekesha uyu shitata cilepala kwati kuli ifyo alelolesha pantu amenso yakwe ne cinso cakwe cilolesha kumbi.
eng_translation: But when you look closely at him, it's like he is looking at something because hes face is focussed elsewhere.

bem_transcription: Ca cine nalimo kuli fiyo baletamba pantu nanamayo wine alemoneka kwati pali uko alelolesha uku kwine ukulelosha umulumendo elyo kabili ne ng'anda yabo ilemoneka iyabusaka.
eng_translation: Very true because it's like the woman is also watching something.  Their house looks neat too.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alimumuputule emo babikile amabaloni elo aleyaposha ukubomfya akamuti.
eng_translation: A boy is in a room full of balloons and is popping then with a stick.

bem_transcription: Elo cilemoneka kwati aya amabaluni bacilayabpmfya lintu bacilaangala pantu nayafula.
eng_translation: It's like they had a function because the balloons are just too many.

bem_transcription: Mukati yamuputule wine, balitantikamo ifibokoshi kabili necikopo umwakuposa ifiko.
eng_translation: There a boxes inside this room and a dust bin.

bem_transcription: Mwati naumona ukutila uyu umulumendo cilemoneka kwati tatemwa icongo cakupoleka kwamabaluni?
eng_translation: Have you noticed that it's like this young man doesn't like the sound of the popping balloons?

bem_transcription: Ca cine nimbona ati kwena muli nakamwenso pantu eminine akatalamukila pakuyatula amabaluni elo alebomfya nakamuti.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen that there's some fear in him because he is standing at a distance when popping them and he is using a stick.

bem_transcription: Banamayo babili nabafukama elo babili nabeminina nabekata nashitata,
eng_translation: Two women are kneeling down while two others are standing and are holding a man.

bem_transcription: Nomba cilepala kwati uku bali nikubwinga pantu aba babili abali panshi nabekata namaluba kuminwe elo shibwinga nuyu wine shitata uwiminine uo babikile pakati.
eng_translation: Its like this is a wedding ceremony because these two even have flowers in their hands. The groom is this very man that is standing in between these two women.

eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

eng_translation: Have you seen that the one on the groom's right hand side is looking like is the bride?

eng_translation: Have you seen how these ladies are looking?

bem_transcription: Ee nimbona, cilepala kwati kunuma yabo uku kuli uulebalandisha uo balelolesha.
eng_translation: Yes it's like there's someone behind them talking to them.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili nechola cakwe cilemoneka icafiitulukila kabili muminwe yakwe nakwata ico babomfya ukukopelako ifikope.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo aleangala icangalo icakushelemuka pakantu akakwata amawilo.
eng_translation: A young man is skateboarding.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilepala kwati alishibisha sana ici icangalo pantu nabomfya fye ukuulu kumo ukukemishe kulubali lumo.
eng_translation: He looks like a professional skateboarder as he is just using one one leg to left it on one end.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili napantu aleangalila palemoneka palitelela tekuti apona nokupona?
eng_translation: Where he is skateboarding from looks slipperly, will he not fall?

bem_transcription: Elyo nomba nga cakutila aliponene kuti aicena ububi, pantu pamushili pantu pakosa sana.
eng_translation: If he fell, he would hurt himself badly because the floor is very hard.

bem_transcription: Ca cine kuti aicena ububi nga aliponene nomba nangu cingabe fyo uyu muntu teti apone pantu kuntashi yakwe kuli utushimbi uko engekata.
eng_translation: It is true he might hurt himself badly. But he can't fall because there are some metals were he can hold onto.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alelisha umutolilo.
eng_translation: A young man is playing a flute.

bem_transcription: Uyu umulumendo cilemoneka kwati aliishibisha ukulisha umutolilo kumonafye fintu apompele amatobo nefyo awikete.
eng_translation: This young man looks like he really knows how to play the flute as we can see from the way he is blowing his cheeks and holding the flute.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona imishishi shakwe ifyo shatalimpa?
eng_translation: Have you seen how long his hair is?

bem_transcription: Ee nimbona, elo shalifiita bwino sana, nashisakula ukushitwala kunuma.
eng_translation: Yes and it's very black and we'll combed and taken behind.

eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Bashitata babili baletamba ukuwa kwakasuba kukamana.
eng_translation: Two men are watching the sunset.

bem_transcription: Bashitata bonse bali nefimuti kuminwe yabo, bushe ifimuti ifi finshi balefibomfesha?
eng_translation: They all have sticks in their hands. What are these sticks for?

bem_transcription: Fyakupansa inshila umo baleenda.
eng_translation: It's for clearing the path were they are passing.

bem_transcription: Ninshi bashitata bene balemonekela abafiituluka ifyakwebati tabalemoneka napamenso bwino bwino?
eng_translation: Why are these men not clearly visible on their faces?

bem_transcription: Ninshita yacungulo bushiku echo tabalemonekela.
eng_translation: It's because it is evening that is why we can't see them clearly.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo aleshana naima namumuulu.
eng_translation: A young man is dancing high in the air.

bem_transcription: Awe taleshana fye natoloka sana mumuulu aimya nokuboko kumo.
eng_translation: No he is not dancing. He has just jumped high with one hand up.

bem_transcription: Elo cilemoneka nakalimo aleumfwa fintu alecita pantu alemoneka uwansansa pamenso sana.
eng_translation: It's like he is enjoying what he is doing because he looks happy.

bem_transcription: Nomba nga walolesha kunuma yakwe bushe finshi ulemonako?
eng_translation: When you look behind him, what can you see?

bem_transcription: Kunuma yakwe kwena nga nalolekesha bwino ndemonako abantu abaleyendela fye kuli ifikuulwa ifitali kabili namalaiti yalesha imyotoka ukupita nangula ati abantu bapite.
eng_translation: When I look closely behind him I can see people walking. There are also tall buildings and traffic lights.

bem_transcription: Abakashana babili bali kuncende yakwangalilako baleangala.
eng_translation: Two ladies are in a play ground.

bem_transcription: Elo cilemoneka kwati uku nimukowa bele pantu balemoneka namenshi pamubili nemishishi shabo nashiboomba.
eng_translation: It looks like they have gone for swimming because their hair and bodies are wet.

bem_transcription: Bushe elyo naumona ati nabakwata nobwalwa kuminwe? Elo balemoneka abansansa nabomfwa bwino sana.
eng_translation: Have you noticed that they also have beer in their hands? They look very happy.

bem_transcription: Nimbona, cila muntu naimya ubwalwa kuminwe emulandu wine bacensele sana.
eng_translation: I have seen. Each wine has raised the beer in their hands and are smiling.

bem_transcription: Elyo kunuma yabo kuli nabantu nabambi, ndemona umulumendo wiminine akatalamukila nafwala neshati lyakatapakatapa.
eng_translation: There are other people behind them. I can see a young man in a green shirt.

bem_transcription: Namayo alimunshila, alelanda pali lamya.
eng_translation: A woman is walking in the road while talking on the phone.

bem_transcription: Elyo uyu wine namayo alinapabukulu naimya nakachola akafiita.
eng_translation: This woman is pregnant and is carrying a black bag.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati uyu umusebo balaubomfya sana abantu pantu abantu nabafulamo.
eng_translation: It is like this is a busy road because there are a lot of people in it.

bem_transcription: Kabili kunuma yakwe kwine balipangako nakansaka akakutushishamo nalimo nga kuli akasuba.
eng_translation: Behind him is a grass thatched house for resting when it is very sunny.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

eng_translation: This structure is well built with beautiful looking stones on the floor.

bem_transcription: Elyo tetumabwe tweka iyo, panse pene balibyalapo notumuti utwayemba nga nshi.
eng_translation: Apart from the stones, theve planted beautiful trees outside.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ukutila kuli naumbi uwikele panshi?
eng_translation: Have you noticed that there is another one sitting down?

bem_transcription: Ee nimbona, kuli naumbi uwikele panshi elo alemoneka mukashana kabili ukulubali kuli naumbi uwiminine uufwele itoloshi lyakatapakatapa.

eng_translation: This is a treadmill.

bem_transcription: Pali cimashini pene nabakanikapo netaulo lyabuuta.
eng_translation: There's a white towel on the treadmill.

bem_transcription: Elyo umu mulemoneka nimumuputule pantu kucibumba kuli necikope.
eng_translation: This looks like a room because there is even a picture on the wall.

bem_transcription: Icikope cakaena cintu cayemba nga nshi pantu cikope camaluba, utumaluba twakashikila filya kabili notwa katapakatapa.
eng_translation: It is a picture of red and green flowers. It is very pretty.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo naiminina nacensa nakukanwa.
eng_translation: A young man is standing with the mouth open.

bem_transcription: Elo uyu umulumendo ifyo alemoneka filesekesha, naluka notukuti apentako namacaala ayapusana pusana.
eng_translation: This young man has a funny look. He has braided his hair and painted the braids different colours.

bem_transcription: Elyo kwena nacimbi icilesekesha, nolubeyo abeyele nalo lwine lulesekesha apa ponse pantashi tapabe mishishi elo mumbali emwaba fye utumishishi natwena utwasonsomana.
eng_translation: The hair cut too is funny. There is no hair in the middle only on the sides of the head and it is kinky too.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Nimbona icampepo cilemoneka icatikama kabili icafiita cilemoneka kwati likoti.
eng_translation: I have seen. The jersey is thick and black it looks like a coat.

bem_transcription: Elyo nomba uyu wine shitata alisunga nemwemfu ishitali kabili ishabuuta elyo kabili cilemoneka nalimo bushiku ubu aleoca.
eng_translation: This man had kept long white beards and it's like he is welding in the night.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka umukashana no mulumendo baleenda, lubali lumbi balelanda pali lamya.
eng_translation: It is like a young man and a young woman are walking and on the other side they are talking on the phone.

bem_transcription: Umo shitata aleshitisha pakamtemba elo umo shitata uuli pantashi ena nakwata tumo uto alelya muka pakapepa.
eng_translation: One man is selling in a small shop and another man in front had something on a paper that he is eating.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati tuntu uyu shitata alelya tubalala bushe naumona?
eng_translation: It looks like this man is eating ground nuts have you seen?

bem_transcription: Ee nimbona kwena tubalala utu alelya, elo mumusebo wakaena mulemoneka nalimo cushi cushi filya nampo nga pali uuleoca mupepi.
eng_translation: Yes I have seen he is eating groundnuts. The road looks smoky it's like someone is burning something nearby.

bem_transcription: Abaice babili umulumendo nomukashana baleangala.
eng_translation: A young boy and a young girl are playing.

bem_transcription: Aba balemoneka nipacilupwa, pali indume ne nkashi.
eng_translation: It looks like this is a family. There is a brother and a sister.

bem_transcription: Ici icangalo baleangala cilemoneka nabacitemwa sana pantu bali abansansa, nga kakashana nakashibatako namenso.
eng_translation: It's like they are enjoying the game they are playing because they look happy. The girl has even closer her eyes.

bem_transcription: Elyo balemoneka kwati balitemwana sana pantu nabasekelela.
eng_translation: It seems they love each other because they look very happy.

bem_transcription: Elyo nga nalolesha imishishi shabo efyo shilemoneka awe shilondolola ati aba bena cishinka nipalupwa pantu nabakwata imishishi shapalana shonse shili ishabuuta.
eng_translation: You can tell that they are family because they both even have white hair.

bem_transcription: Umwaice umulumendo ali pacimpelwa icitali.
eng_translation: A young boy is on a long swing.

bem_transcription: Elyo nabamukakilila bwino sana pakutila tapusumwike nokupona.
eng_translation: He is safely tied so that he does not fall.

bem_transcription: Ici icimpelwa cakaena balicipanga bwino sana pantu nacikwata intambo ishingi esho bakakilila nalimo shakulenga abantu tabaponene.
eng_translation: This swing is good because it has belts that you can use to tie yourself with so that you don't fall.

bem_transcription: Nomba bushe naumona ifyo afwele uyu umwaice?
eng_translation: Have you noticed what this young is wearing?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Namayo alelya icakulya.
eng_translation: A woman is eating food.

bem_transcription: Apantu pekele umukashana uyu, bushe nindungama ukutila nipancende yakushitapo ifyakulya?
eng_translation: Is that a place where you can buy food where that young woman is sitting?

bem_transcription: Endita e, namulungama, pakushitila ifyakulya.
eng_translation: Yes, it is a food place.

bem_transcription: Ukulolesha imiliile ileliilamo umukashana alemoneka kwati ali nesala sana, bushe kuti caba efyo?
eng_translation: Looking at how the girl is eating, it's like she is very hungry.

bem_transcription: Ee, ali nsala icine cine, echo afililwe nokuyaikala kumbi aamba ukulila palya pene pancende.
eng_translation: Yes she is very hungry that is why she is even eating from right there.

bem_transcription: Bakapaso bali mucibansa nabeminina.
eng_translation: Body guards are standing in the ground.

bem_transcription: Nakabili muminwe yabo nabemya imfuti elyo bambi bemishe ifyapala imifwi.
eng_translation: They are holding guns in their hands and others are holding what look like spears.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Nomba bushe ifi ifyabulungana ifyo bemishe muminwe nifinshi?
eng_translation: What these round things they are lifting?

bem_transcription: Ishi bakwete ninkwela isho babomfya lintu bali pabulwi.
eng_translation: These are shields that they use in battle

bem_transcription: Abalumendo nabakashana bali mucibansa cafyangalo.
eng_translation: Young men and young women are in a play ground.

bem_transcription: Umu mucibansa nimulya bangalila icangalo cakushelemuka ne nsapato shamawilo.
eng_translation: In this ground is where they play roller skating.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona fintu bafwele abakashana bakaena nabalumendo?
eng_translation: Have you seen what these very young men and young women are wearing?

bem_transcription: Nimbona pantu cilemoneka kwati aba libumba limo nabafwala fimo fine ifyafiita ne nsapato shamawilo.
eng_translation: I have seen. It looks like they are on the same team because they are wearing black and roller shoes.

bem_transcription: Cacine libumba limo ili elo muibansa cine nakwisa nabantu bambi aba beshile fye mukutamba aba bakaleangala icangalo.
eng_translation: It is true this is one team. There are also other people in the ground who have come to watch them

bem_transcription: Abaice batatu bali panse baleangala.
eng_translation: Three children are playing outside.

bem_transcription: Uku kulemoneka kwati tepanse fye lelo nikumpanga kuntu baanika ifyani ifyauma.
eng_translation: This is not just outside but it is a place in the bush where they dry reeds.

bem_transcription: Elo kabili ukwangala baleangala aba bana beleangasha ifyani balefipoosa mumuulu, nga nikamo nakanina napamupili wafyani.
eng_translation: They are playing with the Reed. One has even climbed on top of a reed bunch.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ukutila kuli ifyani ifyo balongele kwati mumiseke?
eng_translation: Have you seen that there are reeds that have been put in buskets?

bem_transcription: Ca cine nimbona pantu nga walolekesha bwino, ishi miseke elo balongamo ifyani elo abana babili baninapo pamuulu wamiseke.
eng_translation: Yes it is true I have seen. These baskets have been packed with reed and the children are on top of the Reed.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo nomukashana baleimba.
eng_translation: A young man and a young woman are singing.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka kwati baleumfwa bwino ulwimbo luntu baleimba pantu nabashibata nokushibata pakwimba.
eng_translation: It seems like they are enjoying the song that they are singing as they have even closed their eyes.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo wakaena aliteeka ne mwemfu kabili nafwala ne shati lyafiita.
eng_translation: The young man has a beard and is wearing a black shirt.

bem_transcription: Nomukashana nankwe nafwala icafiita kumuulu elyo nabikako namagalashi.
eng_translation: They young lady is also wearing a black top and is wearing glasses.

bem_transcription: Elo muntu baleimbila umu mulemoneka nimumuputule, nomba icikope cakaena ici tacilemwenekesha, umulumendo ena alemwenekesha nomba umukashana ena pamenso tapalemoneka.
eng_translation: It's like they are in a room. The young man is visible but the young womans face cannot be seen clearly.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo balesunka icibaala apo balongele amasaka namakontena.
eng_translation: Young men are pushing a wheelbarrow which has sacks and containers.

bem_transcription: Elo aya amasaka yalemoneka masaka yabuunga neefikontena muli saladi.
eng_translation: These are sacks of mealie meal and the containers have cooking oil.

bem_transcription: Elyo filemoneka nafifina pantu nabafulilapo namashati pakusunka.
eng_translation: It seems they are heavy as the one pushing has even removed his shirt.

bem_transcription: Elo uku kulemoneka nikumaliketi pantu abantu nabafulako.
eng_translation: This place seems like it's a market because there are a lot of people.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka kwati umu nimumbali yamusebo pantu nabanru balepita.
eng_translation: It seems like this is along the road because people are passing.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Nomba bushe naumona ifyo shitata alemoneka pamenso?
eng_translation: Have you seen how the man is looking on the face?

bem_transcription: Nimbona, aleimba, nomba icilepapusha cakwebati alemoneka kwati nalimo alefwaya ukulila.
eng_translation: Yes he is singing but he is looking like he is crying.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Elyo uyu wine shitata naikala panshi kuli fimo ifyo alepanga, nomba bushe naumona ifyo afwele?
eng_translation: This same man is sitting down making something. Have you seen how he is dressed?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Nomba umulandu afwalile ifi mulandu wakuti fintu alepanga nafikwata ulukungu lelo talefwaya ulukungu lwingile mumona
eng_translation: He is dressed like this because what he is working with has dust and he does not want to inhale the dust.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Amenshi yakaena yalemoneka nimupepi pantu napeteka netoloshi, cilemoneka kwati yalefika fye mumakufi.
eng_translation: The water seems not to be deep. He has folded his trousers and the water is only reaching the knees

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Nomba icilempapusha cakutila aleangalila mumenshi lelo akachola acili nakapapa elo alemoneka uwasekelela.
eng_translation: What is surprising is he is playing in the water and still the bag on his back and he looks happy.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Bakateya bamupila balimucibansa bateya umupila.
eng_translation: Football players are in the pitch

bem_transcription: Elo aya amabumba yabili ifibapusenye fyakufwala bafwele bambi bafwele ifyakashika elo bambi bafwele ifyabuuta.
eng_translation: What's differentiating the two teams is the color of the jerseys. One team is in red and the other is in white.

bem_transcription: Elo babili bakateya nabema mumuulu balefwaya ukupanta umupila.
eng_translation: Two players are in the air wanting to kick the ball.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ifyo icibansa ciiswile?
eng_translation: have you seen how full the stadium is ?

bem_transcription: Ala nimbona naciisula nga nshi elo abafulile nibalya abafwele ifyakashika.
eng_translation: I can see that it is full and that the majority is in red.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo bane nabekala panse yakucikuulwa.
eng_translation: Four young men seated outside the building.

bem_transcription: Nomba bonse aba cila muntu nakwata ifyapusana ifyo alecita, bushe naumona?
eng_translation: Each one is doing something different from the other have you noticed?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING
