bem_transcription: Elyo apa palemoneka nipanse yacalici pantu pali ne cipampa epo balembele ukutila licalici.
eng_translation: This looks like outside a church because there is a post which is saying Church.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING .

bem_transcription: Umuntu alimumuulu na parashuti.
eng_translation: A person in the air with a parachute.

bem_transcription: Yanshi iyi ine parashuti?
eng_translation: What is the parachute for?

bem_transcription: Iyi parashuti baibomfya nga watoloka mucintu caciba mumuulu icapala ne ndeke.
eng_translation: It is used when you jump off something that is in the air. For example when you jump from a plain.

bem_transcription: Ngeci icilemoneka icabutulukila futii cafiitulukila bushe nacena cili kuli parachute nangu naciibela fye palwaciko
eng_translation: What about that thing that is looking whitish and blackish at the same time. Is it also part of the parachute?

bem_transcription: Coni cilepupuka mumuulu.
eng_translation: That is a bird flying.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Apa palemoneka nipacipooma ca menshi pantu amenshi yalemuponena elo nayamufimba nokumufimba.
eng_translation: This looks like a water falls because water is falling on him and covering him.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka ali ne nsansa naimya namaboko mumuulu nakalimo nacimfya.
eng_translation: It looks like he is happy and is raising the hands. Maybe he had won.

bem_transcription: Akabwato kanoono sana kabili kalemoneka akakashika, umuntu nga taishiba ukowa kuti abuunda
eng_translation: The boat is small and red in color. One can drown if one doesn't know how to swim.

bem_transcription: Ca cine kuti abuunda, nomba uyu nakwata akamuti ako engabomfya pakwebati tabuundile.
eng_translation: True he can drown, but this one has a stock he can use so he doesn't drown.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo nanina pali kabalwe aleangala.
eng_translation: A young man is on a donkey playing.

bem_transcription: Elo cilepala kwati nakwata ne ntambo intu aleangasha icilengele abantu balemutamba.
eng_translation: He even has a rope that he is playing with that is why people are watching him.

bem_transcription: Abantu bakaena beshile mukutamba ici icangalo nabafula nakalimo balicitemwa ici icangalo bambi nabakwata namabaluni.
eng_translation: It's like people like this game because many have come to watch and they even have balloons.

bem_transcription: Nakabili cilemoneka akasuba nakabalika sana pantu, pantu bekele nipakasuba tapali nencitelelwe.
eng_translation: It looks like the sun is brazing because there is no shade where they are sitting.

bem_transcription: Ico cishinka elyo kabili kunuma yabantu bene abekele abeshile mukutamba kuli necikuulwa icitali icabuuta.
eng_translation: Very true and behind these people that have come to watch is a tall building.

bem_transcription: Abana abakashana nabaninina pafimuti balepeluka.
eng_translation: Little girls are swinging on a tree.

bem_transcription: Elyo nga nuyu uuli kuntashi ena alemoneka naumfwa ulunshingwa kumona fye fintu ekatishe intambo.
eng_translation: The one in front looks like she's feeling dizzy that's why she's holding the rope tightly.

bem_transcription: Elyo futi nakabili uyu wine uuli kuntashi natemwa alemoneka natemwa kumonafye fintu acensele kukanwa ati naumfwa bwino ukupeluka.
eng_translation: The same one in front looks very happy as can be seen from the smile as she is swinging.

bem_transcription: Elyo umuulu ulemoneka bwino sana cilepala kwati yakuli nakasuba.
eng_translation: The sky's look good. It's like there is no sun even.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka kwati ili baninine pafimpelwa pali uulebasunka pantu ndemona ukuboko uko nakupitilila nangula tatulemona icinso.
eng_translation: It's like someone is pushing them as they are swinging because I can see a hand there even though I can't see the face.

bem_transcription: Bashitata babili nabeminina umo alelisha umutolilo elo umbi alelisha icilimba ca nsaale.
eng_translation: Two men are standing. One is playing the flute and the other is playing the harp.

bem_transcription: Elyo aba bashitata bacikulile nangula bakote pantu bonse nabakwata imfwi nangula imishishi ishabuuta.
eng_translation: These men are elderly because they both have grey hair.

bem_transcription: Elyo nakabili kuli shitata naumbi uwikele kunuma ya aba babili abeminine naikalako pakapuna.
eng_translation: There's also a man behind these two who is sitting.

bem_transcription: Nomba alo tulande nomba pafwakufwala fintu bafwele, bushe filemoneka shani?
eng_translation: Let's come to their clothing. How are they looking?

bem_transcription: Ifyakufwala bafwele filemoneka ifyabusaka elyo kabili bonse nababikapo notusote.
eng_translation: The clothes look very neat and they all are wearing hats.

bem_transcription: Namayo naiminina naiminina napapa nakachola.
eng_translation: A woman is standing and has a bag on her back.

bem_transcription: Nakabili muminwe yakwe nakwata fwaka intu abikile kukanwa.
eng_translation: She has a cigarette in her hands which she's put in her mouth.

bem_transcription: Uyu namayo wakaena alemoneka nalimo aciiminina pakwebati bamukope icikope.
eng_translation: It looks like this woman posed for a photo.

bem_transcription: Nangu alepeepa nakabili uyu namayo mukote fwaka kuti yamwipaya.
eng_translation: Even though she is smoking, this cigarette can kill her because she is old.

bem_transcription: Ca cine uyu namayo kwena mukote, pantu kumonafye napamenso ifyo palemoneka kwena nakwata ne nkanshi.
eng_translation: Yes this woman is old because she even has wrinkles on her face.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alimucibansa ico bangalilamo amangalo.
eng_translation: A young man is in a play ground.

bem_transcription: Uyu wine umulumendo aleteya icangalo beta ukutila tennis.
eng_translation: The same young man is playing tennis.

bem_transcription: Mucibansa cakaena kwena tamulemoneka umuntu nangu umo nakalimo alifye eka.
eng_translation: There doesn't seem to be anyone in the play ground. He might be alone.

bem_transcription: Cimbi cakutila mucibansa umu mwalifula umucanga pantu napantu aleumina ici icangalo nipamucanga.
eng_translation: There's a lot of sand in this play ground.

bem_transcription: Elo uyu umulumendo nafwala nefyakuteyelamo ici cangalo, ifi ifyakufwala afwele fintu fyabuuta ukwambila kumutwe ukufika fye kuli kaputula.
eng_translation: He is even wearing the correct attire for the sport. Everything he is wearing is white.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo nomukashana nabeminina pambali ya ngangi nabaikumbata.
eng_translation: A young man and a young woman are standing besides the rail line and are hugging.

bem_transcription: Elyo lolekesha tekuikumbata fye kweka, baletomonana.
eng_translation: Look closely, they are not just hugging but also kissing.

bem_transcription: Ca cine niwe walanda, elo umulumendo napusha nokuboko mumusana wamwanakashi.
eng_translation: You are right. The young man has even placed his hand on the girls waist.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka kwati apa bali nipacitesheni ceshitima.
eng_translation: It looks like they are standing on the train station.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Abantu nabekala kumbali yamumana.
eng_translation: People are sitting on the river bank.

bem_transcription: Elyo apa nipamabwe yantu bakula ukushunguluka umumana bambi bekele fye
eng_translation: They are sitting on the rocks that have been built around the river.

bem_transcription: Kumbali yamumana balikulapo nefikuulwa ifitali nafyo ifingi.
eng_translation: There are even a number of long buildings along the river banks.

bem_transcription: Ifi ifikuulwa filemoneka kwati mayanda pantu balifikulwa bwino sana.
eng_translation: These buildings look like houses because they are well built.

bem_transcription: Elo umumana wakaena ulemoneka uwabusaka elo ukulu nga nshi.
eng_translation: The river looks big and clean.

bem_transcription: Namayo naikata icikope apali abana batatu
eng_translation: A woman is holding a picture where there are three children.

bem_transcription: Elyo alemoneka uwansansa sana nafwala namagalashi.
eng_translation: She looks very happy and is wearing glasses.

bem_transcription: Elo uku ali kulemoneka nikumanda pantu kunuma ifiliko nimanda balibikapo namaluba.
eng_translation: it's like she's at a graveyard because there are graves behind with flowers on top.

bem_transcription: Elo icikope cintu ekete muminwe cilelanga umukashana umwaice umo notubalumendo tubili utuli mumbali yakwe natumwikatilila.
eng_translation: The picture she is holding shows a young girl with two young boys on her sides holding her.

bem_transcription: Iyi ine imanda yakaena yalipalamina mupepi fye nefikuulwa ifyo bakula bwino nga nshi.
eng_translation: This grave yard is near very well built buildings.

bem_transcription: Abantu nabekela mucibansa.
eng_translation: People are sitting in a ground.

bem_transcription: Elyo lkuli ifyo baletamba pantu bonse amenso yabo batontele kuntashi.
eng_translation: They are watching something because there eyes are focussed in front.

bem_transcription: Nomba cilemoneka nakalimo fintu baletamba tafiweme pantu tabalemoneka abansansa pamenso awe.
eng_translation: They don't seem to be enjoying what they are watching because no one looks happy.

bem_transcription: Nga niyu shitata uukwete imwemfu shamfwi kabili ishitali alemoneka fye uwafulwa pamenso.
eng_translation: If it's this man with long grey beards, he even looks angry.

bem_transcription: Elo namayo nao uumupalamine naowine pamenso tatemenwe naikata muminwe umwamfuli.
eng_translation: The woman next to him is equally not happy and is holding an umbrella.

bem_transcription: Imbwa ilebutuka ne cidoli mukanwa.
eng_translation: A dog is running with a doll in its mouth.

bem_transcription: Icidoli ici bushe cidoli cakwangashe imbwa nangu cakwangasha abantu?
eng_translation: Is this doll for humans or for dogs?

bem_transcription: Ici icidoli cakwangasha imbwa elo shilomfwa bwino nga shilesuma sumamo pantu calinaka naka.
eng_translation: It is for dogs and they feel good bitting it because it is soft.

bem_transcription: So ninshi abaciipela imbwa ici icidoli muntu umwine wambwa?
eng_translation: So the owner of the dog is the one who gave it the doll?

bem_transcription: Endita e, umwine wambwa ewaciiposele ukuti ileangasha.
eng_translation: Yes the owner of the dog gave it the doll to be playing with.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alepeepa fwaka.
eng_translation: An old man is smoking a cigarette.

bem_transcription: Nakaka ne nkanshi alemoneka nafulwa bushe nibani alesonta?
eng_translation: He even has a frown on his face and is sad. Who is he pointing at?

bem_transcription: Umu muncende mulemoneka kwati nimucikuulwa cabwalwa alesonta uuleshitisha ubwalwa alekokola ukumupeela.
eng_translation: This looks like a bar. He is pointing at the bar tender because he is taking long to serve him.

bem_transcription: Shikulubantu alemoneka tali eka kuli naumbi uulemoneka uwikele mupepi nankwe bushe kuti aba ninani?
eng_translation: The old man doesn't seem to be alone. There seems to be another one seated near him. Who could it be?

bem_transcription: Ukulingana nakukumona imiloleseshe shamukashana ulemulolesha kuti mwamona ukuti ninamayo wakwe beshile nankwe.
eng_translation: By the way this woman is looking at him, we can tell it's his woman.

bem_transcription: Umukashana aleangala icangalo icakuposa utumupila utunoono mumuulu.
eng_translation: A young woman is juggling.

bem_transcription: Elyo aleposa utu utumupila tonse tutatu mumuulu nokutwankila pamo.
eng_translation: She is throwing three balls in the air and catching them all at once on their way back.

bem_transcription: Elyo kuntu ali uku kuntu kwayemba nga nshi kulemoneka ukwabusaka.
eng_translation: The place where she is looks clean.

bem_transcription: Iyi incende yakutushishapo fye pantu kuli nabalemutamba abekele munshi yacimuti.
eng_translation: This looks like a park because there are even some people watching her that are seated under  a tree.

bem_transcription: Ca cine pantu nimbona naumbi umulumendo naiminina akatalamukila nafwala necakatapakatapa.
eng_translation: True because I have seen another young man standing at a distance and is wearing something green.

bem_transcription: Shitata ali panse aleisambilisha ifyakulwa.
eng_translation: A man is outside training how to fight.

bem_transcription: Uyu shitata aliina alikwata nolufumo ulukalambako panoono nakabili alisebeka ne pala.
eng_translation: This man is fat, with a pot belly and a partly bald head.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona fintu afwele shitata wakaena?
eng_translation: Have you seen what the same man is wearing?

bem_transcription: Nimbona fintu afwele. afwelefye kaputula afwala namakapa kumakasa.
eng_translation: I have seen he is only wearing a short and some tropicals.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Abalumendo babili nabeminina tabafwele namashati elyo kabili naumbi naiminina nao nashintilila napa ncinga.
eng_translation: Two young men are standing without wearing shirts while another is standing and leaning on a bicycle.

bem_transcription: Kumbali yabo nakwena kumoneka nikumusebo pantu kulemoneka abantu babili abaninine pamacinga balecofa balepita.
eng_translation: There seems to be a road besides them because there are people and others are passing ridding their bicycles.

bem_transcription: Umbi pali aba babili abeminine ukwabula ukufwala amashati naikata namumushana elo alemoneka ukutila nakalimo acilabutuka.
eng_translation: One of these shirtless young men is holding his waist and it looks like he was running.

bem_transcription: Iyi incende ilemoneka bwino sana nakabili mumbali muli nefimuti ifikalamba.
eng_translation: This place looks very nice and had big trees in the ends.

bem_transcription: Incende yakaena nakabili balikulilapo nakapuna akakwilapo apa pakweba uuli onse ulefwaya ukuyatuusha kuti ayatuushako fye nga anaka.
eng_translation: They have even put a seat on the place to take a rest when you feel tired.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo batatu bali kucibansa balebomba.
eng_translation: Three young men are working at the play ground.

bem_transcription: Uku kulemoneka kwati nikupaka ukwakwangalila pantu pakatinabakulapo icashinguluka epo baleitilapo umucanga.
eng_translation: This looks like a park because they have even builtna round thing in the middle where they are pouring sand.

bem_transcription: Aba abalumendo bakaeana bonse nga twabalolesha nabafwala namashati ayapalana.
eng_translation: If we look at them, they three young men are even earing similar shirts.

bem_transcription: Aba bantu balemoneka kwati nabanaka sana pantu balebomfya amabala pakwitila umucanga.
eng_translation: These people seem tired as they are using wheel barrows to pour the sand.

bem_transcription: Elo pantu baleitila umucanga palemoneka pakwangalila pantu uku lubali balipangilako ne cimpelwa.
eng_translation: It seems the place where they are pouring sand is for playing because there is even a swing.

bem_transcription: Namayo naikalako panshi alebila icakunyatilapo amakasa pakwingila mung'anda.
eng_translation: A woman is sitting  down kneeting a door mat.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilepala kwati alishibisha ukubomba uyu wine umulimo.
eng_translation: It looks like she knows this job well.

bem_transcription: Uyu namayo cilemoneka nakalimo alomfwa bwino ukubomba uyu umulimo pantu pa menso alemoneka nakalimo naumfwa bwino.
eng_translation: It looks like she enjoys this work as the joy can even be seen in her eyes.

bem_transcription: Elyo nakabili, namayo alikwata imishishi ishafiita bwino kabili ishitali sana.
eng_translation: This woman has black beautiful long hair.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili nafwala nelaya ilyakashika mwapita nefyamakumbi makumbi.
eng_translation: She is wearing a red dress with patches of green

bem_transcription: Umwana umukashana naiminina kumbali yamumana.
eng_translation: A girl child is standing on the river banks.

bem_transcription: Uyu umumana ulemoneka uukalamba sana kabili uwalengama.
eng_translation: The river looks very big and clear.

bem_transcription: Kabili kumbali yamumana kwine kwalifula amabwe pantu utumabwe tuliko twingi elo tunoono tunoono.
eng_translation: there are many small rocks in the river bank.

bem_transcription: Emulandu wine afwalile insapato pakutila utu utumabwe twimucena mumakasa.
eng_translation: That is why she is wearing shoes so that the stones do not hurt her.

bem_transcription: Elo akamwana kakaena kalikwata imishishi ishitali.
eng_translation: The girl has long hair.

bem_transcription: Shitata naikala pakapuna ali mwituuka lyansapato naikata ulusapato.
eng_translation: A man is seated on a chair in a shoes shop holding a shoe.

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati uyu shitata mulema teti akumanishe ukuyendela emulandu wine alebomfesha aka kamashini akapalile kwati cipuna.
eng_translation: It looks like the man is crippled that is why he is seated in this electronic wheel chair.

bem_transcription: Umu mwituuka ali eshile mukushita insapato nomba teshibe luntu alashita pantu alelosha napali lumbi kabili naikata lumbi kuminwe.
eng_translation: He has come to buy she's in this shop but doesn't look decided on which one he will buy because he is holding one type and looking at another type.

bem_transcription: Shitata wine nakabili nafwala necisote icikalamba kwati nicilya bakemba bafwala.
eng_translation: The man is also wearing a very large hat like those musicians wear.

bem_transcription: Kabili kunuma yakwe kuli naumbi shitata nakalimo aleshita insapato.
eng_translation: There's another man behind him. Maybe he is buying shoes.

bem_transcription: Banamayo babili nabafwala ifitambala fyabuuta kabili namashati yafiita balemoneka nalimo nibakatolika
eng_translation: Two women are wearing white head coverings and black shirts. They look like they are Catholics.

bem_transcription: Nomba bonse babili balelolesha pali lamya cilepala kwati kuli ifyo bapokelela ifyabulanda.
eng_translation: They both are looking at a phone and it's like they have recieved bad news.

bem_transcription: Ca cine pantu pamenso palemoneka ababulanda, nga nuyu uuli uku kulubali namayo ena cilemoneka ena eocipapwishe nasana.
eng_translation: Very true because both are looking sad. One of them looks sadder than the other though.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona ukutila bonse babili kuli ifyo bemishe?
eng_translation: Have you seen that both of them are lifting something?

bem_transcription: Nimbona, bonse babili nabemya utufyola utwafiita elyo uyu namayo uwikete lamya ena nafwala nacolona yakuminwe.
eng_translation: I have seen. Both of them are lifting black bags and the other woman who is holding the phone is even wearing a rosary.

bem_transcription: Shitata nanamayo balebutuka pakati ya musebo.
eng_translation: A man and a woman are running in the middle of the road.

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati uko balefuma kuli ubusanso ubukalamba pantu nakuntashi yabo kuli uulebutuka.
eng_translation: It's like there's a huge accident where they are coming from because there is another person running in front of them.

bem_transcription: Kabili kumbali yabo mumusebo mulepita namotoka iikalamba.
eng_translation: There is a big vehicle passing on their side in the road.

bem_transcription: Iyi motoka ilepala kwati nimotoka kwati nimotoka bashilika cilepala kwati eo balebutuka.
eng_translation: This vehicle looks like it is for the soldiers and it's like they are running away from them.

bem_transcription: Ca cine pantu nga nalolekesha ndemona kulya kumbali yamusebo kuli umushilika umo napona kabili kuli uulemwafwa nalimo kuli inkondo.
eng_translation: Very true. Because when I look closely on the side of the road there's a soldier down and someone is helping him up. Its like there is a war.

bem_transcription: Abaice abalumendo babili baleangala pakati kamusebo.
eng_translation: Two young boys are playing in the middle of the road.

bem_transcription: Elyo balemoneka abansansa sana elo nacintu balebomfya pakwangala nikamotoka akanoono,
eng_translation: They look happy playing with a small car.

bem_transcription: Kumbali yamusebo kuli abalumendo abalebatamba abakuluko umo ali napacinga.
eng_translation: There are two older boys on the roadside that watching them play. One of them is on a bicycle.

bem_transcription: Elyo nga walolekesha nakabili kulya kunuma kulemoneka amamotoka yantu beminike
eng_translation: When you look closely behind them there are vehicles that have been stopped.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu nabekala balelya ifyakulya.
eng_translation: A group of people is seating and eating a meal.

bem_transcription: Ibumba ili lilemoneka ulwapalana, bushe kuti lwaba lupwa lumo ulwile mukulya ifyakulya?
eng_translation: They look alike. Could they be one family that has gone to have a meal?

bem_transcription: Endita lupwa naluya fye mukulya ifyakulya.
eng_translation: Yes it is a family that has gone to have a meal.

bem_transcription: Ici icibili cileaka, bushe epo bacilaipikila ifyakulya balelya?
eng_translation: could they have cooked the food from this burning fire?

bem_transcription: Endita e, epo bacilaocela ifyakulya.
eng_translation: Yes. they were roasting the food from there.

bem_transcription: Akabwa kali mumenshi kaleangala.
eng_translation: A dog is playing in the water.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilepala kwati umu kali mumenshi muntu umo imbwa ishingi shilecimfyanya mukowa.
eng_translation: it's like many dogs are competing in these waters it is in.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka nalimo kuli abantu abeshile mukutamba pantu kunuma yambwa ndemonako amakasa nangula shilemona icinso.
eng_translation: It is like there are people that have come to watch because I can see human legs behind the dogs even though I cannot see the face.

bem_transcription: Iyi imbwa cilemoneka kwati baliisambilisha bwino sana oantu ilesamba bwino mumenshi.
eng_translation: It's like this dog has been well trained because it is swimming well.

bem_transcription: Iyi imbwa nakaeana intu yayemba na pantu intu yafiita kabili mwapita nefya buuta.
eng_translation: This dog is pretty because it is black with white stripes.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo babili balipanse balenwa ubwalwa.
eng_translation: Two young men are outside drinking beer.

bem_transcription: Nomba bonse babili balemoneka abafulwa nabakaka inkanshi lintu balenwa ubwalwa.
eng_translation: They both look angry and with frowns on their faces as they are drinking.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka nakalimo ubwalwa balenwa nabulula eicho tababutemenwe nakalya iyo.
eng_translation: It's like the bear they are drinking is bitter and so they are nit enjoying it.

bem_transcription: Kunuma yabo kuli nomukashana nankwe cilemoneka kwati alenwako.
eng_translation: Behind them is a woman who looks like she is also drinking.

bem_transcription: Bushe mukashana fye eka? Cilemoneka nalimo kuli fye na bantu nabambi nangula moolu fye yabo yalemoneka pamenso tabalemoneka.
eng_translation: It is not just the girl. It seems there are also other people aswell even though we can only see the legs and not the faces.

bem_transcription: Shitata alimumuputule naimya namaboko mumuulu nakalimo pali ifyo alelondolola.
eng_translation: A man is in a room and is raising his hands. He looks like he is explaining something.

bem_transcription: Elyo nafwala bwino sana pantu nafwala ijaketi ilyafiita.
eng_translation: He is well dressed because he has a black jacket on.

bem_transcription: Uyu shitata wakaena mukote sana pantu alikwata ne mfwi.
eng_translation: This man is very old because he has grey hair.

bem_transcription: Cimbi naco cakutila tamwenesha emulandu wine afwalile amagalashi.
eng_translation: Additionally he has poor eye sight that is why he is wearing spectacles.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili icakulundapo fye mumuputule ali mulemoneka mwabusaka pantu icibumba cili fye icabuuta.
eng_translation: Further the room where he is in looks neat because the wall is white.

bem_transcription: Shitata ali pamenshi aleangala icangalo cakucimfyanya ukusamba.
eng_translation: A man is in the water in a swimming competition.

bem_transcription: Elyo tali eka, kuli bambi abanankwe abengile kale mumenshi abashilemoneka.
eng_translation: And he is not alone. There are others that are in the water that we can't see.

bem_transcription: Shitata wakaena nga twamulolekesha bwino nafwala amagalashi ayamakumbi makumbi.
eng_translation: When we look closely at the man he is wearing blue glasses.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilepala kwati alefwaya ukucimfya emulandu wine abikileko amano.
eng_translation: This man is focussed because he wants to win.

bem_transcription: Elo amenshi yakaena yalemoneka yabusaka pantu tamuli ifiko nangu fimo awe nakalya iyo.
eng_translation: The water looks clean because there is no any visible dirt.

bem_transcription: Shitata ali pamuulu walupili alefwala itoloshi.
eng_translation: A man is on top of the mountain putting on his trousers.

bem_transcription: Elyo nakabili mumbali yalupili mulemoneka mwashinguluka amayanda.
eng_translation: They are houses around the mountain.

bem_transcription: Kuli lupilil lwakaena uku ali kulemoneka ifyani fyonse fyalyuma notumuti tonse twalyuma.
eng_translation: This mountain is full of dry grass and trees.

bem_transcription: Nomba bushe naumona fintu afwele kumuulu?
eng_translation: Have you noticed what he is wearing on top?

bem_transcription: Nimbona, nafwala ishati lyabuuta kabili nakaputula afwele ine naibuuta.
eng_translation: Yes, I have, he is wearing a shirt as white as his pants.

bem_transcription: Banamayo nabeminina pamo balelya ifyakulya.
eng_translation: Some women are standing together and enjoying a meal.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilemoneka kwati kuntu bali uku kuli icangalo cimo cintu beshile mukutamba.
eng_translation: If seems this place has something exciting that they are here to watch

bem_transcription: Ca cine pantu uyu namayo uuli pakati ena nafwala kumutwe akatambala akapitilemo ifyakashika kabili nefyabuuta neshati afwele lintu lyakashika.
eng_translation: That's true because the lady on the middle is wearing a red and white bandana with a red shirt.

bem_transcription: Elo cilepala kwati ifyakulya fintu balelya nafiwama sana pantu balemoneka abasekelela.
eng_translation: And it seems the food they are eating is very delicious, they seem so happy.

bem_transcription: Kunuma yabo nabakulako nakantemba, nalimo mwakutuushisha.
eng_translation: There's a shop behind them, I'm sure it's a resting place.

bem_transcription: Namayo nabashitata babili bali panse balelolesha ubwalwa buntu baleshitisha.
eng_translation: A lady and a man are outside watching over the beer they are selling.

bem_transcription: Ubu ubwalwa bulemoneka busuma sana kabili bwalikwata umutengo.
eng_translation: It seems like very nice beer and also expensive beer.

bem_transcription: Kunuma yabo kuli nabantu fye bambi abaleipitila.
eng_translation: They are some people behind them that are headed their own different directions.

bem_transcription: Cilepala kwati uku nikumaliketi pantu kuli utumantemba utwingi tuntu bakuula.
eng_translation: This place looks like a market because they are many shops around.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili tetuntemba fye tweka iyo kuli necikuulwa cimo icitali icabuuta.
eng_translation: They are not only shops but also buildings with one storey white one.

bem_transcription: Bashitata babili nanamayo bali mumuputule wakwipikilamo.
eng_translation: Two men and a woman are inside a kitchen.

bem_transcription: Bashitata babili ebali kucitofu baleipika ifyakulya.
eng_translation: The men are the ones manning the stove.

bem_transcription: Elyo namayo ena naiminina alecensha nalimo kuli uulemukopa icikope.
eng_translation: The lady is smiling as she stands, maybe she is taking a picture.

bem_transcription: Kunuma yabo kuli nomukate uwingi sana.
eng_translation: There is lots of bread behind them.

bem_transcription: Imikate shili mumuputule wakaena nashifula nalimo balapangile limo.
eng_translation: There's a lot of bread in the room. Maybe they just make I'm advance.

bem_transcription: Namayo uuli pabukulu naikala aletukusha umubili.
eng_translation: A pregnant woman is exercising.

bem_transcription: Elyo cilepala kwati naumfwa bwino pantu alemoneka uwansansa.
eng_translation: it's like she is enjoying because she looks happy.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona fintu afwele namayo wakaena?
eng_translation: Have you seen what the same lady is wearing?

bem_transcription: Nimbona, nafwala itoloshi ilikalamba nakashati akanoono.
eng_translation: I have seen. She is wearing a huge trousers and a small shirt.

bem_transcription: Elyo kabili mumuputule ali mulemoneka mwabusaka pantu necibumba fye cili icabuuta.
eng_translation: The room where she is looks clean because the wall is white.

bem_transcription: Shitata uwaina nga nshi nanina pali kamotoka kamawilo yabili.
eng_translation: A fat man is on a two wheeled car.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka wabung'ani tatemwa ukwenda namoolu emulandu wine alebomfesha aka kamotoka akakumwensha fye.
eng_translation: He looks lazy and doesn't like walking that is why he just wants to be driving.

bem_transcription: Bushe naumona fintu afwele shitata wakaena?
eng_translation: Have you seen what the same man is wearing?

bem_transcription: Nimbona nafwala icakufwala icatemwa ukufwala abacaice.
eng_translation: I have seen. He is wearing what kids love to wear.

bem_transcription: Elo incende aliko ilemoneka nincende yabusaka pantu takuli ifiko nangu fimo iyo.
eng_translation: And the place where he is looks very neat because there are no any litter around.

bem_transcription: Umwaume aletumbika munshila aleenda.
eng_translation: A man is tacking as he is walking in the road.

bem_transcription: Icikuulwa cili kunuma yakwe, bushe kuti caba cikuulwa cakwikalamo abantu?
eng_translation: Could that building behind him be for people to live in?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, cikuulwa camakwebo.
eng_translation: No. it is a building for business.

bem_transcription: Ici afwele icafiita, bushe cilikoti?
eng_translation: Is this black thing he is wearing a coat?

bem_transcription: Endita e, nafwala ikoti.
eng_translation: Yes he is wearing a coat.

bem_transcription: Shitata naikala pakapuna aleimba.
eng_translation: A man is sitting on a chair singing.

bem_transcription: Nomba cipalile kwati talatampa ukwimba pantu alesonta pacipepala.
eng_translation: It's like he hasn't started singing yet because he is pointing at the paper.

bem_transcription: Eya niwe walanda, elo cilemoneka kwati abantu bonse abali kunuma yakwe balemulolela ambe ukwimba.
eng_translation: You are right. And it's like all the people behind him are waiting for him to start singing.

bem_transcription: Shitata wakaena nafwala icisote neshati lyabuuta.
eng_translation: The very man is wearing a hat and a white shirt.

bem_transcription: Elo nabantu bonse abali uku balemoneka bafwele fye ifyafiita.
eng_translation: And all the people here look like they are wearing black.

bem_transcription: Kanabwinga kanoono nakashibwinga kanoono baleenda mwitempele.
eng_translation: The small bride and the small groom are walking in the temple.

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya aba abana baleponya fye amaluba mwitempele umwalaisa mukwenda abaleupana.
eng_translation: These children are throwing flower petals in the temple where the ones getting married will come and pass.

bem_transcription: Ninshi umuntu uwaponya amaluba umulepita banabwinga naena kufwala kwati nabashibwinga nibanabwinga?
eng_translation: Does it mean that the ones who will be dropping flower petals for the bride and the groom should also dress like them?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya tebonse abafwala nga bashibwinga na banabwinga, but intambi shaba ishapusanapusana.
eng_translation: No not everyone dresses like the bride and the groom. Traditions vary.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo baleangala ubwangalo bwakuteya inkondo.
eng_translation: The boys are playing a war simulation game.

bem_transcription: Kwaliba ne nkondo iyakwangalako fye?
eng_translation: There is also a mock war?

bem_transcription: Iyi inkondo iyi abangala fi bashilika nga baletrainer nga namumona nababiye baletamba palya pamuulu palya.
eng_translation: The ones who play this game are soldiers when they are training. If your notice their friends are even watching them from up there.

bem_transcription: So ninshi nangu bakulasa utu twine balelasa ninshe teti ufwe?
eng_translation: So if they hit you with these things they are shooting can't you die?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya teti ufwe, utu balelasa twakukulamfya fye kwilaya ufwele.
eng_translation: No you cannot die. These things they are shooting only make you dirty.

bem_transcription: Umukashana aleshana mumusebo, kunuma kuli nencikupiti cabantu.
eng_translation: A lady is dancing in the streets and there is a group of people behind her.

bem_transcription: Amasha aleshana eyalenga afwale utupimpinya utu mumusebo?
eng_translation: Is she wearing these skimly clothes because of the kind of dance she is doing?

bem_transcription: Utu utupimpinya afwele kumubili wakwe twakulanga intambi nga balesefya ubu bwine ubushiku.
eng_translation: These skimpy clothes she is wearing show tradition when they are celebrating this day.

bem_transcription: Nga nintambi ninshi bonse tabafwalile utupimpinya utu? pantu umwanakashi uyu afwele fye eka.
eng_translation: If it is tradition why are they all not wearing skimpy clothes because only her is dressed like this.

bem_transcription: Ebo basala ukucinda ebafwala fye utu twine, abashala bafwile bafwala fye bwino bwino nga balelisha inyimbo ishi shine bacinda aba bene abakashana.
eng_translation: Only those that have been chosen to dance wear such. The rest should wear normal clothing.

bem_transcription: Umwana mukashana aleensha ifingolongolo mumusana wakwe.
eng_translation: A girl child is playing with noisy things that she's placed around her waist.

bem_transcription: Ninshi incende baliko kwakwangasha fye ifingolongolo.
eng_translation: Is this place just for playing with these noisy things?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Ninshi ibumba lyabantu ili lishile mukutamba umwana uyu wine?
eng_translation: Is this group of people here to watch this child?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, uyu umwana aleyangalila fye umwine balemulolela nabawishi kunuma kulya abashala nabo bali nefyo balecita.
eng_translation: No. This child is just playing on her own and the father is waiting for her. The rest of the people have their own things they are doing.

bem_transcription: Umukashana aleteya ubwangalo ubo beta ukuti baseball.
eng_translation: A young woman is playing baseball.

bem_transcription: Ngechi cimpompo afwele kumutwe canshi?
eng_translation: What is this helmet that she is wearing on her head for?

bem_transcription: Iyi cimpompo afwele cakumucingilila ukutaluka kukuicena kukamupila bapoosa.
eng_translation: It is to prevent her from getting hurt by the ball that they throw.

bem_transcription: Ici icimupina akwete nishi ecakuminako bola?
eng_translation: Is this bat that she has for hitting the ball?

bem_transcription: Endita e,uyu wine umupina ewakuminako akakena kamupila baposa kumuntu uo uleteya nankwe.
eng_translation: Yes it is for hitting the ball when the one she is playing with throws it at her.

bem_transcription: Kapokola alesosa nabantu bakwelele pali honda.
eng_translation: A police officer is talking to people on a motorcycle.

bem_transcription: Aba bantu pali honda, bushe nindungika ukutila nibawishi, abakashi no mwana?
eng_translation: Am I right to say these people on a motorcycle are the mother the father and a child?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Ngechi cine cimpompo bafwele , bushe cibombe nshi?
eng_translation: What is the function of this helmet they are wearing?

bem_transcription: Ici cimpompo bafwele cakuicingilila kumansanso yapa musebo wapona ne cine cimbayambaya.
eng_translation: This helmet is to protect in case of a road traffic accident.

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti cabantu cileenda mumusebo.
eng_translation: a crowd of people is walking in the road.

bem_transcription: Bushe ibumba ili nikuntu kumo baleya bonse?
eng_translation: Are they all going to the same place?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya aba bantu tabeshibikwe nga bali pamo lelo lyena baleenda fye pamusebo umo wine.
eng_translation: No. it is not known whether these people are together or they are just using the same road.

bem_transcription: Uyu umusebo ninshi musebo wamutauni?
eng_translation: Is this a town road?

bem_transcription: Efyo cipalile umu nimutauni nimukalale, baleya kuma offices ukwalekana lekana ayoo yalemoneka kufikuulwa ifyo fili kunuma yabo uko.
eng_translation: It appears so, they are going to their various offices in those buildings that we can see behind them.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo natoloka mumuulu.
eng_translation: A young man has jumped high.

bem_transcription: Nga aka kantu akalemoneka ako anyatilepo bushe kanshi?
eng_translation: What is this thing that he is stepping on?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Umulumendo uyu aletoloka ukufuma pamuulu apa alefwaya ukuponena panshi.
eng_translation: This young man is jumping from a height he wants to land on the floor.

bem_transcription: Endita e, afumine ukutantala pa muulu wacibumba cilya cine kunuma yakwe.
eng_translation: Yes. He is from walking on top of that wall behind him.

bem_transcription: Icimbayambaya nacibutuka nacifutukumuna ne loba.
eng_translation: A vehicle is speeding and causing dust.

bem_transcription: Ukubutuka kwamotoka iyi teti yapunka abantu aba abalemoneka kuntashi?
eng_translation: With this speed will the vehicle not hit those people I'm front there?

bem_transcription: Mumbali balibikamo amalinga ayakwiminina kunuma abantu lelo umuntu nga ali mupepi kuti camupunka.
eng_translation: There's a fence between the road and the walkway but if a person is near, he/she can be hit.

bem_transcription: Nomba ninshi umuntu aleensesha motoka ifi so mucinkupiti cabantu?
eng_translation: But why is this person driving like this in this crowd?

bem_transcription: Iyi motoka ilebutuka ukucilikana neshi nankwe echo umuntu uyu aleensesha uyu musango.
eng_translation: This vehicle is racing with others that is why he is driving like this.

bem_transcription: Shikulubantu ali pakamana no bwato.
eng_translation: An old man is on the river with a boat.

bem_transcription: Mubwato umu bushe kuti akwanisha ukubwensha eka?
eng_translation: Can he manage to pilot the boat alone?

bem_transcription: Ee kuti akwanisha.
eng_translation: Yes he can manage.

bem_transcription: Ninshi shitata wine alemonekela ukufiitulukila?
eng_translation: Why is this man not clear on the picture?

bem_transcription: Alemonekela ukufiituluka kumulandu wakuti akasuba kaleingila cungulo bushiku ici.
eng_translation: Because the sun is setting and it is evening.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabanamayo nabashitata nabafwala amandeleshi yalekanalekana.
eng_translation: A group of men and women is wearing different dresses.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ibumba ili ninshi lifwalile ifyaso ifilemoneka ifikulu fikulu?
eng_translation: Why are they wearing such big clothes?

bem_transcription: Aba bantu baleibukisha umuntu wali wamunshita yakale balemusefya.
eng_translation: They are remembering and celebrating one person of old.

bem_transcription: Ninshi bonse aba bantu bakolongana bonse bakolonganine umulandu wacintu cimo?
eng_translation: Are all these people here gathered for one purpose?

bem_transcription: Kumona ifyo bafwele ifyapalanapalana cilelangilila ukuti bali bonse pamo
eng_translation: Just looking at how similar their clothes are you can tell that they are together.

bem_transcription: Umwana umukashana naikata mumbali yamilomo.
eng_translation: A girl child is holding the sides of the lips.

bem_transcription: Nga cinshi alepangila icinso icaifi umwana uyu?
eng_translation: Why is this child making this face?

bem_transcription: Ilingi line abana nga balecita ifi ninshi balekanina umuntu uulebeba fimo.
eng_translation: Most of the times children do this when they are saying No to someone who is telling them something.

bem_transcription: Bushe umwana uyu umukashana aleangalila pamo noyu umulumendo uuli kunuma?
eng_translation: Is this girl playing with the boy behind?

bem_transcription: Endita e, cilemoneka bali mun'ganda mukichini baleangalila pamo.
eng_translation: Yes. It appears they are playing together inside the house in the kitchen.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabanamayo nabashitata baleanshika utwakulalapo.
eng_translation: A group of men and women are arranging their mats.

bem_transcription: Baleanshika ekuti balalepo akasuba?
eng_translation: Do they want to sleep there in the afternoon?

bem_transcription: Utu baleanshika utu twakulalapo nga baleyolola uto beta mucisungu ati yoga.
eng_translation: No the mats are for yoga.

bem_transcription: Abalemoneka abaiminine bena ninshi tabaleyolola?
eng_translation: Are those that are standing not taking part in yoga?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya taciishibikwe lelo kwena bali ne bumba line ili.
eng_translation: Well we can't tell. But they are with this very group.

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Icibansa baleteyelapo cilemoneka icabuuta buuta, bushe finshi babikapo?
eng_translation: The ground where they are playing from looks whitish. What do they apply?

bem_transcription: Mufibansa umu balabikamo ifyo beta ukuti ice pakutila insapato bafwala shiletelela bwino.
eng_translation: The put ice in these stadiums so that their shoes can slide nicely.

bem_transcription: ubwangalo bwine ubu bateya shani?
eng_translation: How do they play this same game?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Icinso camukashana balicikakatika pacibumba.
eng_translation: A girl's face has been stuck on the wall.

bem_transcription: Apa bakabamtika icikope ici nipa tuuka?
eng_translation: Is this place a shop where this picture has been stuck?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya ici icikuulwa taciishibikwe nakalya iyo.
eng_translation: No we don't know this place.

bem_transcription: Uyu umulumendo uulemoneka uku kumbi ninshi naena cikope?
eng_translation: Is this young man we are seeing this other side also a picture?

bem_transcription: Uyu umulumendo ulemonekela palya epamwinshi pene epo bapitila tecikope nakalya iyo muntu fye umwine mwine.
eng_translation: That one is a real person. It looks like that's the door they use to enter the building.

bem_transcription: Umwana umukashana naikata kukanwa.
eng_translation: A girl child is holding her mouth.

bem_transcription: Cinshi cingalenga umwana uyu ukwikata kukanwa mumusango ekete?
eng_translation: What could make her hold her mouth like this?

bem_transcription: Uyu umwana kuti limbi aleseka alemona icintu icamumfwishishe bwino.
eng_translation: Maybe the child has seen something funny and she is laughing.

bem_transcription: Nga aka ako afwele pamutwe nikanshi?
eng_translation: What is this thing she is wearing on her head?

bem_transcription: Akasote ako afwele kumutwe bafwika ngolesefya ubushiku wafyelwe.
eng_translation: It's a hat you wear when you are celebrating your birthday.

bem_transcription: Abantu babili bali mukamana mupepi necisabi.
eng_translation: Two people are in the river near the fish.

bem_transcription: Aba bantu balemoneka bali panshi yamenshi nomba teti banwine?
eng_translation: These people look like they are under the river. Cant they drown.

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, nabafwala pakanwa intambo iileleta umwela ukufuma kucilitanki bapapile munuma.
eng_translation: No they can't. they have a tube giving them air from the Gass tanks that they have on their backs.

bem_transcription: Ngechi icisabi nomba cilemoneka icikulu teti cibalya?
eng_translation: What about this big fish can't it eat them?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya ifi ifisabi tafimina abantu, filangala nabantu efilya beta mucisunga ati dolphin.
eng_translation: No these don't eat people. They play with people. They are called dolphins

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabakashana batatu nomulumendo nabekala panshi baleisha.
eng_translation: A group of three girls and one boy are seated chatiing.

bem_transcription: Ngechi icitambo cilemoneka necishimbi uku bushe nicinshi?
eng_translation: What about this metal and this rope what are they?

bem_transcription: Ilingi ici icitambo bakobekelako flagi.
eng_translation: It is mostly used for hanging the flag.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo wasaalile abanakashi aba nalwala nangu taleumfwa bwino?
eng_translation: Is the young ma that chose these ladies unwell?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya alifye umutuntulu efyo bekele fye pakwiisha.
eng_translation: No he is just fine. That is just how they are seated as they are chatting.

bem_transcription: Shitata nanamayo nabekala kumbali yakamana.
eng_translation: A man and a woman are seated on the river bank.

bem_transcription: Shitata uyu nanamayo bekele baleisha?
eng_translation: Are they chatting?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya balelobe sabi.
eng_translation: No,  they are fishing.

bem_transcription: Kuti baikata isabi apa balelobela mupepi nabantu?
eng_translation: Can they fish when they are fishing near where there are people?

bem_transcription: Imikatile bekatilamo isabi mupepi nakamana kupoose fyakulya mupepi isabi lilesa mukulya ifyofine ninshi epa kuliikata nokulikata.
eng_translation: The way they fish is to throw fish food near. The fish comes to eat and that's how they catch it.

bem_transcription: Abantu bali petuuka baleshita.
eng_translation: People are buying at a shop.

bem_transcription: Isabi line lilemoneka ilyabuuta buuta bushe malaiti yonse aya babikileko?
eng_translation: The fish looks whitish. Is it all the lights that they have added?

bem_transcription: Ee, malaiti yapusana pusana amakalas ukuti bawamye ncende ilemoneka iyalelema.
eng_translation: Yes. The lights have different colors so that they can beautify the place.

bem_transcription: Abantu bonse aba batanteme ninshi balefwaya ukushita fintu baleshitisha mwituuka ililine?
eng_translation: All these people lined up here want to buy things from this shop?

bem_transcription: Namulungika, aba bantu balelolela ukushita ifyo baleshitisha apa pancende.
eng_translation: You are right.These people are waiting to buy what they are selling at this place.

bem_transcription: Bashitata batatu balebomba mumusebo.
eng_translation: Three men are working in the road.

bem_transcription: Kumusebo balebombelapo aba bashitata kulemoneka takuli abantu, balemonekako fye beka bushe cinshi cingalenga?
eng_translation: The doesn't seem to be any other people apart from themselves in this road they are working on. Why do you think this is so?

bem_transcription: Teti kupitile abantu kumulandu wakuti balebomba.
eng_translation: People cant use this road because they are working on it.

bem_transcription: Bushe ifibombelo balebomfya fibombelo fyashani ifi ifyakula so?
eng_translation: These tools look too big. what kind of tools are they?

bem_transcription: Fibombelo fyakuwamishako imisebo.
eng_translation: They are road maintenance tools

bem_transcription: Shitata aletina kompyuta yakwe.
eng_translation: A man is pressing his computer.

bem_transcription: Ngoyu umukashana uulemoneka bushe muntu olo cikope?
eng_translation: This girl that we can see, is it a real person or just a picture.

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya uyu umukashana cikope fye babikile pacibumba.
eng_translation: No this is just a picture that they have put on the wall.

bem_transcription: Shitata uyu bushe ali mwi ofeshi nelyo ali mung'anda?
eng_translation: Is this man in the office or in his house.

bem_transcription: Kumona nefyo akele pacipuna nefyo amalaiti yali yalya ayali kunuma yakwe ne mfimfi kunuma yakwe cilelanga ukuti ali mung'anda.
eng_translation: looking at how he is seated on the chair, how the lights behind him are and the darkness behind we can say that he is in the house.

bem_transcription: Iconi cilepupuka pesamba pali namenshi.
eng_translation: A bird is flying with water below.

bem_transcription: Ninshi iconi ici calefuma mumenshi?
eng_translation: Is this bird coming from the water?

bem_transcription: Ici coni calefuba utusabi utufumina pamuulu yakamana.
eng_translation: It was grabbing small fish that were near the surface.

bem_transcription: Coni camusango shani ici cine?
eng_translation: What kind of a bird is this?

bem_transcription: Ici cioni cintu beta mucingeleshi ati seagull.
eng_translation: It is a seagull

bem_transcription: Bashitata batatu nabeminina abali nakuntashi babili nabakumbatana iminwe.
eng_translation: Three men are standing. The two in front are crossing arms.

bem_transcription: Bonse bashitata basalile fye ukufwala utusote utwamusango umo?
eng_translation: Did all the men just choose to wear same hearts?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya utu utusote bafwele twalutambi lwabo lwakuchurch kumyabo ma mozilemu aba bantu.
eng_translation: No these people are Muslims. These hearts they are wearing are their church traditions.

bem_transcription: Ngafilya ifyalemonekela ifyabuutulukila buutulukila kuti fyaba nifinshi?
eng_translation: What about those whitish things?

bem_transcription: Filya ifilemoneka ifilemoneka ifyabuutulukila kulya mapulashitiki emupombelwe ifintu fyakushita ifyalingana nefyakufwala.
eng_translation: Those whitish things are plastics where theve put things equivalent to clothes.

bem_transcription: Nakulubantu umukote nalolesha kumulumendo.
eng_translation: An old woman is looking at a young man.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo uyu kuti aba nibululu wakwa nakulu bantu uyu?
eng_translation: Could this young man be her relative?

bem_transcription: Kwena apa teti cishibikwe, cilemoneka kwati nakulu alepita fye uyu.
eng_translation: Well we can't tell. it's like this old woman is just passing.

bem_transcription: Cinshi engekatila kumatobo nakulu bantu uyu?
eng_translation: Why would this old lady old her arms.

bem_transcription: Limbi pali cimo icibabile ico alefwenya kumatobo uyu nakulu.
eng_translation: Maybe there's something itching that she wants to scratch on her cheeks.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu nanakulu bantu nabeminina.
eng_translation: An old woman and an old man are standing.

bem_transcription: Ngechi icibikile nakulu bantu pa menso bushe nicinshi?
eng_translation: What is this thing on the old woman's face?

bem_transcription: Ici cintu babomfya ukukopela ifikope cintu beta mucingeleshi ati kamela.
eng_translation: This is a camera.

bem_transcription: Nikuntu nshi uku bali uku?
eng_translation: where is this place?

bem_transcription: Kwena teti cishibikwe uko bali lelo lyena aba bantu bali kuncende ukuli ukusefya.
eng_translation: Well we can't tell but these people are in a place where they are celebrating.

bem_transcription: Umukashana nakwela pe horse.
eng_translation: a girl is on a horse.

bem_transcription: Ngecimpompo afwele kumutwe umukashana uyu bushe cibombe nshi?
eng_translation: What is the function of this helmet that she is wearing?

bem_transcription: Ici cimpompo afwele kumutwe cakumucingilila ukutaluka mukuicena nga apona panshi.
eng_translation: The helmet  is to protect her from hurting herself when she falls.

bem_transcription: Alemoneka napoosa sana amano kufintu alecita umukashana uyu, bushe finshi fingalenga ukuposa amano?
eng_translation: The girl looks very focused. What could make her focus this much?

bem_transcription: Icilengele ukuposa amano alelolesha uko aleya pantu uyu umukashana balecilikana nababiye.
eng_translation: It is because she wants to see where she is going because they are competing.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabashitata lilesha inyimbo.
eng_translation: A group of men is playing music.

bem_transcription: Nga apa baiminine bashitata aba nipanshi?
eng_translation: Where are these men standing?

bem_transcription: Apa beminine aba bashitata pantu beta mucingeleshi ati pa stage ngelyo abantu balemitamba ifyo mulecita.
eng_translation: This is a stage where you perform from.

bem_transcription: So ninshi kuncende uku bali kwali abalebatamba?
eng_translation: So there were people watching in this place?

bem_transcription: Ee, endita e, ishi incende nga namwiminina mumusango uyu ninshi kuli abalemitamba.
eng_translation: Yes when you are standing like this in this place it means there are people watching.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu naikala alebelenga necipepala.
eng_translation: An old man is seated reading a book.

bem_transcription: Ninshi apa shikulu bantu aikele epa n'ganda ekala?
eng_translation: Is this man sitting at his house?

bem_transcription: Kwena tacishibikwe nga epo ekele nipa n'ganda nangu ekele fye aletuusha.
eng_translation: Well we don't know if we're he is seated is his house or he is just resting from there.

bem_transcription: Bantu balya baleisa balelola uko shikulubantu ekalile bushe nikuli shikulu bantu bengalaisa?
eng_translation: Those people are coming towards the old man. Could they be coming to him?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya taciishibikwe aba bantu nabo kuti baya fye nokobaleilolela nabena palwabo.
eng_translation: Well we don't know. They could be just on their own route.

bem_transcription: Bashitata baleangala ubwangalo ubo beta ukuti hockey mucingeleshi.
eng_translation: Men are playing hockey.

bem_transcription: Ngashi inkonto bekete muminwe shanshi?
eng_translation: what are these sticks they are holding for?

bem_transcription: Ishi inkonto bekete muminwe esho babomfya pakuteyela ubu bwine ubwangalo.
eng_translation: These sticks are the ones they use to play hockey.

bem_transcription: Nge fi filesabuka kuli uyu uutangile uuleshelela nifinshi?
eng_translation: What are these things splashing from the one in sliding in front?

bem_transcription: Iyo iilesabuka ni ice pakwebati aletelela bwino insapato shakwe ishi shine babomfya pakutelela.
eng_translation: What is splashing is ice so that they could slide well.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu naikala pambao mupepi ne wiindo.
eng_translation: An old man is seated on timber near a window.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka apa pekele shikulu bantu nipa muulu teti apone?
eng_translation: It looks like this old man is sitting on top. Can't he fall?

bem_transcription: Uyu shikulubantu teti apone efyo ekele naishiba ishi imbao ekelepo nashikata kufintu fimo mukati.
eng_translation: He cannot fall. That is why he is seated because he knows that there is something inside holding them.

bem_transcription: Nifinshi allecita uyu wine shikulu bantu apa pa mbao ekele?
eng_translation: What is this old man even doing on this timber?

bem_transcription: Ukulingana nokumona icikope pantu ekele uyu shikulubantu alepenta mumbali ye wiindo lyakwe.
eng_translation: It looks like he is painting planks of his window.

bem_transcription: Shikulubantu aleenda mumusebo necaketi nafula nakobeka pakubeya.
eng_translation: An old man is walking in the road with his jacket hang on the shoulder.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alemoneka ali namatontonkayo ayalemushupa bushe cinshi cingalenga?
eng_translation: This old man looks like there are thoughts troubling him. What could they be?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya taciishibikwe nga ali namatontonkayo ayalemushupa lelo alemoneka fye nanaka.
eng_translation: We we can't tell if he has thoughts troubling him. He just looks tired.

bem_transcription: Bushe alekomboka kuncito?
eng_translation: Is he knocking off from work?

bem_transcription: Efyo cipalile kwena ukuti alekomboka kumilimo.
eng_translation: That's what it looks like. He is coming from work.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alepampa bwino ifibokoshi.
eng_translation: An old man is stacking the boxes well.

bem_transcription: Nipanshi pantu akwelelele shikulu bantu uyu?
eng_translation: Where is this man stepping?

bem_transcription: Akwelelele pafibokoshi fibiye ifishikwete ifintu mukati.
eng_translation: He is stepping on other boxes that have no things in them.

bem_transcription: Ifibokoshi ifi teti fyatantuluka nokumuponena shikulu abantu uyu?
eng_translation: Cant these boxes move and fall on the big man.

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya ifyo bafipampile fili ifyaikatana bwino bwino.
eng_translation: No. The boxes are well stacked. They cannot fall.

bem_transcription: Imbwa shilebutuka nabantu bali kunuma yashiko.
eng_translation: The dogs are running and people are behind them.

bem_transcription: Uyu muntu kunuma yambwa ishi bushe finshi alecitako?
eng_translation: What is this person doing behind the dogs?

bem_transcription: Aba bantu bali kunuma nabakwele pacintu ico bapopelela ico bakulika kumbwa nga shilebutuka.
eng_translation: These people are in a cart which is being pulled by dogs.

bem_transcription: So ninshi ici cintu bafwele mumutwe aciledonsa ishi imbwa shlebutuka shilebensha?
eng_translation: Are these things on their heads the ones connected to the running dogs and pulling them?

bem_transcription: Endita e, namulungama, icintu bakwelele ecikulikilwe kumbwa ishi.
eng_translation: Yes you are right. This cart is connected to the dogs

bem_transcription: Umwana umulumendo nabutuluka kumenso.
eng_translation: The young boy is dirty on the face.

bem_transcription: Cinshi cingalenga umwana uyu ukuibutulusha pamenso bushe ebwangalo baleangala.
eng_translation: Why is he this dirt on the face? is it a game they are playing?

bem_transcription: Capalile kwati aba bana ekwangala baleangala kwaleipenta kumenso.
eng_translation: It seems like that's the game they are playing of painting each other's face.

bem_transcription: Imilomo shamulumendo shibutulukile kumo, ninshi emukutila acilalya ifintu acilashinga kumenso?
eng_translation: The lips are equally dirty. Does it mean he was eating something and then he smeared it around the face?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya ifintu acilapenta te fintu acilalya, apentele fye kumo nakukanwa.
eng_translation: Not at all. What he painted is not something he was eating. He just painted the mouth as well

bem_transcription: Ibumba lya bantu nalikolongana lileumfwa kufilelanda uuli kuntashi.
eng_translation: A group of people is gathered listening to what the one in front is saying.

bem_transcription: Ninshi bafwalile ifyampepo nefisote fyakumitwe aba bantu?
eng_translation: Why are they wearing sweaters and head socks?

bem_transcription: Uku kuncende bali uku kuli ukwatalala kuli ice echo bafwalile ifi.
eng_translation: Because this place is really cold and has ice. That is why.

bem_transcription: Ice ine eyalenga bafwele nefi bafwele nakunsapato, ifyo balenyatapo?
eng_translation: Is it because of the ice that they are wearing these things they have on their feet?

bem_transcription: Ifi bafwele kunsapato fyakutelelela nga baya mukwangala umu mwine muli ice.
eng_translation: These on their shoes are for sliding when the to play on the ice.

bem_transcription: Iminwe yabantu ilepentana amaala.
eng_translation: People's hands are painting each other's nails.

bem_transcription: Ninshi balebomfya ukupenta amaala iyi, bushe ni paint iyi ine bapentalako amayanda?
eng_translation: What is this they are using to paint their nails? Is it the same lsint we use for painting houses?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, iyi paint balebomfya yakupentela fye amaala iyo beta mucingeleshi ati nail polish.
eng_translation: No this is just nail polish.

bem_transcription: Umuntu walepenta uyu balepenta ekuti ni cuibusa wakwe?
eng_translation: Are these two friends?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya teti cishibikwe, lelo lyena ishi imipentele shilaba nimwituuka fye nokulipila walipila.
eng_translation: We can't know for sure. But this is usually just done in a shop where you go they paint, you pay and leave.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu aletamba pabunkolanya.
eng_translation: The Old man is watching TV

bem_transcription: Apa aikele shikulu bantu ekuti epa ng'anda ekala?
eng_translation: Is this his house?

bem_transcription: Kwena teti cishibikwe, kuti caba nipa n'ganda lelo lyena apa nipalukungu.
eng_translation: We can't know for sure. It could be he's at the house but this is the backyard.

bem_transcription: Ubukolanya bwine bulemoneka nababufimba ne cisalu icakashika, bushe cinshi cingalenga.
eng_translation: The Television is covered in a red cloth. Why do you think this is so?

bem_transcription: Echo bafimbile icisalu ici cakucingilila ulukungu ululepupuka mumwela.
eng_translation: To protect the Television from the dust

bem_transcription: Bakapokola babilil, nabeminina mumusebo.
eng_translation: Two police officers are standing on the road.

bem_transcription: Nikwisa uku baiminine aba bakapokola?
eng_translation: Where is this that they are standing?

bem_transcription: Aba bantu beminine, cipalile umu nimukalale.
eng_translation: It's like these two are standing in town

bem_transcription: Nge fi bafwele ifyakatapa katapa fibomba inshi?
eng_translation: What is the function of these green things they are wearing?

bem_transcription: Ifi bafwele ifyakatapa katapa, fyakulangisha abantu ukuti aba niba kapokola.
eng_translation: These green things they are wearing are for showing people that they are policemen

bem_transcription: Abantu babili nabeminina nabakumbatana.
eng_translation: Two people are standing and are hugging.

bem_transcription: Emukutila pali umukashana no mulumendo pa bantu aba?
eng_translation: Does it mean there is a girl and a boy of the two people here?

bem_transcription: Ukumona nefyo bakumbatene kuti watila umo mukashana umo mulumendo.
eng_translation: Just looking at how they are hugging you can say one is a girl and one is a boy.

bem_transcription: Cimbayambaya cilya icilemoneka icabutulukila kunuma yabo?
eng_translation: Is that a vehicle that looks greyish behind them?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Cimbayambaya.
eng_translation: Yes it is a vehicle

bem_transcription: Umukashana no mwaume balecinda.
eng_translation: A young man and a young woman are dancing.

bem_transcription: Masha yashani aya baleshana, ayakwimya amaboko mumuulu na moolu?
eng_translation: What kind of dance is this where they lift the hands and the legs in the air?

bem_transcription: Iyi imicindile balecindilamo intu beta mucingeleshi ukuti salsa.
eng_translation: It is called salsa

bem_transcription: Amasha yene baleshana, eyalengele ukuti umo afwele icabuuta umo afwele icafiita?
eng_translation: Is it because of the dance that one is wearing white and the other one black?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, lelo lyena basalile fye ukufwala ifi fine pakumonekela kubantu.
eng_translation: Not at all. They just chose to wear that today.

bem_transcription: Umuntu nakwela pa cinga iitali alecofa mumusebo.
eng_translation: A person is riding a very long bicycle.

bem_transcription: Ifi afwele emukutila ni sister wakukatolika?
eng_translation: These clothes she's wearing, does it mean she's a Catholic sister?

bem_transcription: Endita e! ba sister efyo bafwala aba ku catholic.
eng_translation: Yes. that is what catholic sisters wear.

bem_transcription: Nomba kuti aba sister uyu, imimonekele te mwaume uyu?
eng_translation: But could this one be a sister? Is this not a man?

bem_transcription: Icinsoo cilemoneka cakwa shitata endita e, lelo lyena tacishibikwe nga alesansamusha fye abantu mumusebo elyo nangu ni sister wa cine cine.
eng_translation: It's true the face looks like a man. We can't tell of he's just making people laugh or it really is a sister.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alenwa ubwalwa no mulumendo.
eng_translation: An old man is drinking beer with a young man.

bem_transcription: Bushe umulumendo uyu kuti aba mwana waka shikulu bantu uyu nangu muntu fye uo baishibana fye?
eng_translation: Could the young man be the old man's son or they just know each other?

bem_transcription: Kwena kuti aba umwana wakwa shikulu bantu wine.
eng_translation: It's possible he could be the son of the old man.

bem_transcription: Nge ci ekete shikulu bantu kuminwe, bushe kuti fyaba fyakulya nafyo?
eng_translation: What is this other thing the old man is holding? could it be food too?

bem_transcription: Endita e, fyakulya.
eng_translation: Yes it is food.

bem_transcription: Namayo naiminina kumbali yakwa shitata nabafwala nefya buuta buuta.
eng_translation: A woman is standing next to a man and is wearing something whitish.

bem_transcription: Ifi bafwele emukutila pali umukashi no mulume?
eng_translation: Does this kind of dressing mean there's a wife and a husband?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya tacishibikwe nga bafuma mukupana nga bale-enda fye teti cishibikwe nakalya iyo.
eng_translation: No. We don't know if they are from getting married or they are just walking.

bem_transcription: Ifi ifisote bafwele kwati nibamfumu olo bafumine ku n'ganada ya bufumu, bushe kuti baba bakubufumu?
eng_translation: These hats they are wearing like they are royalty or they are from a royal household, could they be royalty?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya nacho tacishibikwe, lelo lyena bafifwalile fye pakuseefya ifintu baleseefya.
eng_translation: We can't tell either. All we know is they wore them as they were celebrating what ever it is that they were celebrating.

bem_transcription: Umwana umukashana ali mumenshi aleowa.
eng_translation: A girl child is swimming in the water.

bem_transcription: Nga aya amagogo afwele umwana uyu bushe pali ifyo yalebomba mukowa kwakwe?
eng_translation: Are these goggles she's wearing helping her in her swimming?

bem_transcription: Aya amagogo afwele yakumucingilila amenshi ukwingila mumenso ilyo aleowa.
eng_translation: These goggles are to protect water from entering her eyes as she is swimming.

bem_transcription: Nga ifi fintu ekete nafikwata incito nafyo?
eng_translation: What about these things she's holding, are they also important?

bem_transcription: Pantu bali nipa ma offices apo babombela abantu kufwala ifyacindama.
eng_translation: This place has offices where people work from. They have to wear something important.

bem_transcription: Umwana umukashana no mulumendo bali mucintu nabamwentula.
eng_translation: A Man and a lady are in something and are smiling.

bem_transcription: Umukashana alemoneka ekele fye mwenso mwenso.
eng_translation: The lady looks scared

bem_transcription: Icintu bakwelelemo cilapilibuka echo alemonekela uwamwenso.
eng_translation: The thing they are in can overturn. That is why she is scared

bem_transcription: Akalumendo kena kalemoneka fye akansansa nakomfwa bwino.
eng_translation: The young man looks comfortable and happy.

bem_transcription: Kena nakatemwa ifilecitika ecilengele kalemoneka akasansa.
eng_translation: He loves what is happening that is why he looks happy.

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti cabantu nacitantama mumushilwa.
eng_translation: A crowed of people is in a queue.

bem_transcription: Mulaini wamusango shani nangula finshi balefwaya ifyakutantamina icilaini cakula ifi?
eng_translation: What do they want for them to make such a long queue?

bem_transcription: Cipalile baleingila mukuya mucikuulwa ici cine icili kuntashi yabo.
eng_translation: It's like they have lined up to enter the building in front of them

bem_transcription: Bonse aba bantu bakolongene so balefwaya ukwingila umu mwine mucikuulwa.
eng_translation: All these people gathered here want to enter this building?

bem_transcription: Endita e! baleingila mucikuulwa cine ici.
eng_translation: Yes they are entering this same building.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo baleteya ubwangalo bwakuposeshanya umupila.
eng_translation: The young men are playing rugby.

bem_transcription: Ngefi baifimbile kumenso nafyo fibombe nshi?
eng_translation: What's the use of these things on their faces?

bem_transcription: Ifi fintu bafimbene nafyo kumenso fyakubacingilila ilyo balepunkana ukukanaicena ilyo balepunkana?
eng_translation: It is to protect them when they bump into one another so they don't hurt themselves.

bem_transcription: Nangu bola iyi ine bakushema pa menso teti fikalipe?
eng_translation: What about when the ball hits your face, can't it hurt?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya icimpompo cine ici bafwele emo itanuka bola wine uyu.
eng_translation: No it can't. The ball bounces off the very helmet they are wearing.

bem_transcription: Umukashana nabutuka ne nsapato ishakwata amawilo.
eng_translation: A girl is running with wheeled shoes.

bem_transcription: Kulemoneka kuli na umbi umukashana walemukonka panuma emukutila balecilikana?
eng_translation: It's like there's another girl following her behind. They are competing.

bem_transcription: Endita e! ubu bwangalo bwakucilikana ukubutuka notu twine utusapato.
eng_translation: Yes this is a roller skating competition.

bem_transcription: Ili ibumba lya bantu ililemoneka lyaishile ukutamba aba bene abalecilikana?
eng_translation: Did all these people come to watch this same competition?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Ili ibumba lishile mukulumba aba bene bantu abalepepekana.
eng_translation: Yes. They all have come to cheer these competitors.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu nalisangalala.
eng_translation: A crowd of people is happy.

bem_transcription: Ibumba line ili pali fye no mukashana umo abashala bonse balumendo, bushe ninshi pengabela fye umukashana umo?
eng_translation: There's ony one girl in this crowd. The rest are men. Why is there only one girl?

bem_transcription: Echo abelelepo eka namayo cakuti ewaishile fye eka mukusakopwako icikope.
eng_translation: It is because she is the only one that came to get a picture.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo nabekata ifintu muminwe bushe finshi ifi bekete?
eng_translation: The boys are holding something in their hands. what is it?

bem_transcription: Ifi bekete muminwe shabo mabotolo yabwalwa.
eng_translation: They are holding alcohol bottles.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu aleipika mu kichini.
eng_translation: The old man is cooking in the kitchen.

bem_transcription: Nga aka akabuuta akakile mumusana?
eng_translation: What is this white thing tied around his waist?

bem_transcription: Aka akabuuta afwele mumusana kakumucingilila ukukanailamfya itoloshi afwele.
eng_translation: It is an apron so that his trousers doesn't get dirty.

bem_transcription: So apa yalebutuka ninshi ilecilika nashimbi imbwa?
eng_translation: It is running and outrunning the other dogs.

bem_transcription: Ukulingana ukumona nefyo baifwikile, endita e! kuli ishinankwe isho balepepekana nasho.
eng_translation: According to how it's dressed, Yes it is competing with others.

bem_transcription: Imbwa ilebutuka mukamana mumenshi mukati.
eng_translation: The dog is running in the river

bem_transcription: Ninshi pali ifyo yalefwaya mumenshi umu yaingile?
eng_translation: Is it looking for something in the water?

bem_transcription: Kuti kwaba fimo ifyo baiposeele mukamana ifyo bakonkele mukusenda
eng_translation: Maybe it is fetching something that they threw in the river.

bem_transcription: Nomba tali imbwa shilatina amenshi tashifwaya ukwingila mumenshi?
eng_translation: But dont dogs fear water?

bem_transcription: Cili fye nefyo baikushe imbwa shimo shalitemwa ukwangala mumenshi.
eng_translation: It depends on how it's been trained. some love playing in water.

bem_transcription: Umukashana mucintubwingi nabika umbrella kumutwe.
eng_translation: A girl in public with an umbrella over her head.

bem_transcription: Nomba umukashana wine alebika umbrella ukwabula imfula?
eng_translation: Is she moving with an umbrella when there are no rains?

bem_transcription: Umbrella taibomba fye kumfula yeka lelo lyena akasuba nga nakabalikisha kuti waibikako kumutwe,
eng_translation: An umbrella is not only for rains. You can also use it when the sun is too hot.

bem_transcription: Nga aka akalitoni akalemoneka pamona wakwe?
eng_translation: What is this dot on her nose?

bem_transcription: Aka akalittoni lisikiyo atula pamona pene.
eng_translation: It's a hole for a nose ring.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo aletolokela mu menshi.
eng_translation: A boy is jumping in the water.

bem_transcription: IUku ukutoloka kwa mulumendo uyu bushe kutoloka kwakweba ati owe?
eng_translation: Is this jumping a cry for help?

bem_transcription: Endita e! aletolokela ukuti owe.
eng_translation: Yes it is a cry for help.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu pool wa menshi uli mu n'ganda cause cilemoneka naishungulukwa namagalashi?
eng_translation: Is this water pool inside because it looks like it's been fenced with glass.

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya nipanse, balitabililako fye amagalashi.
eng_translation: No it is outside. it is just fenced with glass

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alebomba mucikuulwa icamoneke ukuti caliwile.
eng_translation: The only man is working in a building which looks like it collapsed.

bem_transcription: Bushe uyu shikulu bantu te aba beta ati ama fire fighters abapususha abantu mubusanso?
eng_translation: Is this old man not a firefighter?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Shikulu bantu uyu nyabo bene bantu mwasosa ma fire fighters.
eng_translation: Yes he is a firefighter.

bem_transcription: Bushe cibomba inshi icimpompo afwele kumutwe uyu shikulubantu?
eng_translation: What is the use of that helmet on the head of this old man.

bem_transcription: Ici icimpompo afwele cakumucingila ukukanaicena icintu nga capona kumuulu.
eng_translation: It is to protect his head from falling objects.

bem_transcription: Banamayo nabekata nefyakupyangilako bale-enda mumusebo.
eng_translation: Women holding brooms are walking in the road.

bem_transcription: Ngotu utusalu bafimbile pakanwa, ninshi balefimbilapo pakanwa?
eng_translation: Why are they wearing face masks?

bem_transcription: Utu utusalu bakwete pakanwa twakubacingilila kulukungu ilintu balepyanga.
eng_translation: The face masks are for protecting them from the dust as they are sweeping.

bem_transcription: Ninshi banamayo aba balepyanga mumusebo?
eng_translation: Are they sweeping in the streets?

bem_transcription: Endita e! aba banamayo balewamye misebo.
eng_translation: Yes they are cleaning the streets .

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti cabantu nacikolongana, nacitantama namu laini.
eng_translation: A crowd of people is gathered and is in a queue

bem_transcription: Ninshi pali uko balefwaya ukwingila abantu bene aba?
eng_translation: Are they trying to go somewhere?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Abantu baleingila cipalile pali ifyo baile mukutamba mukati ka cikuulwa.
eng_translation: Yes they are entering the building. It's like they are going to watch something in there.

bem_transcription: Ninshi bengaya ukutamba munshita ya bushiku?
eng_translation: What could they go to watch this evening?

bem_transcription: Ilingi line balaya mukutamba umupila wakumakasa nelyo umupila wakuminwe uo beta baseball,
eng_translation: Mostly they go to watch football or baseball

bem_transcription: Icikunpiti cabantu cile-enda mupepi ne fikuulwa.
eng_translation: A crowd of people is walking near the buildings.

bem_transcription: Nimukalale abantu bali umu?
eng_translation: Are they in town?

bem_transcription: Kuti caba nimukalale bali pantu icikuulwa ifi fili ifyamyemba sana.
eng_translation: It could be that they are in town because the buildings look really nice.

bem_transcription: So ninshi ifikuulwa ifi ifilemoneka matuuka ayalekana lekana?
eng_translation: So are these buildings different shops?

bem_transcription: Endita e! fili ifyaputukwa mumiputule ishapusana pusana fikuulwa ifyausana pusana, amakwebo yantu yapusana ayalesangwamo.
eng_translation: Yes the building are partitioned into many different shops with different businesses.

bem_transcription: Umwana umukashana alelisha eko beta mucingeleshi ati violin.
eng_translation: A girl is playing the violin

bem_transcription: Alemoneka natemwa ukulalisha ifyo alelisha umukashana uyu.
eng_translation: It looks like this girl is enjoying what she is playing.

bem_transcription: Ali uwamwentula kumulandu wakuti cilelila ifyo acilaenekela.
eng_translation: She is smiling because the sound is coming out just like she wanted.

bem_transcription: Emukuti pali abalemutamba olo aleilishisha fye umwine aleyumfwisha bwino?
eng_translation: Are they people watching her or she's just enjoying the music alone?

bem_transcription: Iyo mukwai teti cishibikwe, but ilingi line cilaba ukuti balekutamba.
eng_translation: Well we can't know for sure. But mostly there are people watching.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu lileingila pamwinshi wacikululwa.
eng_translation: A crowd of people is entering a building.

bem_transcription: Umukashana ali pntashi alemoneka uwadabwa dabwa.
eng_translation: The girl in front looks surprised.

bem_transcription: Eco alemoneka uwapapa papa, limbi kwali umuntu wamwitile kunuma eko acebukile ati aloleshe
eng_translation: Maybe she looks surprised because someone called her from behind and she's trying to figure out who.

bem_transcription: Bushe ibumba lya bantu ili pali ifyo bale-esha ukutamba?
eng_translation: Is this crowd of people trying to watch something?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Aba bantu cimoneke baleya mukwingila mukutamba umupila.
eng_translation: It's like these people are going to watch football.

bem_transcription: Umwana umulumendo aleteya umupila.
eng_translation: The boy is playing football.

bem_transcription: Ukwimya ukuulu kwamusango uyu ekuti acilapanta bola?
eng_translation: By the way he has lifted his leg could it be he was kicking the ball?

bem_transcription: Endita e! acilapanta bola.
eng_translation: Yes he was kicking the ball

bem_transcription: Bushe kuti caba ati pali abo alepantila nangu aleipantila fye umwine eka?
eng_translation: Could it be that he was kicking it to someone or he's just alone?

bem_transcription: Teti cishibikwe nakalya, limbi alepantila kucibumba cali kuntashi yakwe.
eng_translation: We can't tell. Maybe he was aiming for the wall in front of him.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu lilewamya mumisebo ipitamo abantu.
eng_translation: A group of people is cleaning the road which people use.

bem_transcription: Abalepyanga ninshi ebali nefimbaya-mbaya ifi ifili mupepi?
eng_translation: Are the ones sweeping the owners of these parked cars?

bem_transcription: Endita e! abalepyanga ebalekusaka ifisooso nokupoosa mufimbaya-mbaya fine ifi.
eng_translation: Yes. They are sweeping and putting the dirt in these parked cars.

bem_transcription: Cilemoneka pali abatantike amakwebo yakushitisha.
eng_translation: It looks like there's someone selling something.

bem_transcription: Endita e! balya bantu nabo nibalya abashitisha mumbali yamisebo abo beta ati ama street vendors.
eng_translation: Yes those are street vendors.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu naikala nashintilila nakucibumba.
eng_translation: The old man is sitting and leaning in the wall

bem_transcription: Ukuifimbilisha kwansalu uku alemoneka shikulu bantu aline mpepo.
eng_translation: By the way he wrapped himself in these cloths you can tell that he is cold.

bem_transcription: Kuti caba nakutalala echo aifimbile muli ifi ifyakufwala.
eng_translation: It's could be that it's cold that's why he has covered himself with these cloths.
