bem_transcription: Nomba ninshi teti eme aya kun'ganda aingila mucikuulwa umukabileko?
eng_translation: But why can't he get up and go inside where it's warmer?

bem_transcription: Teti cishibikwe limbi apa pene epo asendema.limbi takwata ukwakwikala.
eng_translation: We can't tell maybe that's where he sleeps. maybe he doesn't have a house.

bem_transcription: Umwana umwanakashi umunoono alebutuka.
eng_translation: A small girl is running.

bem_transcription: Kuntu aleya uyu umwana uyu kulemoneka kwali umwaume, ninshi alebutukila bawishi umwana uyu?
eng_translation: There's a man where this girl is running to. could it be her father?

bem_transcription: Teti cishibikwe nakalya iyo but ukuntu alebutulukila ekulya kwine kulemonekela umuntu ulya,
eng_translation: We can't know for sure but she is running torwards the man.

bem_transcription: Uku ali umwana uyu ekuntu bangalila abana?
eng_translation: Is this a playground for kids where this girl is?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, taciishibikwe ico, kuti kwaba fye ni kuncende fye ukwakuti fye mwaya kofye mukwangala umuntu uuli onse kuti aangala
eng_translation: We can't tell for sure. it could be just a place where anyone can go for some leisure time.

bem_transcription: Umwana umwanakashi ali pe wiindo lyeshitima.
eng_translation: A girl child is on the window of the train.

bem_transcription: Umukashana wine uuli pa wiindo alemoneka naikata icintu kumaboko, bushe nicinshi?
eng_translation: The girl on the window is holding something in her hand. What is it?

bem_transcription: Cakulembeleko ico asendele.
eng_translation: It is a pen

bem_transcription: Umukashana wine alemonekamo fye eka mwishitima ili akwelelemo, bushe alimo eko olo bambi emobali nabo?
eng_translation: The girl is the only one visible in the train. Could she be alone in it or there are others?

bem_transcription: Alimo na bantu bena tabalemoneka fye kumulandu wakuti nakufiita.
eng_translation: She is with other people. We just can't see them because it is dark.

bem_transcription: Umuntu natoloka ali mumuulu naikata nakucintu.
eng_translation: A person has jumped, he is in the air and is holding onto something.

bem_transcription: Utu utumantoni toni tulemoneka utwabuuta menshi?
eng_translation: Are these whitish spots water?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Menshi panshi pantu ali pali amenshi.
eng_translation: Yes because there's water below.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo uyu so ninshi aletelela pamenshi?
eng_translation: Is this young man sliding on water?

bem_transcription: Enditta e! ubu ubwangalo aleangala bwapa menshi.
eng_translation: Yes he is surfing

bem_transcription: Umuntu nafwala umbrella alesosa no muntu mubiye kuntashi.
eng_translation: A person is in an umbrella talking to another person.

bem_transcription: uyu wikete umbrella alemoneka kwati mukashana
eng_translation: The one holding an umbrella looks like she's a girl.

bem_transcription: Kuti caba mukashana pantu iyi nindeleshi afwele.
eng_translation: It could be a girl because she is wearing a dress.

bem_transcription: Muntu alelanda nankwe alemoneka nafwala itoloshi kuti aba mulume?
eng_translation: The one she's talking to is in a trousers. Maybe it's the husband.

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya teti cishibikwe lelo lyena kuti baba pamo.
eng_translation: No we can't know for sure but it's possible.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu lilebutuka mumusebo.
eng_translation: A group of people is running in the road.

bem_transcription: Nga aba bambi abali pamacinga?
eng_translation: What about these others on the bicycles?

bem_transcription: Aba bantu bambi bali pamacinga balechecking'a abantu nga apona afenta.
eng_translation: They are checking to see if anyone falls and faints.

bem_transcription: Balebutuka ukucilikana abanakashi nabaume pamo bonse?
eng_translation: They are competing male and female at once?

bem_transcription: Endita e! ubu ubwangalo bwali fye pabalumendo nabakashana ukubutukila pamo.
eng_translation: Yes, this was about boys and girls running together.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu lileculuka pamusebo.
eng_translation: A group of people is crossing the road

bem_transcription: Fikuulwa fyashani ifi ifili mumbali yabantu?
eng_translation: What kind of buildings are these on the sides of the people?

bem_transcription: Ifi ifikuulwa mwaliba ama offices umubombela abantu.
eng_translation: These buildings have offices where people work from.

bem_transcription: Nimutauni nangula emukalale umu abantu bali?
eng_translation: Is this the town center?

bem_transcription: Endita e! abantu bali mukalale.
eng_translation: Yes the people are in town

bem_transcription: Abana abanoono abalumendo baleangala.
eng_translation: Young boys are playing.

bem_transcription: Nowikete icidoli ici mwaume? Temwanakashi uyu ukulolesha imishishi shakwe?
eng_translation: Is the one holding the doll also a boy? is it not a girl when you look closely at the hair?

bem_transcription: Kuti aba mulumendo olo umukashana lelo kwena taciishibikwe kaili ali kunuma.
eng_translation: It could be a boy or a girl. it's difficult to tell from behind.

bem_transcription: Umbi umwana uufwele icabuuta alemoneka uwasekelela.
eng_translation: The boy in white looks happy.

bem_transcription: Kuti aba uwasekelela kumulandu wakuti uyu wine umubiye wikete ici icilubi alelanda fimo ifyasekesha.
eng_translation: It could be that the other one that's holding a doll is saying something funny.

bem_transcription: Namayo nashitata nabekala palunkoto balelanda napali balamya babo.
eng_translation: A man and a woman are sitting in the loan and both are on the phone.

bem_transcription: Nomba bali babili but futi bali busy pama phone.
eng_translation: They are the two of them and yet both are busy on their phones.

bem_transcription: Bali batumina bonse pali balamya babo kubantu abapusana.
eng_translation: Both were called on their phones by different people.

bem_transcription: Imikalile iyi bushe kuti baba mulume nomukashi.
eng_translation: This sitting arrangement could they be husband and wife?

bem_transcription: Kuti caba, kuti caba mulume nomukashi nabaya mukutandala.
eng_translation: It's possible. It could be a husband and a wife who have gone for a walk.

bem_transcription: Banamayo babili nabekala nabapakatila notubotolo muminwe shabo.
eng_translation: Two women are sitting holding bottles in their hands.

bem_transcription: Tubotolo twanshi utu baikete muminwe?
eng_translation: What are these bottles for that they are holding?

bem_transcription: Utu utubotolo balenwamo, balelilamo ice cream.
eng_translation: They are ice cream bottles.

bem_transcription: Ngechi icamuntuntula icilemoneka kunuma nicinshi?
eng_translation: What is this yellow thing behind them?

bem_transcription: Ico icili kunuma yabo lishitima.
eng_translation: It's a train.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu naikala pe tebulo alewamye ifintu.
eng_translation: The old man is sitting on the table repairing things.

bem_transcription: Cinshi ici icintu ico ekete muminwe yakwe?
eng_translation: What is he holding in his hands?

bem_transcription: Ici cintu ekete muminwe cakusumunwinako ka waya eko beta mucingeleshi ukuti sobering wire.
eng_translation: It's a soldering gun used for melting the soldering wire.

bem_transcription: Ninshi shitata uyu nimakanika?
eng_translation: Is this man a mechanic?

bem_transcription: Uyu shitata alalungisha utuntu kuti aba nimakanika.
eng_translation: It's possible because he repairs things.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu ali panshi nakontama alewaminikisha ifintu ifyo balepanga.
eng_translation: An old man is down and has bent down furnishing what is being made.

bem_transcription: Teti ibe ni n'ganda iyi intu balekula apa?
eng_translation: Could this not be a house that they are building?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya taciishibikwe ukulingana nokumona mukati ifyo mulemoneka teti ibe ni n'ganda iyi.
eng_translation: No we can't tell by looking at it on the inside it can't be a house.

bem_transcription: Ngechi icibaketi cakatapa katapa canshi akwete uyu?
eng_translation: What is this green bucket he is holding for?

bem_transcription: Tachishibikwe ifilimo mukati but ukulingana nefyo cilemoneka cakutapilamo amenshi ici.
eng_translation: We can't tell what's inside but by the look of things it could be for drawing water.

bem_transcription: Cikunpiti cabantu uyu cile-enda cilepitana.
eng_translation: A group of people is moving around.

bem_transcription: Cinshi cingalenga abantu ukubuungana so munshila iyakuipatika patika?
eng_translation: What could cause people to be moving like this, pressing on each other?

bem_transcription: Aba bantu cipalile bali pacisankano baleshita shita mumatuuka.
eng_translation: It's like they are buying things from the shops.

bem_transcription: Ukushita fye ifintu ekwingalenga ukubuungana so kwaba nabakapokola?
eng_translation: Just buying things is what could cause this crowd and the police to be present?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Aba bantu cipalile kumyabo balifula sana.
eng_translation: Yes, it's like there are lots of people in their area.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alepeepa fwaka.
eng_translation: An old man is smoking cigarettes.

bem_transcription: Ukuboko kumbi ukwaka shikulu bantu uku nakwikata mumusana, bushe cinshi cingalenga aiminina mumusango wa so?
eng_translation: His other hand is placed on his waist, why might he be standing like this?

bem_transcription: Icingalenga mukwai cakuti limbi nanaka.
eng_translation: It could be that maybe he is tired.

bem_transcription: Bushe nga anaka shikulu bantu ecakulenga ukuti apeepe fwaka?
eng_translation: Is being tired a reason for smoking?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Ecilenga ukupeepa fwaka emwine efyo asala.
eng_translation: Yes. That's his reason for smoking

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alefwembela amabwe yamumpili.
eng_translation: A young man is holding onto rocks of the mountain

bem_transcription: Finshi alecita uyu umulumendo nikwisa alefwaya ukuya.
eng_translation: What is this young man doing and where does he want to go?

bem_transcription: Alepanga ama exercise alekwela alefwaya afike pamuulu wamabwe.
eng_translation: He is exercising. He is climbing and wants to reach the top

bem_transcription: Nomba uku alenina teti apusumuka apona afwa nangu aicena?
eng_translation: Will he not slip and fall and hurt himself or die?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya balakwata intambo isho baikaka abene teti apone kamo fye iyi intambo yapusumuka uko baikakile kwilibwe.
eng_translation: No he can't. they usually have ropes tied around them that hold them. Unless the rope cuts from where it is tied.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alenwa kwibotolo.
eng_translation: The old man is drinking from the bottle

bem_transcription: Libotolo lyanshi ili alenwano, bushe te lyabwalwa?
eng_translation: What bottle is that? Is it not a beer bottle?

bem_transcription: Ukulingana nefyo lilemoneka, lilemoneka lyamoolokoso ili.
eng_translation: From the looks, it's a beer bottle.

bem_transcription: Alikwata imishishi ishikulu kwati mwanakashi.
eng_translation: He has long hair like a lady

bem_transcription: Mungeleshi imishishi shilakula bena.
eng_translation: He is white, their hair grows very much

bem_transcription: Umwana umulumendo naikala namwentula nokumwentula.
eng_translation: A young boy is seated smilling.

bem_transcription: Ni kumusebo elo kumbali yamusebo uku aikele?
eng_translation: Is he seated on the road or on the roadside?

bem_transcription: Apa nipambali yamusebo apo ekele.
eng_translation: He is seated on the roadside

bem_transcription: Utu utubotolo tulemoneka bushe kwali ifyo alenwa uyu umwaume uyu?
eng_translation: These bottles that we can see, was he drinking something?

bem_transcription: Endita e! ifi ifibotolo filelanga ukuti pali ifyo balenwa nabantu ali nabo.
eng_translation: Yes. These bottles indicate that him and the people hes with are drinking something.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabashitata lili pakamana epo lilebombela.
eng_translation: A group of men is working on the river.

bem_transcription: Muli inshi umu bakwelele aba bashitata?
eng_translation: What is in this thing that these men have boarded

bem_transcription: Ici bakwele ciketwe nakucibwato bakwelele.
eng_translation: This thing is held by the boat

bem_transcription: Bushe impompo bafwele nincito nshi bengalabomba pakati ka mumana.
eng_translation: What could they possibly be doing in the middle of the river?

bem_transcription: Kwena imilimo balebomba apa tashishibikwe iyo.
eng_translation: We don't know what they are doing.

bem_transcription: Namayo nashitata balelolesha muli cimashini icikopa icikope.
eng_translation: A man and a woman are looking into the camera.

bem_transcription: Temumpanga umu balekopa?
eng_translation: Is this not in the forest that they are taking photos

bem_transcription: Kuti caba nimumpanga umu balekopela.
eng_translation: It could be in the forest.

bem_transcription: Conse ici icikulu icakukopelako bushe ninshi cikopa apatali?
eng_translation: This big machine that they are capturing with. Does it mean it captures from a long distance?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Umulumendo aleteya ubwangalo ubwitwa mucisungu ati baseball.
eng_translation: A young man is playing base ball

bem_transcription: Umulumendo uujwepele icimupini alefwaya ukuuma kabola?
eng_translation: The young man with the bat wants to hit the ball.

bem_transcription: Endita e! Ubwangalo efyo babuteya nga bakuposela kabola ufwile ukukalopola
eng_translation: Yes thats how the game is played. When the ball is thrown at you, you have to hit it with the bat

bem_transcription: Naba abafwele ifyafiita kunuma nabo bali baleteya.
eng_translation: The one in black behind was also a baseball player.

bem_transcription: Aba abafwele ifyafiita bantu abatungilila ukumona amafunde yaubu bwine ubwangalo buli ubwayana.
eng_translation: The ones in black are referees

bem_transcription: Umulumendo natoloka ne ncinga mumuulu.
eng_translation: the young man has jumped with his bike

bem_transcription: Aimishe shani incinga iyi ukuimya so pamuulu?
eng_translation: How did he Jump with the bicycle so high?

bem_transcription: Alipita pacalundumana ecilenga ukwima mumuulu ifi.
eng_translation: He passed through an elevation. That's why.

bem_transcription: Ninshi ekuti alefwaya ukushumbuluka nayaena mumuulu incinga iyi?
eng_translation: Does he want to spin in the air with the bicycle?

bem_transcription: Efyo cipalile alefwaya ukuipilibula, ale-angala ubwangalo ubwapala ifi fine.
eng_translation: That's what it looks like. That's the game he is playing.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu naiminina alelolela mwituuka.
eng_translation: The old man is waiting in a shop.

bem_transcription: Fyakulya ifi ifitanteme apa ifyo alelolela shikulu?
eng_translation: Is it the food that's lined up that this old man is waiting for?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Fyakulya fili pantashi palya pa table efyo eshile mukushita.
eng_translation: Yes it's the food that is on the table in front that this old man is here to buy.

bem_transcription: Mwituuka mwine tamwali abaleshitisha?
eng_translation: Is there no seller in the shop?

bem_transcription: NOT PLAYING
eng_translation: NOT PLAYING

bem_transcription: Namayo ali nabantu babili abeminine elo alekopa nefikope.
eng_translation: A woman is with two people who are standing as she is taking photos.

bem_transcription: Ishi imwemfu shikwete shitata bushe mwemfu shacishinka nangu ashibikileko fye?
eng_translation: These beards that this man has are they real or they are fake?

bem_transcription: Mwemfu shakwe fye temwemfu shakubikako ishi.
eng_translation: It's his real beard. It's not fake.

bem_transcription: Pali ifyo balemweba apa pene aiminine?
eng_translation: Is there something he was being told where he is standing?

bem_transcription: Ukulingana nefilemoneka, uyu namayo umbi uletonya lamya yakwe balemoneka ngabalelolela ifintu.
eng_translation: According to what can be seen, The lady that's pressing her phone looks like she's waiting for something.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu mumbali yamusebo liletamba abalumendo balecinda.
eng_translation: A group of people in the streets is watching boys that are dancing.

bem_transcription: Kucinda kwashani uku ukwakubika amoolu mumuulu?
eng_translation: What kind of dancing is this with the legs in the air?

bem_transcription: Ishi imicindile shintu beta mucisungu ati break dance.
eng_translation: it's called break dance.

bem_transcription: Abantu bene abalebatamba baiminine fye ukutali?
eng_translation: The people watching are standing at a distance?

bem_transcription: Beminine akatalamukila, ukuti babapele abalecinda incende iikulu.
eng_translation: The are at a distance to give the dancers more room.

bem_transcription: Abakashana babili balelanda mumusebo.
eng_translation: Two ladies are chatting on the street

bem_transcription: Abakashana babili aba bonse balemoneka nabafwala amagalasi, bushe kuti yaba yanshi amagalasi aya?
eng_translation: Both of them are wearing glasses. What could these glasses be for?

bem_transcription: Kuti yaba yakuncigilila ulukungu ululeima mumusebo ukufuma mukutobolwa kwa menso.
eng_translation: It could be to prevent dust from going into their eyes.

bem_transcription: Bushe cibotolo canshi ici cikete umukashana muminwe yakwe?
eng_translation: What is the bottle for that this lady is holding.

bem_transcription: Ici icibotolo ekete ca menshi.
eng_translation: He is holding a water bottle

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alelolesha mucikope.
eng_translation: The old man is looking at the picture.

bem_transcription: Nomba icikopelo cakwe aciloleshe mumuulu, bushe finshi engalakopa mumuulu?
eng_translation: His camera is pointed in the sky. What could he be capturing in the sky?

bem_transcription: Alekopa intanda shamumuulu encito yacikopelo ici cine.
eng_translation: He is capturing the stars of the heavens. That's what that thing he had does

bem_transcription: Cipalile kwati tali eka kuncende iyi, bushe aba bambi nabo finshi balelolesha?
eng_translation: It's like he is not alone in this place. What are these others looking at?

bem_transcription: Aba bambi balelolesha pafikope efyo bakopa kale ifya muulu.
eng_translation: These others are looking at pictures of the sky.

bem_transcription: Umukote naikala mumbali yamusebo.
eng_translation: An old man is seated along the road.

bem_transcription: Uyu kuti caba kwati pali efyo alelolela elo aletushako fye nanaka.
eng_translation: It's like he is waiting for something but he is just resting because he is tired

bem_transcription: Cipalile alelombelekesha mumusebo abantu abalepita.
eng_translation: It's like he is in the streets begging from passerbys.

bem_transcription: Ngechi icibokoshi ekete muminwe kuti acibomfeshe nshi?
eng_translation: What's the box in his hands used for?

bem_transcription: Ici icibokoshi ekete muminwe cintu alembelepo amafya alepitamo.
eng_translation: He is using it to write all the problems he is going through.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo baleteya ubwangalo ubo beta ukuti basket ball.
eng_translation: Some men are playing basketball.

bem_transcription: Ukukutoloka na bola muminwe alefwaya ukuiposela umwakwingishisha?
eng_translation: He is bouncing the ball in his hands, does he want to score?

bem_transcription: Endita e! alefwaya ukwingisha muli kalya akalemoneka aka round.
eng_translation: Yes he wants to score in the net.

bem_transcription: Abantu baleteya nabena, nabeminina fye bena baletamba balemuleka aleingisha?
eng_translation: Are the other players going to just sit back and watch him score?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, tabali fye mupepi nankwe eco alengela ukuti balemutamba uko aletoloka eka.
eng_translation: No, they are just not close to him that's why they are just watching him.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo balelisha inyimbo.
eng_translation: Some young men are playing music.

bem_transcription: Ifi fintu bakwete efili nokupanga ulwimbo?
eng_translation: Are what they are playing used to make music?

bem_transcription: Ifi baikete kuminwe ifyo balebomfya, efyo babomfya pakulisha inyimbo.
eng_translation: Yes, they are music instruments.

bem_transcription: NI mumusebo umu baleimbila?
eng_translation: Are they on the road when singing?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya tacishibikwe nga nimumbali yamusebo lelo mulemoneka fye nimucikuulwa umu.
eng_translation: It's not clear whether it's on the side walk or inside a building.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo natoloka aleingisha umupila muli ka ring.
eng_translation: A young man as jumped as he throws the ball into a basket.

bem_transcription: Ishi iminwe shikete naimwimya uyu pakuti afike apakwingisha?
eng_translation: Are the hands pulling him so that he doesn't score?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya kulaba ukuitolokela fye we mwine.
eng_translation: No, people just jump.

bem_transcription: Pakwingasha ubwangalo ubu bwine baleangala ninshi ufwile wafika apali ici goal?
eng_translation: Are you supposed to reach the goal to score?

bem_transcription: Telyonse ufwile ukutoloka ukufika, lelo lyena kuti waposa uyu wine umupila na panshi pene.
eng_translation: It's not always, you can just throw it even from the ground.

bem_transcription: Banamayo nabashitata nabekala pamacinga.
eng_translation: Some women and men are sited on bicycles.

bem_transcription: Efyo bafwele fili ifyapalana palana nabafwala nefimpompo kumutwe.
eng_translation: The are dressed uniformly with helmets on.

bem_transcription: Ifimpompo bafwele fyakubacingilila ukukanaicena kumutwe nga wapona.
eng_translation: The helmets are meant to protect them incase they fall.

bem_transcription: Balefwaya ukwamba ukucilikana?
eng_translation: Are they about to start competing?

bem_transcription: Efyo cipalile, bali mukwamba ukucilikana ukucofa.
eng_translation: It seems, it should a bike race competition.

bem_transcription: Nakulu naikala aletusha pamupando.
eng_translation: An elderly lady is resting while on a chair.

bem_transcription: Imisango iikalilemo nakulu bantu uyu ilemoneka kwati pali ifilemushupa.
eng_translation: She seems amazed by something, it's clear from the way she's sited.

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya teti cishibikwe alemoneka fye nanaka echo ekalile pamupando.
eng_translation: No, not quite, it seems she's tired and resting on her couch.

bem_transcription: Ninshi nimukalale umu aikele?
eng_translation: Is she in town?

bem_transcription: Kuti caba nimupepi namukalale umu ekalile.
eng_translation: It seems she's close to town.

bem_transcription: Umwanakashi naiminina nakontama nako.
eng_translation: A lady is standing and bent a little.

bem_transcription: Ngechi afwele icilemoneka icakashika kashika bushe pali ifyo cilepilibula?
eng_translation: What's this reddish thing he is wearing, does it mean something?

bem_transcription: Ici afwele icakashika cilembelwepo icilambu awinine ku fintu afuma mukucita.
eng_translation: It has writings on it showing that he won some competition he was in.

bem_transcription: Kuntu bamoda eko bafwala utupimpinya ngotu afwele uyu?
eng_translation: Is this how people dress in modelling competitions?

bem_transcription: Efyo cipalile, efyo bafwala nga balemoda ukuti ule-enda bwino.
eng_translation: It seems, they do this so that they are able to walk well as they are modelling

bem_transcription: Umwaume ale-enda muli ice.
eng_translation: A man is walking on ice.

bem_transcription: Nikulupili uku alekweleka?
eng_translation: Is this a mountain he is climbing?

bem_transcription: Efyo cimoneke lupili uko alekwela.
eng_translation: Yes, it seems he is climbing a mountain.

bem_transcription: Mwela uyo uulemonekela uwabuutulukila buutulukila?
eng_translation: Is that whitish stuff I'm seeing air?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Ulya mwela.
eng_translation: Yes, indeed it is!

bem_transcription: Umwana umulumendo aleangala palunkoto.
eng_translation: A little boy is playing on a lawn.

bem_transcription: Tukooko utu bakobekele kumuulu?
eng_translation: Are those little chicks that have been hang on up?

bem_transcription: Iyo tetukooko utu utwacine, fidoli fye ifi.
eng_translation: They are not actually chicks, they are stuffed toys.

bem_transcription: Ngefi filemoneka ifyafiita kutudoli twine utu kuti fyaba nifinshi?
eng_translation: What of the black stuff on the dolls what could they be?

bem_transcription: Tumabola bakulikililako fye.
eng_translation: Those are just decorated dolls.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alepuuta mwipenga.
eng_translation: A man is blowing a trumpet.

bem_transcription: Ngo yu umbi shikulu bantu aleikala kwimpenga lyalepuuta uyu umbi, finshi alecita?
eng_translation: What of the other man sited next to the man, what is he doing?

bem_transcription: Aletininina ukuti ipenga lilile sana.
eng_translation: He wants to ensure that the trumpet is not over blown.

bem_transcription: Emukuti balalisha pamo bonse balacinjanya?
eng_translation: Does this mean they are exchanging?

bem_transcription: Ee, aba bantu balacinjanya nga balelisha.
eng_translation: Yes, they usually exchange while playing.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alecofa incinga.
eng_translation: A man is riding a bike.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo nafwala icintu pamutwe, bushe kuti caba canshi icintu ici afwele?
eng_translation: What is that thing he is wearing on his head?

bem_transcription: Ici icimpompo afwele kumutwe cakumucingilila ukutaluka mukuicena nga apona.
eng_translation: The thing on his head is an helmet to protect him Incase he falls.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo wine alemoneka naposa sana amano kufyo alecita ifya kucofa incinga ifi fine, bushe cinshi cingalenga ukuposa amano mukucofa fye iyi incinga?
eng_translation: He looks so focused on his bike, why is he this focused?

bem_transcription: Eco aposeleko amano mukucofa incinga nokuibutusha ni pamulandu wakuti balecilikana nabanankwe ukufika bwangu uko baleya.
eng_translation: He is this focused on riding because he is competing with others.

bem_transcription: Namayo ale-ensha incinga mumbali yamusebo.
eng_translation: A lady is riding a bike on the side walk.

bem_transcription: Umu ale-ensha uyu namayo bushe temwakupita abantu, teti apunke abantu abalepitila?
eng_translation: Isn't this side walk meant for pedestrians, won't she hurt someone?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya nakwata belu kuncinga yakwe so kuti alelisisha abantu.
eng_translation: No, she has a bell to signal people.

bem_transcription: Ngechi apapile kunuma kuncinga yakwe?
eng_translation: What's this she's carrying behind her bike?

bem_transcription: Ico icafiita cili pancinga yakwe kunuma cipalile campepo ico afwele.
eng_translation: The black thing behind seems to be her jersey.

bem_transcription: Abana babili baleangala nabamwentula nokumwentula.
eng_translation: Two kids are playing and they are smiling.

bem_transcription: Balemoneka nimumusebo bale-enda abana aba, bushe balifye beka?
eng_translation: It seems they are walking on the road, are they by themselves?

bem_transcription: Tacishibikwe lelo lyena kuti baba no muntu umukulu.
eng_translation: I'm not sure, but there should be an adult with them.

bem_transcription: Imishishi shabo shilemoneka kwati shabanakashi.
eng_translation: From their hair, it seems they are girls.

bem_transcription: Emishishi bakwata ishi shine abangeleshi.
eng_translation: This is the hair that whites have.

bem_transcription: Abantu bale-enda mumbali yamusebo.
eng_translation: Some people are walking on the sidewalk.

bem_transcription: Ninshi umushili ulemonekela uwabuuta buuta?
eng_translation: Does the ground look this white?

bem_transcription: Nakuponena ifyo batila mucingeleshi ukuti snow.
eng_translation: Because snow has fallen.

bem_transcription: Aba bantu nangula abana abalemonekela mupepi ne cimuti bushe baleangala olo bale-enda fye?
eng_translation: Are the people, let me say the kids near the tree playing or just walking?

bem_transcription: Balemoneka baleangala aba bantu.
eng_translation: It seems they are playing

bem_transcription: Nakulu bantu naiminina pa balcony yamuputule yaku n'ganda yakwe.
eng_translation: An elderly lady is standing on the balcony of her house.

bem_transcription: Afumine fye ukwebati apemeko umwela?
eng_translation: Is she out to get some fresh air?

bem_transcription: Kuti cabe fyo fine kuti afuma fye mukupupwa umwela.
eng_translation: Yes it could be.

bem_transcription: Palemoneka kwati kuti pawama ukulatambilapo abantu abalepita nangula icalo.
eng_translation: It seems like a nice spot to watch scenery from.

bem_transcription: Pena palomfwika bwino pantu nipamuulu ulemwena abantu pamuulu abali panshi.
eng_translation: Yes that's true be because it's an elevated ground

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu nakontamika umubiye alemutinya ukumuume kofi.
eng_translation: A man has bent another threatening to punch him.

bem_transcription: Nomba nankwe uo balefwaya ukuuma nakontamafye naena aletambako balefwaya ukumuma?
eng_translation: Is this man that has bent going to just sit back and get punched?

bem_transcription: Cipalile fye kwati balemuanga fye ifyakucita ngo ulefwaya ukuuma umuntu.
eng_translation: No, it seems he is being trained on how to hit someone.

bem_transcription: Ninshi uyu shikulu bantu nikafundisha alefunda umulumendo ifyakulwa?
eng_translation: Is this man a trainer on how to fight?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya tacishibikwe, limbi mubiye fye alemulanga ifyakucita.
eng_translation: That's not known, they could just be friends.

bem_transcription: Bashikulu bantu babili baleshimike lyashi.
eng_translation: Two men are chatting.

bem_transcription: Ninshi balemonekela abepi elo futi abanoono?
eng_translation: Why do they look so short and small?

bem_transcription: Tebepi nakalya icibumba fye icili apa nacibacinga fye kwisamba lyabo.
eng_translation: No they are not small, it's because of the shadow of the wall near them.

bem_transcription: Balemoneka nabafwala ifyamucinshi mucinshi ifyawama.
eng_translation: They seem very well dressed they look smart.

bem_transcription: Pantu bali nipa ma offices apo babombela abantu kufwala ifyacindama.
eng_translation: Because they are at their offices, people are usually well dressed

bem_transcription: Umwana umukashana nomulumendo bali mucintu nabamwentula.
eng_translation: A little girl and boy are playing in something and they are smiling.

bem_transcription: Umukashana alemoneka ekele fye mwenso mwenso.
eng_translation: The little girl seems scared though.

bem_transcription: Cintu bakwelelemo cilapilibuka echo alemonekela uwamwenso.
eng_translation: It's because they are in a merry go round.

bem_transcription: Akalumendo kena kalemoneka akansansa nakomfwa bwino.
eng_translation: The little boy however doesn't look scared.

bem_transcription: Kena nakatemwa ifilecitika ecilengele kalemoneka akansansa.
eng_translation: He is happy to be on it.

bem_transcription: Icinkupiti cabantu nacitantama mumushilwa.
eng_translation: A crowd of people is gathered in a line on the road.

bem_transcription: Mulaini wamusango shani nangula finshi balefwaya ifyakutantamanine icilaini cakula ifi?
eng_translation: What sort of line is this, why would they be gathered in such a line?

bem_transcription: Cipalile baleingila ukuya mucikuulwa cine icili kuntashi yabo.
eng_translation: It's seems they are lined up to enter the building in front of them.

bem_transcription: Bonse aba bantu bakolongene so balefwaya ukwingila muli ici icine ickuulwa.
eng_translation: Are they all lined up to enter this building?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Baleingila mucikuulwa cine ici.
eng_translation: Yes they are

bem_transcription: Abalumendo baleteya ubwangalo bwakuposeshanya umupila.
eng_translation: Some men are playing rugby.

bem_transcription: Ngefi baifimbile kumenso nafyo fibomba inshi?
eng_translation: What are the things they are covering their faces in for?

bem_transcription: Ifi fintu bafimbene nafyo kumenso fyakubacingilila ilyo baletunkana ukukana icena.
eng_translation: They are meant to protect them as they play.

bem_transcription: Nangu bola iyine bakushema pamenso teti fikalipe?
eng_translation: What if a person throws a ball at your face, doesn't it hurt?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, mucimpompo cine ici afwele emo itanuka bola.
eng_translation: No, it bounces off the helmets they are wearing.

bem_transcription: Umukashana nabutuka ne nsapato ishakwata amawilo.
eng_translation: A lady is running with her skating shoes.

bem_transcription: Kulemoneka kuli na umbi umukashana walemukonka panuma, emukutila balecilikana?
eng_translation: There's another lady behind her, are they competing?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Bwangalo bwakucilikana ukubutuka notutwine utusapato.
eng_translation: Yes, they are in a skating competition.

bem_transcription: Ili ibumba lyabantu lilemoneka lyaishile kutamba ababene abantu abalecilikana?
eng_translation: Are all these people here to watch the people competing?

bem_transcription: Endita e! ili ibumba lishile mukulumba aba bene bantu balepepekana.
eng_translation: Yes, they are here to watch the people racing.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu nalisangalala.
eng_translation: The crowd of people is excited.

bem_transcription: Ibumba line ili pali fye umukashana umo abashala bonse balumendo, bushe cinshi pengabela fye umukashana umo?
eng_translation: It's a group of men with only one lady, why can such a crowd have only one lady?

bem_transcription: Echo abalelepo eka namayo cakuti ewaishile fye eka mukusakopwako icikope.
eng_translation: It is because she is the only one here that came to be part of the picture.

bem_transcription: Abalumendo nabekata ifintu muminwe, bushe finshi ifi bekete?
eng_translation: Some young men are holding things in their hands, what are they holding?

bem_transcription: Ifi bekete muminwe shabo mabotolo yabwalwa.
eng_translation: They are holding some bottle of beer.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu aleipika mukichini.
eng_translation: A man is inside the kitchen cooking.

bem_transcription: Nga aka akabuuta akakile mumusana?
eng_translation: What's this white thing tied around his waist?

bem_transcription: Aka akabuuta afwele mumusana kakumucingilila ukukana-ilamfya itoloshi afwele.
eng_translation: It's an apron meant to prevent his trouser from being stained as he cooks.

bem_transcription: Aka akatambala akakile kumutwe nakena pali ifyo kalecingilila?
eng_translation: Is the cloth on his head protecting him from something too?

bem_transcription: Aka akatambala afwele kumutwe kakucingilila ilibe lilaponena mufyo aleipika.
eng_translation: It's to prevent sweat from falling into what he is preparing.

bem_transcription: Namayo naikata akapepala alelangisha umuntu muminwe.
eng_translation: A lady is holding a paper in her hands and showing it to someone.

bem_transcription: Nikeki iyi iili pambale?
eng_translation: Is that cake on the plate?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Icili pambale nikeki.
eng_translation: Yes it's cake.

bem_transcription: Ninshi aba bantu pali ifyo balesefya?
eng_translation: Are these people celebrating something?

bem_transcription: Tacishibikwe nakalya nga balesefya but keki isangwa kuncende uko balesefya.
eng_translation: I'm not sure if they are, but one thing's that cake is found in celebrations.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu naikata icilimba ico babika kumatwi.
eng_translation: A man is holding headphones.

bem_transcription: Incende intu aliko shikulu bantu uyu ilemoneka nge ncende bateyelako umupila.
eng_translation: He seems to be in a football pitch.

bem_transcription: Endita e! Nincende eyo bateyelako umupila.
eng_translation: Yes, it is a football pitch.

bem_transcription: Nga abaleteya bena ninshi nikwisa bali?
eng_translation: Where are the players then?

bem_transcription: Bali kucibansa mukati echo tabalemonekela.
eng_translation: They are inside the pitch and that's why we can not see them.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu ali mwituuka alebelenga necipepala.
eng_translation: A man is in the shop reading a paper.

bem_transcription: Ngo yu umukashana uli kunuma, bushe nao muntu?
eng_translation: Is the lady behind a person?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, icili kunuma fye cikope camukashana, temuntu umwine mwine fye.
eng_translation: No, it's not a lady it's only a lady's picture

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alemoneka ngo mwine we tuuka nangu aishile fye ukushita?
eng_translation: Is this man the shop owner or he is only here to shop?

bem_transcription: Uyu shikulu bantu alemoneka fye ngo muntu uwishilefye mukushita ifintu umu mwituuka.
eng_translation: He looks like someone that's only here to shop.

bem_transcription: Abakashana babili balekolopa panshi yacikuulwa.
eng_translation: Two ladies are mopping inside a building.

bem_transcription: Ngeyi mbeketi ilemoneka iyakashika?
eng_translation: What's this red bucket for?

bem_transcription: Emuntu babikile sopo iyo balebomfya ukukolopela.
eng_translation: That's where there's detergent that they are using as they mop.

bem_transcription: Bushe namayo uuli mupepi nembeketi nakwata icakukolopelako?
eng_translation: Does the lady near the bucket have a mop?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Alingile ukukwata echo afukamine.
eng_translation: Most definitely that's why kneeling.

bem_transcription: Umwana umulumendo napunda umusowa.
eng_translation: A little boy is screaming.

bem_transcription: Bushe ninshi engalalila umwana uyu?
eng_translation: Why is the little boy crying?

bem_transcription: Limbi muntu bamubikile alimonamo icamutinishe.
eng_translation: He might have seen something scary where they put him.

bem_transcription: Ngeci cintu abikileko ukuboko, kuti cabe ati nacimufwanta olo nacimucena?
eng_translation: What of thing he is resting his hand against could it be that it's hurt him?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya tacilemoneka ukwingasha umuntu ukuboko.
eng_translation: No, it doesn't seem like something that can hurt anyone.

bem_transcription: Umwana umunoono alelengela umuntu bamubikile.
eng_translation: A little child is playing where he's been put.

bem_transcription: Bushe alefwaya ukumona banyina abacimubikamo?
eng_translation: Does he want to see the mother that perhaps put him in there?

bem_transcription: Efyo cipalile alefwaya ukulatamba naena abantu.
eng_translation: It seems so, he too wants to be watching people.

bem_transcription: Umwana uyu ninshi bamushile fye palwakwe?
eng_translation: Has this child been left alone?

bem_transcription: Awe nakalya, ngabamushile palwakwe nga acilalila.
eng_translation: No ways, if he was alone he would be crying.

bem_transcription: Namayo alefwembela ulupili.
eng_translation: A lady is climbing a mountain.

bem_transcription: Ngesho intambo shilemoneka ishakashika kashika?
eng_translation: What of those red ropes?

bem_transcription: Intambo isho shakumucingilila ukukanapona panshi nga atelela.
eng_translation: They are meant to protect her in case she slips.

bem_transcription: Ukulolesha pamushili uulemonekela ukutali, palemoneka apakwelele namayo uyu patali.
eng_translation: She is far from the ground, she has climbed up so high.

bem_transcription: Endita e! Apo bakwela palalepa.
eng_translation: Indeed! Usually they climb so high.

bem_transcription: Abantu nabeminina mulubali lwamusebo,bali pancende apalefuuke icuushi.
eng_translation: A place are standing along the road in a place full of smoke.

bem_transcription: Ninshi icushi ici cilefukila so, umusango uyu?
eng_translation: Why is there so much smoke?

bem_transcription: Ici icushi cipalile baleocapo ifilyo.
eng_translation: They are grilling some food.

bem_transcription: Bushe ibumba lyabantu ili ilyakolongene lyaishile mukoca nokulya?
eng_translation: Are they all gathered to roast food?

bem_transcription: Ili ibumba liminine ukuti lishite ifilyo ifyo baleoca apa pantu.
eng_translation: They are here to buy the food being roasted.

bem_transcription: Umwana umwanakashi nakwela pacimpelwa nacimusukusa namumuulu.
eng_translation: A little girl is on a swing that's suspended in the air.

bem_transcription: Pali abalemusunka umwana uyu?
eng_translation: Is there someone pushing her?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya tacishibikwe nomwine kuti aisunka.
eng_translation: It's not certain, she might be pushing herself.

bem_transcription: Umwana uyu pacimpeelwa ici nga apusumuka, bushe nakwata abakumwanka?
eng_translation: If she fell off that swing, is there someone to hold her?

bem_transcription: Teti cishibikwe lelo lyena intambo ishi bashipangila nefyela tashiputuka putuka.
eng_translation: It's not certain, but one thing's for sure, they swing has metal like ropes it can not break.

bem_transcription: Bashitata abali fo nabeminina panse pacikuulwa cakuwamishamo imyotoka.
eng_translation: Four men are standing outside a garage.

bem_transcription: Bashitata bene balemoneka kwati pali ifyo balelolela fiise, bushe ni finshi bengalalolela bashitata aba?
eng_translation: They should be waiting for something, what could it be?

bem_transcription: Ifintu ifyo balelolela ni myotoka ishakwisa mukuwamya.
eng_translation: They waiting for vehicles to clean.

bem_transcription: Bashitata bene beminine fye pakasuba peka peka, bushe teti beminineko mucintelelwe?
eng_translation: They are standing under the sun, can't they stand under some shed?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya teti bengile mucintelelwe, abantu abaleleta imyotoka bafwile balebamona ati epo bali abakuwamye myotoka.
eng_translation: No they can't, they have to stand where they are so that as people bring their cars they are able to see them.

bem_transcription: Namayo naiminina patushimbi namaboko yakwe.
eng_translation: A lady has her body in the air with her hands on a metal bars.

bem_transcription: Bwangalo bwamusango shani ubu?
eng_translation: What sort of game is this?

bem_transcription: Ubu bwangalo bwakupilibuka mumuulu.
eng_translation: It's one of doing flipping in the air.

bem_transcription: Ninshi kulashumbuluka akashimbi akakene nomubili wobe?
eng_translation: Are you supposed to go round this metal bar with your entire body?

bem_transcription: Endita e! kulashumbulukila apa pene nga wapilibuka elo waponena panshi.
eng_translation: Yes, one has to keep flipping their body until they reach the ground.

bem_transcription: Namayo balemukopa kuli shitata nakucimuti ekete kuli ifyoni.
eng_translation: A lady is being captured by a man while holding a tree with a bird on it.

bem_transcription: Fyoni fyashani ifi ifiikele pacimuti ici ifishitiina abantu?
eng_translation: What sort of birds can be sited on a stick that are not afraid?

bem_transcription: Ifi ifyoni fintu fisangwa fye kukamana ifikata utusabi.
eng_translation: These are shore birds.

bem_transcription: Namayo uyu nashitata uyu ninshi baishile fye kukukopa amapikicha nangula ifikope nangu baishile ukuloba isabi?
eng_translation: Is this man and woman here to take pictures or fish?

bem_transcription: Cipalile baishile mukulobe sabi aba bantu.
eng_translation: It seems they are here to fish.

bem_transcription: Bashitata nabeminina balebila nefiishibisho mwitempele.
eng_translation: A man is standing and preaching with some symbols.

bem_transcription: Ifi bafwele bonse ifyapalana ifyabuuta buuta, emkutila enshi?
eng_translation: Why are they both dressed in white?

bem_transcription: Ico bafwalile ifyabuuta, aba bantu bapatili.
eng_translation: Because they are catholic fathers.

bem_transcription: Aka kantu uyu umbi shitata akete muminwe ekantu balebelengapo ifyo balelanda kubantu?
eng_translation: Is the scroll this man holding the one they read from?

bem_transcription: Endita e! Epo balembele ifiishibisho.
eng_translation: Yes they are some writings on it.

bem_transcription: Banamayo babili nabeminina mupepi yacimbaya-mbaya.
eng_translation: Two women are standing next to a vehicle.

bem_transcription: Bamayo aba ninshi baleisa mukukwela icimbaya-mbaya icali mupepi yabo?
eng_translation: Are these ladies about to get on the vehicle nearby?

bem_transcription: Kuti caba nifyo fine, kuti baisa mukukwela ici icine icimbaya-mbaya.
eng_translation: It could be they are about to get on the vehicle nearby.

bem_transcription: Utuntu ekete muminwe namayo matiketi yakwingilila mucimbaya-mbaya?
eng_translation: The lady is holding bus tickets for it.

bem_transcription: Kuti caba nifyo fine, kuti limbi bekete amatiketi yakucimbaya bamya kwine uku.
eng_translation: Yes, it could be so, it could be they are holding tickets for this bus.

bem_transcription: Umukashana nababiye balepeepa fwaka.
eng_translation: A lady with her friends are smoking.

bem_transcription: Ninshi bonse abali kuncende iyi baikele fye balepeepa?
eng_translation: Are all of these here to smoke?

bem_transcription: Efyo cipalile aba abantu bekele balesefya ifintu fimo.
eng_translation: It seems they are celebrating something.

bem_transcription: Ngotu utulemoneka utwabeeka beeka pacafiita ico?
eng_translation: What are those shinny things on that black thing?

bem_transcription: Utu, tuma disiki umo babika inyimbo ishakumfwilako.
eng_translation: These are music discs.

bem_transcription: shikulubantu naikata muminwe alelisha banjo.
eng_translation: A man is playing a violin in his hands.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu uyu waima ukuti nikemba wanyimbo?
eng_translation: Is this man a musician?

bem_transcription: Endita e! nimushika nyimbo uyu shikulubantu.
eng_translation: Yes! Indeed he is.

bem_transcription: Ngeci aikete kuminwe cinshi?
eng_translation: What is he holding in his hands?

bem_transcription: Aka kantu babomfya ukulishishako ka banjo kene aka ututambo twaliba twacepa.
eng_translation: He is holding a bow used in playing his violin in the way it's designed.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lya bantu nalikala mufipuna.
eng_translation: A group of people is sited on chairs.

bem_transcription: Nikwi tempele uku babungene?
eng_translation: Are they gathered in a temple?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya teti mube mwitempele umu, umulandu wakuti abantu bambi nabafwala utusote.
eng_translation: No this can not be a temple, because some people are wearing caps.

bem_transcription: Bushe kuti caba ati abantu bonse abali umu nabaishibana?
eng_translation: Do all these people know each other?

bem_transcription: Kuti caba, cilemoneka aba bantu babombela pamo pene, yali fye ni mitini bakwete.
eng_translation: Yes, it seems they work for the same company and were only holding a meeting.

bem_transcription: Nabwinga alelanda kuli shibwinga.
eng_translation: A bride is talking to her groom.

bem_transcription: Bushe teti ciba ati uyu nabwinga aleimba fye kulwimbo atemenwe?
eng_translation: Could it be that she is singing a song she loves?

bem_transcription: Kwena teti cishibikwe nga kuti alepaata nangu alemwimbilefye inyimbo.
eng_translation: It is unclear whether she is shouting  or singing a song she loves.

bem_transcription: Shikulubantu uyu bushe pali ifyo alefwenya mumutwe nangu asalilepo fye ukwikatamo?
eng_translation: Is this man scratching his head or has just chosen to hold it?

bem_transcription: Imikatile yamumutwe yakupishamo ifintu balekweba kuntu umunankwe.
eng_translation: He is thiking about what his friend is saying to him.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo natoloka kumbali ya waya.
eng_translation: A young man has jumped next to a wire.

bem_transcription: Ngefi ifitaila atantike apa filebomba inshi?
eng_translation: What of these tyres he's arranged here, what are they for?

bem_transcription: Alibikile ukuti afwile ukuculuka kuntashi yafitaila.
eng_translation: He has arranged them so that he can jump in front of them.

bem_transcription: Bushe teti apone necicine alesikiidapo?
eng_translation: Can't he fall off the thing he is skating on?

bem_transcription: Kuti apona nga tatolweke bwino, nga apusa apakwisanyanta.
eng_translation: He can fall if does not jump well, if he misses his step.

bem_transcription: Icikunpiti ca bantu mumusebo ciletamba uko aba balecinda.
eng_translation: A group of people on the road is watching as they dance.

bem_transcription: Bonse abantu baiminina fye kwati nimukalaini?
eng_translation: Are they all standing in a line?

bem_transcription: Endita e! abalakonkapo nga bapwisha ukushana aba abalumendo.
eng_translation: Yes, they are up next when the young man is done dancing.

bem_transcription: Uyu umulumendo waleshana abikile umutwe panshi, bushe pakuti upwishe ukushana teti waicena nangu umukoshi wa-amba ukukalipa?
eng_translation: This young man dancing with his head on the ground, won't he hurt his neck or experience headache?

bem_transcription: Awe nakalya balaterena pakucita ifi, bashungulukila panshi nomutwe wine.
eng_translation: No, they are trained to spin their heads as they dance.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo mumenshi alesansamusha ibumba lya bantu ililemutamba.
eng_translation: A young man is playing in water while a crowd of people watching him.

bem_transcription: Ibumba line ililetamba lilemoneka nalipoosa sana amano kufyo umuntu alecita, bushe cinshi cingalenga ukuposa amano kuli uyu umulumendo?
eng_translation: The crowd seems to be paying attention to what he is doing, why are they this focused?

bem_transcription: Icilelenga cakweba ati nafiwama ifintu ifyo alecita.
eng_translation: It is because he is doing something impressive.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alemoneka naikata intambo, bushe yanshi intambo iyi ekete?
eng_translation: He is holding on a rope. what is it for?

bem_transcription: Iyi intambo ekete yakumucingilila ukuwa mumenshi ilintu alepilibuka.
eng_translation: It is to help him not fall in water as he spins

bem_transcription: Bashitata bali kulubali lwakamana.
eng_translation: Some men are at the seashore.

bem_transcription: Ninshi balemonekela abafiituluka fiituluka abantu bonse aba?
eng_translation: Why do all these people look dark?

bem_transcription: Cungulo bushiku, akasuba kalewa eco balemonekela abafiitulukila.
eng_translation: It is in the evening, the sun is setting that's why.

bem_transcription: Bonse tabafwele nama shati, bushe baishile mukuloba nangu baishile mukowa kukamana uku?
eng_translation: They are all shirtless, are they here to fish or swim?

bem_transcription: Eco bonse bafulile amashati baishile mukowa kukamana kene aka.
eng_translation: It is because they are here to swim.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu lile-enda mumbali yamusebo nomukashana pantashi.
eng_translation: A group of people is walking on the road side with a lady infront.

bem_transcription: Umukashana wine ali pantashi, bushe euletungulula ibumba lya bantu?
eng_translation: Is she the one guiding the group?

bem_transcription: Endita e, namulungika, eulebatungulula ukuntu baleya.
eng_translation: Yes, you are right, she is the one guiding them.

bem_transcription: Bushe cinshi cingalenga ibumba lyabantu ilya so ukukonganika mumusango wa so?
eng_translation: Why could they be gathered in this way?

bem_transcription: Ili ibumba lilefunda abantu pabukankala bwabumi bwabo.
eng_translation: It is because they are learning about their health matters.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu nabekata itumbo lilesansa amenshi.
eng_translation: A group of people is holding on to a hosepipe that is splashing water.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyonse ili likolongene ukulatapilila fye ifi fine baletapilisha kumupaipi uyu uulefumya amenshi?
eng_translation: Are they all gathered to simply splash water from the pipe?

bem_transcription: Ee, endita e, nabekala balesansa ukule-ambuka umulilo.
eng_translation: Yes, this is because they are all trying to put off a fire.

bem_transcription: Bushe umuntu fye umo fye pali aba bantu bonse aba teti akumanishe ukwikata itumbo ililefumya amenshi?
eng_translation: Isn't one person from them able to do this?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya teti akwanishe, itumbo balebomfya lyalikwatisha amaka nga lilefumya amenshi kwikata abengi.
eng_translation: No he can not, the pressure from the hose pipe is too much that they all have to hold on to it.

bem_transcription: Umukashana ale-elela mumwela.
eng_translation: A young lady is floating on air.

bem_transcription: Nomba, bushe cacine umuntu kuti aelela pamwela so? Bushe cishinke ci?
eng_translation: Is a person able to float this way? Is this really true?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, tecishinka, alitoloka fye.
eng_translation: No, this is not true, she just jumped.

bem_transcription: imitolokele ya so bushe teti aicene nga apona?
eng_translation: Can't she fall with this sort of jumping?

bem_transcription: Kuti aicena nga teminine bwino.
eng_translation: Yes she can if she does not land well.

bem_transcription: Banamayo babili nashitata umo baletamba akabwa.
eng_translation: Two ladies with one man are watching a dog.

bem_transcription: Nga ulya umbi umwanakashi uutalwikeko kuli ili bumba lya batatu, bushe ena tali nabena olo nao naibela fye palwakwe?
eng_translation: What of the other lady at a distance is she with them or alone?

bem_transcription: Uyu namayo naibela fye.
eng_translation: She is just alone.

bem_transcription: Nga aka akana kambwa, bushe kamulumendo olo kali nabakashana?
eng_translation: Does this little puupy belong to the man or the ladies?

bem_transcription: Aka akabwa kakwa shikulubantu uufukeme nakena panshi.
eng_translation: It belongs to the young man kneeling next to it.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabanamayo baleteya ubwangalo ubwakuminwe ebo beta ukuti volleyball.
eng_translation: A group of ladies is playing volleyball.

bem_transcription: Nga uyu umulumendo wiminine mupepi naba abakashana baleteya, bushe nifinshi alecita?
eng_translation: What is this man standing near the ladies playing doing?

bem_transcription: Uyu umulumendo wiminine mupepi nabanamayo aletungilila amafunde yamupila.
eng_translation: This man is the referee.

bem_transcription: Kuli iyi ncende bushe takwali abaile ukutamba?
eng_translation: Are there no people watching them?

bem_transcription: Eko bali abaletamba lelo lyena tabalemonekela fye.
eng_translation: Yes they are people watching though we can't see them.

bem_transcription: Shikulubantu alecofa incinga mumabwe.
eng_translation: A man is riding his bike on rocks.

bem_transcription: Nomba ninshi cinshi cingalenga alecofa incinga mumpili shamabwe? Bushe teti aicene? Nikwisa aleya?
eng_translation: Why is riding on rocky mountains? Won't he get hurt? Where is going?

bem_transcription: Enshila bapelwe iya kwendelamo kubwangalo baleteya.
eng_translation: This is the route they are told to use in this game.

bem_transcription: Ngechi icimpompo afwele kumutwe canshi?
eng_translation: What is the helmet on his head for?

bem_transcription: Icimpompo afwele kumutwe cakuicingilila kukuicena nga apona.
eng_translation: It is to protect him incase he falls.

bem_transcription: Shikulubantu mukasote kafiita alepeepa fwaka.
eng_translation: A man in a black hat is smoking a cigarette.

bem_transcription: Ngoyu nakulu uuli kunuma yakwa shikulu, bushe alekopa ena?
eng_translation: Is the man behind him capturing him?

bem_transcription: Awe, alekopa ico ibumba lyonse lyaile mukutamba.
eng_translation: No, he is capturing the entire crowd that is watching.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyonse lilemoneka naliisokela nefya mpepo, bushe cinshi?
eng_translation: Why is the entire crowd in jerseys?

bem_transcription: Bafwalile ifyampepo kumulanu wakwebati bali munshita yampepo.
eng_translation: This is because it's cold.

bem_transcription: Icikunpiti ca bantu cileumfwako inyimbo balelisha.
eng_translation: The crowd of people is listening to the songs they are playing.

bem_transcription: So icinkupiti conse ici calongene ukwisa ukumfwa fye inyimbo isho balelisha kuncende iyi ine?
eng_translation: Are all these people gathered here to only listen to the songs being played in this place?

bem_transcription: Endita e, ici icikunpiti cikumanine fye kukumfwa inyimbo isho balilsha.
eng_translation: Yes, of course they are gathered to listen to the songs.

bem_transcription: Ngoyu umbi umulumendo uninine pacibokoshi, bushe ninshi afulile ishati pacinkupiti ca bantu?
eng_translation: What of the young man on the box,  why is he shirtless before the crowd?

bem_transcription: Ewalesansamusha ibumba ewaleshana no kwimba.
eng_translation: He is cheering the crowd through dancing and singing.

bem_transcription: Ibumba lyabantu lilelolesha ifili kuntashi yabo.
eng_translation: A group of people is looking at something in front of them.

bem_transcription: Bushe finshi bengalalolesha kuntashi yabo muli incende iyafiituluka so?
eng_translation: What can be they looking at in the dark place?

bem_transcription: Cipalile kwati baletamba ubunkolanya.
eng_translation: They are watching a movie.

bem_transcription: Ngoyo mwanakashi alemoneka pantashi bushe ninshi ashintiile munshiku?
eng_translation: Why is the lady holding her head with her hand worriedly?

bem_transcription: Ico ashintile munshiku cakweba ukuti ifyo baletamba fyalibasenda amano.
eng_translation: She is completely taken by the movie.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo alelisha banjo nokwimba inyimbo.
eng_translation: A man is playing his guitar while singing.

bem_transcription: Umulumendo wine alemoneka aliko fye eka, bushe takwaliko nabambi abantu?
eng_translation: It seems he is alone, was he really alone?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, eko bali abantu, eko bali nicofye nakufiita.
eng_translation: No, they are lots of people it's just because it's dark.

bem_transcription: Abantu baliko uku kwine baishile ukutamba umulumendo uyu wine ifyo aleimba?
eng_translation: Are all these people gathered here to watch his musical concert?

bem_transcription: Endita e, baishile mukutamba inyimbo shakwe.
eng_translation: Yes, they are here to watch his music concert.

bem_transcription: Umwana umulumendo napentwa pa menso.
eng_translation: A little boy has his face painted.

bem_transcription: Ukupentwa kwine uko apentelwe umulumendo uyu kulemoneka kwati cinama, cinama cinshi cimoneka so?
eng_translation: He looks like an animal, which animal is it?

bem_transcription: Ici icinama icimoneka so ifyo bamupentele mucisungu batila, Tiger.
eng_translation: He is painted as a tiger.

bem_transcription: Ninshi umwana uyu so alelanda ukutila alefwaya ukufyalwa nga tiger?
eng_translation: Is this to mean that he wanted to be born a tiger?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, bamupenteele pamulandu wakuti alitemwa icinama cakaena.
eng_translation: No he is only painted this way because he loves the animal.

bem_transcription: Iconi cilepupuka.
eng_translation: A bird is flying.

bem_transcription: Bushe iconi ici cikala mumenshi olo caikile fye ukwisa ukunwa amenshi ayali mukamana aka?
eng_translation: Does this bird stay on water or is it just here to drink water from the river here?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, keshile mukusobola utusabi twamukamana.
eng_translation: No, it is here to catch fish from the river.

bem_transcription: Nomba ninshi takakwatilepo akasabi akali konse kukanwa olo kumoolu ukwakwikatilako?
eng_translation: Why does it not have any fish on its mouth or claws?

bem_transcription: Ifi kalemoneka apa ninshi kalebelelela kuli tulya utwalafumina pamuulu utusabi.
eng_translation: From its looks, it being careful to catch some fish that will come on top of the water.

bem_transcription: Icinkunpiti ca bantu ciletota.
eng_translation: A group of people is applauding.

bem_transcription: Bushe incende aliko icinkunpiti ici bushe ni ncende yampepo?
eng_translation: Is this place full of people a church?

bem_transcription: Ee, bali kumapepo.
eng_translation: Yes it is.

bem_transcription: Nga aba bantu bambi abalemoneka ukulolesha ukushilelosha abanabo, bushe finshi balelolesha?
eng_translation: What of this group of people facing the other side what are they looking at?

bem_transcription: Balefwailikisha apakwiminina.
eng_translation: They are trying to find a place to stand.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu ale-ensha ubwato.
eng_translation: A man is steering a baot

bem_transcription: Icintu balimo aba cilemoneka fye mukati kaili tacilemoneka kunse iyo, waishiba shani ati bwato balimo?
eng_translation: It is clear to see the inside but not the outside of where they are, how do you know they are inside a boat?

bem_transcription: Camonekelwa fye kuciwilo aleensha.
eng_translation: It is clear from the wheel he is steering.

bem_transcription: Ibwato iyi yalikwata no mutenge, bushe umuntu umu kuti alala fye bwino?
eng_translation: This boat has a roof, is a person able to sleep well here?

bem_transcription: Endita e, balalala abantu mukati bwino bwino fye.
eng_translation: Yes, people are able to sleep just fine inside.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alekaka insapato.
eng_translation: A man is tying his shoes.

bem_transcription: Shikulu bantu alemoneka kwati muntu acilabutauka ukuyolola, bushe nindungama ukutila ifyo?
eng_translation: He seems like someone who is from running as he stretches, am I right to say so?

bem_transcription: Endita e, namulungama, shikulubantu uyu afuma mukubutuka.
eng_translation: Yes you are right he is from running

bem_transcription: Nge fyakufwala fifwele shikulu bantu fyonse filemoneka fye ifyaputuka-putuka ishati naliputuka amaboko na shoti nayena ili iipi, ninshi afwalilile ifiipi fiipi?
eng_translation: But why is he dressed in ripped clothes, his short sleeved shirt, his shorts, why is he is dressed in short things?

bem_transcription: Ico afwalile ifiipi fiipi cakwebati alebutuka bwino.
eng_translation: He is dressed this way so that he can run well.

bem_transcription: Umwana ali ne mbale ya fisabo ifyalekana-lekana.
eng_translation: A child is with a plate full of different food.

bem_transcription: Bushe umwana uyu bamubikile ifisabo fyonse ati alye nokupwisha fye palwakwe?
eng_translation: Was he given all this food to eat alone and finish?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, ekelepo fye, teti akwanishe nokulya mwana umunoono.
eng_translation: He is just sited, he can not manage to eat all of this food alone, he is too young.

bem_transcription: Kwaliba abana abalya abakwebati ati kuti alya ifisabo fyonse ifi palwakwe fye apwa, bushe uyu teti alye eka?
eng_translation: They are some kids that eat alot such that they are able to finish all of these fruits, can't he finish alone?

bem_transcription: Endita e, ekobaba lelo lyena uyu ena alemoneka akanya sana nameno tayalamena.
eng_translation: Yes some kids eat alot, but this one is too young, he is yet to have teeth.

bem_transcription: Akabwa akafiita kali mumusebo umupite myotoka.
eng_translation: A black dog is on the road full of vehicles.

bem_transcription: Bushe ukufita kwakabwa aka kufiita kwakweba ti efyo kapangwa olo kufiita kwakweba ati keminine apantu pafiita?
eng_translation: Is this just how black the dog naturally is or is it because of where it is standing?

bem_transcription: Ukufiita kwakabwa aka kwakweba ati kali mucintelelwe ico takakopelwe bwino.
eng_translation: It is because it is under the shade, it was not well captured.

bem_transcription: Nge fi fimbaya-mbaya filemoneka, bushe akabwa kaciishila mucimbaya-mbaya cimo pali ifi fyonse?
eng_translation: What of these vehicles, did the dog come here on one of them?

bem_transcription: Iyo nakalya, kalemoneka fye ati kali no muntu umo, uushili napa fimbaya-baya pene apa.
eng_translation: No, it seems it is with someone that is not even driving.

bem_transcription: Bamayo no mwana balebutuka kuntendekelo yakamana.
eng_translation: A woman and a child are running at the source of the river.

bem_transcription: Mukamana mwine mulemoneka utuntu utunoono tunoono,bushe balya bantu?
eng_translation: They are some small things in the river, are they people?

bem_transcription: Ee, namulungika, balya abantu baleowa.
eng_translation: Yes, you are right, these people are swimming.

bem_transcription: Baleowa pamumana wakule fi! Bushe nomba teti banwine?
eng_translation: They are swimming on the river, won't they drwon?

bem_transcription: Awe iyo teti banwine, nabakwata utulebafwilisha uto balekwelapo pakusamba.
eng_translation: No they can not drown, they are getting on some things helping them not to.
